(3, 3, '<h2>Where does it come from?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrary to popular belief, Lorem Ipsum is not simply random text. It has roots in a piece of classical Latin literature from 45 BC, making it over 2000 years old. Richard McClintock, a Latin professor at Hampden-Sydney College in Virginia, looked up one of the more obscure Latin words, consectetur, from a Lorem Ipsum passage, and going through the cites of the word in classical literature, discovered the undoubtable source. Lorem Ipsum comes from sections 1.10.32 and 1.10.33 of &quot;de Finibus Bonorum et Malorum&quot; (The Extremes of Good and Evil) by Cicero, written in 45 BC. This book is a treatise on the theory of ethics, very popular during the Renaissance. The first line of Lorem Ipsum, &quot;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet..&quot;, comes from a line in section 1.10.32.</p>', '2021-12-02 07:37:34', '2021-12-02 07:37:34'),
(4, 6, '<p>A.C.S Medical College and Hospital is a private medical college based in Chennai, Tamil Nadu. It is affiliated to the&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://collegedunia.com/university/25877-dr-mgr-educational-and-research-institute-chennai\" target=\"_blank\">Dr.</a></strong><strong><a href=\"https://collegedunia.com/university/25877-dr-mgr-educational-and-research-institute-chennai\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;M.G.R Educational and Research Institute</a></strong>, which is deemed to be a University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://collegedunia.com/college/56322-acs-medical-college-and-hospital-chennai\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>ACS Medical College</strong></a>&nbsp;offers MBBS Program along with one year of compulsory rotating Resident Internship.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates should be&nbsp;17 years&nbsp;before July 1st of the academic year.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates need to apply to the official website of the NEET to appear for the entrance examination.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates should be 10+2 with Physics, Chemistry and Biology along with English.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates who have studied English courses at 10+2 but not according to the prescribed structure of the National Committee, have to undergo one year of pre-professional training before admission to the Medical College.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates should be&nbsp;passed HSC examination from any other Indian University or recognised board with PCB and English.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates who have taken a pre-professional or pre-medical examination on PCB along with practical tests, after completing higher secondary or equivalent examination are also eligible for the course.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates who have studied the first year of a three year degree course from a recognised university with PCB and appeared for the university examination on the same along with practical tests are also eligible to apply.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates who have passed B.Sc degree and have studied not less than two subjects of Physics, Chemistry and Biology are eligible for MBBS course.</li>\r\n	<li>To be eligible for admission, general category candidates have to secure 50% marks in the qualifying examination and 50% marks in the medical entrance examination&nbsp;<a href=\"https://exams.collegedunia.com/neet\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>NEET UG</strong></a>&nbsp;conducted by CBSE.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission to MBBS Course will be through counselling based on the merit in&nbsp;<strong>NEET-UG&nbsp;</strong>examination conducted by CBSE and a viva voice test conducted by the college.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://acsmch.ac.in/wp-content/themes/mgruniv/images/trans.gif\" style=\"height:5px; width:1px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>ADMISSION</h2>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://acsmch.ac.in/wp-content/themes/mgruniv/images/pic24s.jpg\" style=\"height:209px; width:281px\" /></td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\"><strong>Course</strong><br />\r\n			<strong>M.B.B.S (Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery)</strong>\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n			4 Years 6 Months + 1 Year Internship</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Eligibility</strong><br />\r\n			1)&nbsp;<strong>Age limit</strong>: To be admitted to the Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery (M.B.B.S) Course the candidate should have completed 17 years on or before the 1st July in the academic year he / she is seeking admission.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>2)&nbsp;<strong>Qualifying examination:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The candidate shall be admitted to the First Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS) Course only after he /she has passed a qualifying examination as under:</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>a) The Higher Secondary Examination or the Indian School Certificate examination which is equivalent to 10+2 Higher Secondary Examination after a period of 12 Years of study. The last two years of study should include Physics, Chemistry and Biology with English at a level not less than the core course for English as prescribed by the National Council for Educational Research and Training after the introduction of the 10+2+3 year&rsquo;s educational structure as recommended by the National Committee on Education. (Note: where the course content is not as prescribed for 10+2 education structure of the National Committee, the candidates will have to undergo a period of one year pre-professional training before admission into the Medical College)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(OR)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>b) The Intermediate examination in science of an Indian University/ Board or other recognised examining body with Physics, Chemistry and Biology which shall include a practical test in these subjects and also English as a compulsory subject.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(OR)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>c) The pre-professional / pre-medical examination with Physics, Chemistry and Biology, after passing either the higher secondary school examination or the pre-University or an equivalent examination. The pre-professional / pre-medical examination shall include a practical test in Physics, Chemistry and Biology and also English as a compulsory subject.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(OR)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>d) The first year of the three years degree course of a recognized University with Physics, Chemistry and Biology including a practical test in these subjects provided the examination is a University Examination and candidate has passed 10+2 with English at a level not less than a core subject.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(OR)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>e) B.Sc. examination of an Indian University, provided that he/she has passed the B.Sc. examination with not less than two of the following subjects, Physics, Chemistry, Biology and further that he/she has passed the earlier qualifying examination with the following subjects Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(OR)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://acsmch.ac.in/wp-content/themes/mgruniv/images/pic16s.jpg\" style=\"height:209px; width:281px\" /></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>f) Any other examination which in scope and standard is found to be equivalent to the intermediate science examination of an Indian University/Board having Physics, Chemistry and Biology including a practical test in each of these subjects and English.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>3)&nbsp;<strong>Selection of Students:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The Selection of students to medical course shall be based solely on the merit of the candidates and for determination of merit the following criteria can be adopted.</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>A candidate for admission to medical course must have obtained not less than 50% marks in English and 50 % marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology taken together, both at qualifying and competitive examinations.</li>\r\n				<li>Provided further that in respect of candidates belonging to Scheduled Castes/ Scheduled Tribes and Other Backward Classes (OBC) the marks obtained shall be read as 40 % instead of 50 %.</li>\r\n				<li>To be eligible for competitive entrance examination, the candidate must have passed any of the qualifying examinations as enumerated above at II (2).</li>\r\n				<li>Based on the Merit of the student appeared in the Qualifying examination and Entrance examination / Viva voice conducted by this university.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>4)&nbsp;<strong>Duration of Course of Study</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Four and a half (4 1/2) academic years followed by one year of Compulsory Rotating Resident Internship.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>d) The first year of the three years degree course of a recognized University with Physics, Chemistry and Biology including a practical test in these subjects provided the examination is a University Examination and candidate has passed 10+2 with English at a level not less than a core course.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(OR)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>e) B.Sc. examination of an Indian University, provided that he/she has passed the B.Sc. examination with not less than two of the following subjects, Physics, Chemistry, Biology and further that he/she has passed the earlier qualifying examination with the following subjects Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English</p>\r\n\r\n			<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>First MBBS:</td>\r\n						<td>1 year</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>Second MBBS:</td>\r\n						<td>1 1/2 Year</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>Third MBBS:</td>\r\n						<td>1 year</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>Third MBBS:</td>\r\n						<td>1 year</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n\r\n			<p>One year of compulsory Rotatory Resident Internship.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2021-12-02 12:28:41', '2022-03-04 09:20:35'),
(5, 7, '<p><strong>Course</strong><br />\r\n<strong>M.B.B.S (Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n4 Years 6 Months + 1 Year Internship</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong><br />\r\n1)&nbsp;<strong>Age limit</strong>: To be admitted to the Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery (M.B.B.S) Course the candidate should have completed 17 years on or before the 1st July in the academic year he/she is seeking admission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2)&nbsp;<strong>Qualifying examination:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The candidate shall be admitted to the First Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS) Course only after he /she has passed a qualifying examination as under:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>a) The Higher Secondary Examination or the Indian School Certificate examination which is equivalent to 10+2 Higher Secondary Examination after a period of 12 Years of study. The last two years of study should include Physics, Chemistry and Biology with English at a level not less than the core course for English as prescribed by the National Council for Educational Research and Training after the introduction of the 10+2+3 year&rsquo;s educational structure as recommended by the National Committee on Education. (Note: where the course content is not as prescribed for 10+2 education structure of the National Committee, the candidates will have to undergo a period of one-year pre-professional training before admission into the Medical College)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>(OR)</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>b)&nbsp;</strong>The Intermediate examination in science of an Indian University/ Board or other recognised examining body with Physics, Chemistry and Biology which shall include a practical test in these subjects and also English as a compulsory subject.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>(OR)</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>c) The pre-professional / pre-medical examination with Physics, Chemistry and Biology, after passing either the higher secondary school examination or the pre-University or an equivalent examination. The pre-professional / pre-medical examination shall include a practical test in Physics, Chemistry and Biology and also English as a compulsory subject.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>(OR)</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>d) The first year of the three years degree course of a recognized University with Physics, Chemistry and Biology including a practical test in these subjects provided the examination is a University Examination and candidate has passed 10+2 with English at a level not less than a core subject.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>(OR)</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>e) B.Sc. examination of an Indian University, provided that he/she has passed the B.Sc. examination with not less than two of the following subjects, Physics, Chemistry, Biology and further that he/she has passed the earlier qualifying examination with the following subjects Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>(OR)</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>f) Any other examination which in scope and standard is found to be equivalent to the intermediate science examination of an Indian University/Board having Physics, Chemistry and Biology including a practical test in each of these subjects and English.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>3)&nbsp;<strong>Selection of Students:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Selection of students to medical course shall be based solely on the merit of the candidates and for determination of merit the following criteria can be adopted.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A candidate for admission to medical course must have obtained not less than 50% marks in English and 50 % marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology taken together, both at qualifying and competitive examinations.</li>\r\n	<li>Provided further that in respect of candidates belonging to Scheduled Castes/ Scheduled Tribes and Other Backward Classes (OBC) the marks obtained shall be read as 40 % instead of 50 %.</li>\r\n	<li>Eligibility for admission to MBBS in Deemed Universities is similar to that of NEET. Candidates who will be considered qualified for All India Quota seats on the basis of their rank in NEET.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>4)&nbsp;<strong>Duration of Course of Study</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Four and a half (4 1/2) academic years followed by one year of Compulsory Rotating Resident Internship.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>d) The first year of the three years degree course of a recognized University with Physics, Chemistry and Biology including a practical test in these subjects provided the examination is a University Examination and candidate has passed 10+2 with English at a level not less than a core course.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>(OR)</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>e) B.Sc. examination of an Indian University, provided that he/she has passed the B.Sc. examination with not less than two of the following subjects, Physics, Chemistry, Biology and further that he/she has passed the earlier qualifying examination with the following subjects Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>First MBBS:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>1 year</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Second MBBS:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>1 1/2 Year</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Third MBBS:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;1 year</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Third MBBS:&nbsp;</strong>1 year</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>One year of compulsory Rotatory Resident Internship.</strong></p>', '2021-12-02 18:18:21', '2021-12-02 18:18:21'),
(6, 1, '<p><strong>&nbsp;INSTRUCTIONS to the UG candidates allotted through centralized counselling by MCC of DGHS, New Delhi for admission to MBBS Courses (2022-23)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates who have been allotted through centralized counselling by the MCC of DGHS, New Delhi for admission to MBBS Degree courses in BHAARATH MEDICAL COLLEGE AND HOSPITAL for the academic year 2021-22, are advised to report and complete the admission process strictly within the date and time specified in the&nbsp;<strong>&lsquo;Allotment Letter&rsquo;</strong>&nbsp;issued by the&nbsp;<strong>MCC - DGHS.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A.Instructions for Physical Reporting:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The candidates should report along with&nbsp;<strong>original certificates and Demand Draft</strong>&nbsp;for tuition fees and other fees or UTR No. for Electronic Fund Transfer through RTGS as specified herein below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The certificates/documents to be submitted&nbsp;<strong>in Original</strong>&nbsp;along with&nbsp;<strong>2 sets of photocopies</strong>&nbsp;of the same are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Allotment letter issued by the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.mcc.nic.in/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>MCC of DGHS, New Delhi</strong></a></li>\r\n	<li>NEET (UG) &ndash; 2022&nbsp;Admit Card issued by NTA</li>\r\n	<li>NEET (UG) - 2022&nbsp;Result/Rank letter issued by NTA</li>\r\n	<li>Class X Mark Sheet (both sides of Mark Sheet).</li>\r\n	<li>Class XI Mark Sheet (both sides of Mark Sheet).</li>\r\n	<li>H.S.C. Mark sheet (both sides of mark sheet) or any other equivalent examination.</li>\r\n	<li>Date of birth Certificate (If Metric (10th) certificate does not contain the same)</li>\r\n	<li>Transfer Certificate and Conduct Certificate / Migration certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of Community certificate</li>\r\n	<li>OBC Certificate (dated after 1st April 2020) if applicable</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of Aadhaar Card.</li>\r\n	<li>Ten Passport size &amp; Two Stamp size colour photographs of the candidate (same as in NEET admit card photograph); one Passport size photograph of the candidate&rsquo;s Father and Mother and a Photograph of Local guardian if applicable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates without original certificates/documents shall not be allowed to take admission in Bhaarath Medical College and Hospital.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates who have deposited their original documents with any other Institute/College/University and come for admission with a Bonafide certificate stating that &ldquo;their original certificates are deposited with Institute/College/University&rdquo; shall not be allowed to take admission in the Bhaarath Medical College and Hospital.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>B.Instructions for Online Reporting (Subject to notification from MCC. DG</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The students must pay the Tuition fees by&nbsp;<strong>Electronic Fund Transfer through RTGS/NEFT ONLY</strong>&nbsp;as detailed below (Tuition Fees) and furnish the Details, as mentioned in the Bio-data form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Demand Draft will NOT be accepted for Online Reporting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Acknowledgement mail will be sent on receiving the E-Mail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After due verification of all the documents, admit card will be sent by E-Mail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Allotment letter given by DGHS for admission, is subject to fulfilment of all eligibility criteria prescribed by the NMC and medical fitness of the candidates.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Those who do not fulfil the prescribed eligibility criteria and not found medically fit will not be admitted to the course of study to which they are allotted by the DGHS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Mode of Tuition Fees:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tuition fees specified above may be paid preferably by Electronic Fund Transfer through RTGS/NEFT and payment receipt with UTR No. should be produced at the time of admission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Demand Draft will also be accepted for Physical Reporting. Demand Draft should be drawn in favour of &ldquo;BHAARATH MEDICAL COLLEGE AND HOSPITAL&rdquo; payable at Chennai. (Cheques /Cash will not be accepted).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>General Instructions:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If a candidate fails to report on or before the last date and time specified by MCC of DGHS in the allotment order along with the original Certificates/Documents and/or fails to pay the tuition fee in full by Demand Draft/Electronic Fund Transfer through RTGS/NEFT with UTR No. on the day of admission, he/she will not be permitted to proceed with the admission process and the seat will be considered as vacant and will be duly notified to the DGHS for further action as per rules.</li>\r\n	<li>If any candidate withdraws from the course of study in which he/she was admitted, after the expiry of the cut-off date prescribed for admission to that course of study or in mid-term and the seat is rendered vacant, the first year fee paid will be forfeited and the student will also be required to remit the &lsquo;entire course fee&rsquo; for the remaining years of the course period.</li>\r\n	<li>Students will be governed by all the University rules including rules for refund of fee, disciplinary rules, hostel rules and UGC/NMC Regulations for Curbing the Menace of Ragging etc.,</li>\r\n	<li>At the time of admission, candidates should sign a declaration/undertaking declaring that they shall abide by the rules and regulation of the University including anti-ragging Regulations of the UGC/NMC and observe good conduct and behaviour and that they are bound by the University Rules on payment of fees/refund of fees.</li>\r\n	<li>Both the parents of the students (Father and Mother) shall accompany the students for signing in the declaration form. Another person will not be allowed inside the admission campus.</li>\r\n	<li>If allotted under the category of OBC/SC/ST, the Community Certificate signed by the competent authority shall be produced.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain social distance &amp; Wearing Mask Compulsory.</li>\r\n	<li>Govt.Tamil Nadu /Govt. India Guidelines for COVID-19 protocol should be Strictly Followed.</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate should report only during the normal working hours of the Admission office (10 AM to 5 PM).</li>\r\n</ul>', '2021-12-03 19:35:33', '2022-09-17 12:01:41'),
(7, 8, '<p><strong>ADMISSION PROCEDURE</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As per the Hon&rsquo;ble Supreme Court Order, the admissions into MBBS course for the year 2021-2022 are made through Common Counseling conducted by DGHS (Directorate General of Health Services), Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, Govt. of India, New Delhi. Candidates are hereby informed to visit: www.mcc.nic.in &ndash; &gt; UG &ndash; Counseling -&gt; Deemed / Central Universities (UG Counseling Committee under DGHS) for further information..</p>', '2021-12-06 15:35:25', '2023-02-20 14:47:21'),
(8, 9, '<p>Candidates who have been allotted through centralized counselling by the MCC of DGHS, New Delhi for admission to MBBS Degree courses in Sri Lakshmi Narayana Institute of Medical Sciences, Puducherry for the academic year 2021-22, are advised to report and complete the admission process strictly within the date and time specified in the &lsquo;Allotment Letter&rsquo; issued by the MCC &ndash; DGHS. FEES PAYMENT: ONLY FOR 4.5 YEARS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates without original certificates / documents shall not be allowed to take admission in the allotted Medical College.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ii. Candidates who have deposited their original documents with any other Institute/College/University and come for admission with a certificate stating that &ldquo;their original certificates are deposited with the Institute/College/University&rdquo; shall not be allowed to take admission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>iii. Allotment letter given by MCC-DGHS for admission is subject to fulfillment of all eligibility criteria prescribed by the National Medical Commission (NMC) and medical fitness of the candidates. Those who do not fulfill the prescribed eligibility criteria and not found medically fit will not be admitted to the course of study to which they are allotted by the MCC-DGHS. 1. Recent Passport Size Photos 6 Nos. with parents&nbsp;photos 3 nos.(Furnishing the name &amp; course on the back of the Photo) in a cover shall be produced. 2. NEET(UG) &ndash; 2021 Entrance Exam Admit card 3. NEET(UG) - 2021 Score Statement (Rank Card) 4. Provisional Allotment letter issued by the MCC of DGHS, New Delhi. 5. Class 10 / SSLC (10th)/ or equivalent examination mark sheet 6. HSC (+1, +2) / equivalent examination mark sheet</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Counselling Process (AIQ Quota)</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates applying for Medical/Dental Colleges in&nbsp;<strong>Pondicherry</strong>&nbsp;must register for NEET counselling 2021. Counselling of NEET 2021 for&nbsp;<strong>All India Quota</strong>&nbsp;will be conducted in two rounds in online mode. The counselling will consist of these steps.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Candidate Registration:&nbsp;</strong>Register to the official website.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Choice Filling and Locking (Round 1)</strong>: You have to choose the courses and colleges of your preference and finally lock-in the preferences in the online portal.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Seat Allotment Result (Round 1):</strong>&nbsp;The seat allotment will be published online based on available vacancies and candidate&rsquo;s choices.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Reporting to college:</strong>&nbsp;Those who will be allotted a seat in the first round, will be required to either reject the allotted seat or report to the allotted college and complete the admission formalities.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>New Registration (Round 2):</strong>&nbsp;For candidates who couldn&rsquo;t register in the first round of counselling.</li>\r\n	<li>Fresh Choice Filling and Locking (Round 2):&nbsp;Similar to&nbsp;round 1 mentioned above.</li>\r\n	<li>Seat Allotment Result (Round 2):&nbsp;Similar to&nbsp;round 1 mentioned above.</li>\r\n	<li>Reporting to college (Round 2):&nbsp;Here it is to be noted that, those who will be allotted a seat in the&nbsp;second round of counselling&nbsp;<strong>(15% AIQ Quota)</strong>&nbsp;will not be permitted to vacate their seats as per the orders made by the&nbsp;<strong>Supreme court of India</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2021-12-06 16:10:49', '2022-03-04 07:45:03'),
(9, 44, '<h1><strong>REGISTRATION OPEN FOR ADMISSION SESSION 2022-23</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>REGISTRATION ADMISSION FORM FOR SESSION&nbsp;2022-23&nbsp;<a href=\"http://isfcp.org/i/courses-offered/\">(D.PHARM., B.PHARM.</a></strong></p>', '2021-12-20 15:10:58', '2022-03-12 11:58:44'),
(10, 46, '<p><strong>Santosh Medical College, Ghaziabad Admission Procedure:-</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Santosh Medical College, Ghaziabad offers admissions to the MBBS programme based on NEET UG scores and to M.D and M.S programmes based on NEET PG scores. Students also need to register and qualify for the All India level counselling conducted to offer admissions to various medical colleges of India based on NEET scores. A detailed description of the admission procedure is mentioned below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For MBBS programmes-</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates seeking admission to the MBBS programme need to appear and qualify for NEET (UG).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Based on the qualifying marks achieved by candidates in NEET (UG), they will have to register themselves for NEET (UG) counselling.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates will register themselves for counselling of NEET (UG) on the official website of NEET along with all required documents and payment of fees.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates need to select Santosh Medical College, Ghaziabad as their first preference while doing the choice locking in the NEET UG counselling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates will get admission to the MBBS programme based on NEET (UG) counselling, choice filling, choice locking, document verification, merit and fee payment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For M.D/M.S programmes-</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates seeking admission to M.D/M.S programmes need to appear and qualify for NEET (PG).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Based on the qualifying marks achieved by candidates in NEET (PG), they will have to register themselves for NEET (PG) counselling.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates need to select Santosh Medical College, Ghaziabad as their first preference in the NEET (PG) counselling.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates need to submit all the necessary documents along with required fees while doing the registration for NEET (PG) counselling.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates will get admission to M.D/M.S programmes based on NEET (PG) counselling, choice locking, document verification, merit and payment of fees.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2021-12-20 16:17:04', '2021-12-20 16:17:04'),
(11, 48, '<p><strong>MBBS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates have to apply and appear for NEET UG exam conducted by National Testing Agency (NTA).</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates with required NEET percentile will have to register for AIQ NEET counselling.</li>\r\n	<li>Further candidates have to participate in the counselling process conducted by The Directorate General of Health Sciences (DGHS) on behalf of Medical Counselling Committee (MCC).</li>\r\n	<li>Final admission will be based on the marks secured, participation in the counselling process, seat allotment, document verification and fee payment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>MD/MS/PG Diploma</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates have to apply and appear for NEET PG exam conducted by National Board of Examinations (NBE).</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates have to secure the minimum qualifying percentile and register for the counselling process.</li>\r\n	<li>Further, candidates have to participate in the counselling process conducted by Directorate General of Health Services (DGHS) on behalf of Medical Counselling Committee (MCC).</li>\r\n	<li>Final admission will be based on the marks secured, participation in the counselling process, seat allotment, document verification and fee payment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PhD</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates have to apply online on the website of Pravara Institute of Medical Sciences &ndash; Deemed to be University.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates have to appear and qualify for the entrance exam conducted by the university.</li>\r\n	<li>Further, candidates qualifying the exam will be called for an interview.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates have to qualify for the interview.</li>\r\n	<li>Based on the merit of the entrance exam and performance in the interview, a merit list will be prepared with a weightage of 70 and 30 per cent respectively.</li>\r\n	<li>SET, NET, GATE and M. Phil candidates are exempted from the entrance test and will be called for the interview directly.</li>\r\n	<li>Final admission will be based on the merit of the entrance exam, performance in the interview, university-level document verification and fee payment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>B.Sc Medical Radiology and Imaging Technology Programme</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates have to apply on the website of Pravara Institute of Medical Sciences &ndash; Deemed to be University.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Admission will be based on the merit of the qualifying exam and hence candidates will be shortlisted on the basis of merit.</li>\r\n	<li>Shortlisted candidates will be offered admission on the basis of merit, university-level document verification and fee payment.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2021-12-28 18:10:32', '2021-12-28 18:10:32'),
(12, 49, '<p>Bharati Vidyapeeth Medical College, also known as BVMC Pune, is a constituent college of&nbsp;Bharati Vidyapeeth Deemed University (BVDU) Pune. It is accredited with an &ldquo;A&rdquo; Grade by the National Assessment and Accreditation Council (NAAC) and is recognised by the Medical Council of India (MCI). The College has also been ranked 40 for Medical by India Today in 2020. Currently, the College offers UG, PG, super speciality, certificate and PG diploma programmes in the Medical stream across its 24 departments. It also has an attached hospital approved as the Centre of Excellence for Mother and Child Health &amp; Eclampsia.</p>', '2022-01-05 19:25:42', '2022-01-05 19:25:42'),
(13, 50, '<p>Aarupadai Veedu Medical College (AVMC) is situated at Kirumampakkam in Pondicherry. It was established in the year 2000 and is affiliated to&nbsp;<strong>Vinayaka Mission University (VMU), Salem</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Aarupadai Veedu Medical College</strong>&nbsp;offers five and a half year MBBS at the UG level. The college also offers three-year MD and MS at the PG level along with two-year Diploma courses.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates can submit the application form online.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates having a minimum of 50% marks in English and 50% marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology are eligible to take admission in MBBS.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission in MBBS is done through valid score in&nbsp;<strong>NEET UG</strong>&nbsp;and through the merit list sponsored by the Centralized Admission Committee (CENTAC).</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates with an MBBS degree are eligible to take admission in MD/ MS/ Diploma courses.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission to MD/ MS/ Diploma courses is based on the valid score in<strong>&nbsp;NEET PG</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-01-14 17:35:15', '2022-01-14 17:35:15'),
(14, 52, '<p><strong>Heritage Institute of Medical Science</strong>, commonly referred to as HIMS, was established in 2015 in Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh. HIMS Varanasi is affiliated with&nbsp;Mahatma Gandhi Kashi Vidyapeeth University (<strong>MGKVP</strong>). The courses have been approved by the Medical Council of India. The courses offered by the institute include MBBS at the UG level and MD and MS at the PG level.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;On the basis of&nbsp;<strong>NEET</strong>.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Eligibility for the MBBS course is 10 + 2 with PCB or PCM in extra Biology.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Admissions to MD or MS is on the basis of&nbsp;<strong>NEET PG</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>Eligibility for the MD/MS courses is MBBS.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HIMS</strong>&nbsp;is a leading medical college of Purvanchal, with a vast expanse of hi-tech campus and excellent faculty for students. With 10 lakh sq. ft. of completed construction and the rest in active development, HIMS is easily one of the largest medical institutions in UP.</p>', '2022-01-29 20:40:56', '2022-01-29 20:40:56'),
(15, 53, '<p>The admissions of HIMS are offered at the diploma, undergraduate and postgraduate levels. The streams in which these admissions are offered are medicine &amp; allied sciences,&nbsp;pharmacy&nbsp;and sciences. HIMS Lucknow admissions to MBBS courses are offered on the basis of marks obtained in the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test&nbsp;(NEET). HIMS Lucknow admissions to MD/MS courses are offered on the basis of marks obtained in&nbsp;National Eligibility cum Entrance Test (Postgraduate)&nbsp;(NEET-PG) &nbsp;examination. The final admissions are only offered to students who have taken part in the counselling process, verified their documents and paid the admission fees. HIMS Lucknow admission procedure to various courses along with their eligibility criteria and seats are given below:</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Hind Institute of Medical Sciences Admissions to Undergraduate Courses</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>HIMS Lucknow offers a variety of undergraduate courses. The minimum eligibility criteria for admissions to these courses is that the candidate must have passed 10+2 or its equivalent from a recognised board. The duration of undergraduate courses varies from 2 to 4.5 years. The eligibility criteria and the seats for undergraduate courses are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Hind Institute of Medical Sciences Lucknow Courses, Seats &amp; Eligibility Criteria</h3>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Courses</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Seats</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>GNM</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>100</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<p>10+2 or its equivalent from any recognised board with relevant subjects.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://www.careers360.com/colleges/hind-institute-of-medical-sciences-barabanki/anm-course\">ANM</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>40</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://www.careers360.com/colleges/hind-institute-of-medical-sciences-barabanki/mbbs-course\">MBBS</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>100</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>10+2 or its equivalent from any recognised board with Science stream and must have qualified National Eligibility cum Entrance Test (NEET).</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://www.careers360.com/colleges/hind-institute-of-medical-sciences-barabanki/bsc-nursing-course\">BSc. Nursing</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>50</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>10+2 or its equivalent from any recognised board with Science stream.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>HIMS Lucknow Admission Procedure to M.B.B.S. Course</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates have to apply and appear for NEET UG conducted by National Testing Agency (NTA).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The candidates have to meet the NEET UG cut off and register themselves for the counselling process.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates must choose HIMS Lucknow as their choice during the seat allotment process. It must be noted that NEET counselling has two types: One is All India counselling conducted by DGHS for 15% All India Quota seats and the second one is the state counselling held by each individual state medical council for the rest of the 85% of the seats.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Based on these choices filled and seats available in the college, NEET UG All India Rank, reservation criteria and various factors, candidates are granted admission.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The final selection of candidates is offered after payment of the admission fees and document verification.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Hind Institute of Medical Sciences Admissions to Postgraduate Courses</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>HIMS Lucknow offers a variety of postgraduate courses. The minimum eligibility criteria for admissions to these courses is that the candidates must have passed graduation in relevant fields. The duration of postgraduate courses varies from 2 to 3 years. The eligibility criteria and the seats for undergraduate courses are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>HIMS Lucknow Courses, Seats &amp; Eligibility Criteria</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Courses</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Seats</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Post Basic BSc. Nursing</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>40</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Passed General Nursing &amp; Midwifery (GNM) to be eligible to pursue this course.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>M.D.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>39</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<p>An MBBS degree or its equivalent qualifications as specified by the Medical Council of India (MCI)&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>M.S.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>12</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>M. Sc.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>16</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Passed B. Sc. Nursing and have one year of clinical experience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>HIMS Lucknow Admission Procedure to M.D./M.S. Course</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates have to apply and appear for NEET PG conducted by the National Board of Examinations.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The candidates have to meet the NEET PG cut off and register themselves for the counselling process.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates must choose HIMS Lucknow as their choice during the seat allotment process. It must be noted that NEET PG counselling has two types: One is All India counselling conducted by DGHS for 15% All India Quota seats and the second one is the state counselling held by each individual state medical council for the rest of the 85% of the seats.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Based on these choices filled and seats available in the college, NEET PG All India Rank, reservation criteria and various factors, candidates are granted admission.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The final selection of candidates is offered after payment of the admission fees and document verification.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-01-31 15:34:03', '2022-01-31 15:34:05'),
(16, 10, '<p>College offers admission to MBBS courses under State as well as NEET-UG (All India Quota) score. 15% seats are reserved for NEET-UG qualified candidates.The College also accepts direct admission under Lateral entry scheme from second year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Admission Process</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How to Apply for NEET?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow the below-mentioned steps to apply for NEET:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Visit the official site of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ntaneet.nic.in/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>NEET website</strong></a>&nbsp;and click on the New registration link</li>\r\n	<li>After reading the instructions carefully, click on apply online</li>\r\n	<li>Fill out the required details in the application form like personal details, academic details and other details</li>\r\n	<li>Review the application form carefully and click on Final Submit</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates will be issued NEET login credentials after a successful registration</li>\r\n	<li>Sign in again using the credentials in order to complete the NEET application form</li>\r\n	<li>Scan and upload the required documents like photos of passport size and postcard size, signature, the impression of left thumb, passing certificate of class 10 in the form according to the guidelines</li>\r\n	<li>Make the payment of application using Credit Card/ Debit Card/ Net Banking/ UPI app/ E-Wallet</li>\r\n	<li>Take a print copy of the application form and the confirmation page for further reference</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required for Application:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Scanned copy of Passport size photograph of the candidate</li>\r\n	<li>Scanned copy of Postcard size photograph of the candidate</li>\r\n	<li>Scanned copy of the signature of the candidate</li>\r\n	<li>Scanned copy of left thumb impression</li>\r\n	<li>Mark sheet of 10th</li>\r\n	<li>Mark sheet of 12th</li>\r\n	<li>Valid identity proof</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-03-03 16:32:28', '2022-03-04 00:31:47'),
(17, 55, '<h3>Admission Criteria</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Admission Criteria in Gautam Institute of Pharmacy includes some admission process and eligibility criteria in the available courses which are disscussed below.</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>#</td>\r\n			<td>Course</td>\r\n			<td>Duration</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>Bachelor Of Pharmacy (B.Pharma)</td>\r\n			<td>2 Years</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>Diploma In Pharmacy (D.Pharma)</td>\r\n			<td>2 Years</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>Diploma In Pharmacy (D.Pharma)</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Minimum qualification for admission to Diploma in Pharmacy (D. Pharm) course - pass in any of the following examinations with Physics, Chemistry and Biology or Mathematics.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Intermediate examination in Science;</li>\r\n	<li>The first year of the three year degree course in Science,</li>\r\n	<li>10+2 examination (academic stream) in Science;</li>\r\n	<li>Pre-degree examination;</li>\r\n	<li>Any other qualification approved by the Pharmacy Council of India as equivalent to any of the above examination.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bachelor Of Pharmacy (B.Pharma)</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidate shall have passed 10+2 examination conducted by the respective state/central government authorities recognized as equivalent to 10+2 examination by the Association of Indian Universities with English as one of the subjects and Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics/Biology as optional subjects individually.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Intermediate examination in Science;</li>\r\n	<li>The first year of the three year degree course in Science,</li>\r\n	<li>10+2 examination (academic stream) in Science;</li>\r\n	<li>Pre-degree examination;</li>\r\n	<li>Any other qualification approved by the Pharmacy Council of India as equivalent to any of the above examination.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2>Following documents are required at the time of admission:</h2>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Proof of date of birth (Secondary School Certificate).</li>\r\n	<li>Certificate and mark sheet of 10+2 or equivalent examination</li>\r\n	<li>School Leaving Certificate (SLC) / Migration Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Aadhar Card of the student</li>\r\n	<li>Caste Certificate (in case of SC/ST/OBC) from competent authority</li>\r\n	<li>Four coloured passport size photographs</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-03-10 17:14:59', '2022-03-10 17:14:59');
