(24, 47, '<p><strong>A Student Council will set its own objectives. Some general objectives could include</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To enhance communication between students, management and staff.</li>\r\n	<li>To promote an environment conducive to educational and personal development</li>\r\n	<li>To promote friendship and respect among pupils</li>\r\n	<li>To support the management and staff in the development of the college</li>\r\n	<li>To represent the views of the students on matters of general concern to them.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A Student Council will identify activities that it would like to be involved in organising, although the final decision on the activities of a Student Council should be agreed with college management. A Student Council should not through its activities interfere with or detract from, the authority of college management or the teaching staff of the college. It is therefore not a function of a Student Council to discuss or comment on matters relating to the employment or professional affairs of the Principal, teachers and other staff of the college, or to become involved in any issues that fall within their professional competence.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Student Council and the Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The college shall establish and maintain procedures for the purpose of informing about the activities in the college.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The college shall encourage and help students to set up a Student Council and shall assist a Student Council when established.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The college shall draw up rules for the establishment of a Student Council which shall provide for the selection of members and the dissolution of a Council.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The college will have a role in considering the rules governing meetings of the Student Council, and the conduct of its affairs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Management will give active support to the student council. This could involve designating a student advisor in the college to communicate with the Council on an ongoing basis, as well as assisting the Council in drawing up a constitution and in planning and organising its activities.</p>', '2022-07-18 15:51:18', '2022-07-18 15:51:18'),
(25, 74, '<p>Sri Manakula Vinayagar Medical College and Hospital was formed with the aim of providing good quality education in all fields, be it technical or medical. It aims to pay special attention to the weaker sections of the society to make it an all-inclusive growth. It&nbsp;is located in Pondicherry and was established in the year 2006.&nbsp;The medical college and all the courses/degrees run by are recognized by Medical Council of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Institute offers an undergraduate degree course in MBBS.&nbsp;<strong>SMVMCH</strong>&nbsp;also offers M.D. degree and M.S. degree courses at the postgraduate level.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates applying for the courses have to take the form online from the official website of the institute or in person from the Institute, fill it up and send it before the deadline date,&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates will also have to apply for&nbsp;<strong>NEET</strong>&nbsp;examination and/or CET.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates applying for the postgraduate course have to apply online through the official website of NEET PG conducted by National Board of Examination.</li>\r\n	<li>To apply for the undergraduate degree course, candidates must have passed 10+2 or equivalent exam from a recognized board with 50% marks in aggregate are eligible, while for Postgraduate courses, candidates must have a graduation degree in the relevant subject/course.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission into the undergraduate course will be based on NEET UG Scores conducted by CBSE or Common Entrance Examination (CET) conducted by the Puducherry Linguistic &amp; Religious Minority Medical and Dental College Welfare Association.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission into the postgraduate course will be based on&nbsp;<strong>NEET PG</strong>&nbsp;Scores or CET conducted by the association.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission is done strictly on the basis of Merit in the entrance test.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Admission Highlights 2022</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Name of the Institute</td>\r\n			<td>Sri Manakula Vinayagar Medical College and Hospital, Pondicherry</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Institute Type</td>\r\n			<td>Private</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Established</td>\r\n			<td>2006</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Basic Admission Criteria</td>\r\n			<td>NEET and CET</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Application Mode</td>\r\n			<td>Online</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Name of Entrance&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>National Eligibility cum Entrance Test</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Entrance Mode</td>\r\n			<td>Online</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Counselling</td>\r\n			<td>National and State</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Scholarship</td>\r\n			<td>No</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>Sri Manakula Vinayagar Medical College and Hospital, Pondicherry: UG Admission&nbsp;2022</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Sri Manakula Vinayagar Medical College and Hospital offers MBBS degree courses at the undergraduate level. Candidates must have passed 10+2 or equivalent exam from a recognized board with a minimum of 50% marks in aggregate in the subjects: English, Biology/Botany &amp; Zoology, Physics and Chemistry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates should not be below 17 years of age at the time of Application process. Blind (including color blind), deaf, and/or dumb candidates are not eligible to apply for the course.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Admission is done on the basis of NEET UG Scores or CET Score. The merit list will be prepared for all categories based on candidates scores in NEET UG or CET.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Selection of candidates for admission to the MBBS course will be based on the merit list prepared by the Association on the basis of the entrance examination(s). The admission of the candidates will be provisional subject to the recognition of his/her qualifying CET.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility Table</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>Course</th>\r\n			<th>Eligibility Criteria</th>\r\n			<th>Selection Procedure</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>M.B.B.S.</td>\r\n			<td>Candidates should have passed Class XII or any other equivalent examination from a recognized board with minimum 50% aggregate marks in&nbsp;Physics, Chemistry, Biology</td>\r\n			<td>On the basis of NEET scores/CET Score&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Key Points for UG Admissions:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All SC/ST candidates are eligible for the relaxation of 10%.</li>\r\n	<li>For students belonging to SC/ST, the maximum number of appearances (including the first appearance) permitted to pass the CET is two and one for others.</li>\r\n	<li>The age will be reckoned as on December 31 of the current year. There is no upper age limit prescribed.</li>\r\n	<li>The applicant for admission should be a Resident Indian National and should have studied in schools located in India in the preceding two years except for those admitted against seats reserved for Non-Resident Indians.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Sri Manakula Vinayagar Medical College and Hospital, Pondicherry&nbsp;PG Courses&nbsp;Admission 2022</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Sri Manakula Vinayagar Medical College and Hospital, Pondicherry offers Doctor of Medicine(M.D.) degree in 15 specializations and Master of Surgery(M.S.) degree in 5 specializations at the postgraduate level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates who have passed MBBS from any&nbsp;Medical college which is recognized by the medical council of&nbsp;India. Candidates should have completed his/her rotating internship for one year after passing the MBBS examination on or before April 30 are eligible to apply.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates must have got themselves registered(Provisional or Permanent) with any Medical Council (State or Central) to be eligible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Selection is done on the basis of NEET PG entrance examination&nbsp;or CET conducted by the association. The merit list will be prepared for all categories based on candidates scores in NEET PG or CET. Candidates who clear the cut-off score set by the association will be called for the admission process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Counselling will be conducted by the Pondicherry University and the name of candidates who clear the cut-off score will be forwarded to SMVMCH, Pondicherry to complete the admission process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility Table</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>Course</th>\r\n			<th>Specializations</th>\r\n			<th>Eligibility Criteria</th>\r\n			<th>Selection Procedure</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"15\">M.D.</td>\r\n			<td>Anatomy</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"20\">Candidates should have passed MBBS from any medical college which is recognized by the Medical Council of India. Candidates should have completed his/her rotating internship for one year after passing the MBBS examination on or before April 30.</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"20\">On the basis of NEET PG conducted by the DGHS or CET.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Anaesthesiology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Biochemistry</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Community Medicine</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Dermatology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Forensic Medicine</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>General Medicine</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Microbiology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Paediatrics</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Pathology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Pharmacology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Physiology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Psychiatry</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Radiology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Tuberculosis and Respiratory Diseases</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"5\">M.S.</td>\r\n			<td>ENT</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Obstetrics and Gynaecology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Ophthalmology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Orthopaedics</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>General Surgery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Seat Intake</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Total 46 seats are available for admission in the PG Degree courses and 15 seats in the M.S. degree courses at SMVMCH, Pondicherry.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Sri Manakula Vinayagar Medical College and Hospital, Pondicherry Admission 2022 Application Process</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Aspirants looking for admission in&nbsp;at Sri Manakula Vinayagar Medical College and Hospital, Pondicherry&nbsp;are required to apply through offline mode.&nbsp;Here are the steps to apply:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Necessary forms along with information brochure can be obtained in person on payment of INR 1,000 by cash or Demand Draft.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates can also take the form online from the official website of the Institute</li>\r\n	<li>Fill it up and send it to the SMVMCH before the deadline, along with the demand draft of INR 1,000(in case of online form).</li>\r\n	<li>Demand Draft should be drawn in favor of &ldquo;Sri Manakula Vinayaga Educational Trust&rdquo; payable at Puducherry.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates are required to paste recent colored passport size photograph in the size of 3.5x4.5cm.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates should send the duly filled in application form to the &ldquo;Sri Manakula Vinayagar Medical College and Hospital, Kalitheerthalkuppam, Madagadipet, Puducherry - 605107&rdquo;</li>\r\n	<li>Along with this candidates will also have to apply for National Eligibility cum Entrance Test or CET, as admission to SMVMCH is done on the basis of NEET or CET Scores.</li>\r\n	<li>All the duly filled in application form should be submitted/sent to the College Campus, along with the documents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Documents to be attached:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Self-attested copy of board examination certificate of&nbsp;Class X mark sheet</li>\r\n	<li>Self&ndash;attested copy of the provisional or original certificate of&nbsp;Class XII mark sheet.</li>\r\n	<li>Community certificate, SC/ST/OBC (as assigned by competent authority)</li>\r\n	<li>Self-attested copy of income certificate, in case of OBC non-creamy layer (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Migration Certificate, if applicable</li>\r\n	<li>Transfer Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>One copy of recent passport size photograph to be affixed in the admission form</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-07-19 19:11:46', '2022-07-19 19:11:46'),
(26, 79, '<p>Dr BR Ambedkar Medical College, Bangalore offers MBBS, MD/MS and Diploma courses through NEET (UG/PG/SS). The detailed admission process is mentioned below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For Diploma Courses:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates should fill&nbsp;online application form for admission to the College.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission will be done on the basis of the marks scored in National Eligibility Cum Entrance Test (NEET PG).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For Undergraduate Courses (MBBS):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates should fill&nbsp;online application form for admission to the College.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission will be done on the basis of the marks scored in the National Eligibility Cum Entrance Test (NEET UG).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For Postgraduate Courses (MD/MS):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates should fill&nbsp;online application form for admission to the College.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission will be done on the basis of the marks scored in National Eligibility Cum Entrance Test (NEET PG).</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-08-31 14:16:02', '2022-08-31 14:16:02'),
(27, 81, '<p>Admission to various Programmes at Chandra Dental College Safedabad is based on the candidate&rsquo;s performance in NEET. If you are applying for Chandra Dental College Safedabad, these valuable resources will be beneficial. Let us have a look.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>NEET 2022 Expected Cutoff - Category wise</h3>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>NEET 2022 cutoff</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>NEET cut-off marks</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>General</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>50th percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Soon</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>SC/ST/OBC</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>40th percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Soon</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>General-PwD</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>45th percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Soon</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>SC/ST/OBC-PwD</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>40th percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Soon</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2022-09-05 15:05:27', '2022-09-05 15:05:27'),
(28, 82, '<h2>ADMISSION TO THE BACHELOR OF DENTAL SURGERY PROGRAM (B.D.S) - ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>No Candidate shall be allowed to be admitted to the Dental Curriculum of First year of Bachelor of Dental Surgery (BDS) Course until:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1.&nbsp;</strong>He/she has completed the age of 17 years on or before 31st December, of the year of admission to the BDS course;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.&nbsp;</strong>He/She has obtained a minimum of marks in National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test(NEET- UG) as prescribed in sub-regulation 5 of Regulation II under the heading &ldquo;Selection of students:&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.&nbsp;</strong>In order to be eligible to take National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test (NEET-UG) he/she has passed qualifying examination as under:-</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>a.&nbsp;</strong>The higher secondary examination or the Indian School Certificate Examination which is equivalent to 10+2 Higher Secondary Examination after a period of 12 years study, the last two years of study comprising of Physics, Chemistry, Biology and Mathematics or any other elective subjects with English at a level not less than the core course for English as prescribed by the National Council for Educational Research and Training after the introduction of the 10+2+3 years educational structure as recommended by the National Committee on education;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Where the course content is not as prescribed for 10+2 education structure of the National Committee, the candidates will have to undergo a period of one year preprofessional training before admission to the dental colleges;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>b.&nbsp;</strong>The intermediate examination in science of an Indian University/Board or other recognised examining body with Physics, Chemistry and Biology which shall include a practical test in these subjects and also English as a compulsory subject;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>c.&nbsp;</strong>The pre-professional/pre-medical examination with Physics, Chemistry and Biology, after passing either the higher secondary school examination, or the pre-university or an equivalent examination. The pre-professional/pre-medical examination shall include a practical test in Physics, Chemistry and Biology and also English as a compulsory subject;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>d.&nbsp;</strong>The first year of the three years degree course of a recognized university, with Physics, Chemistry and Biology including a practical test in three subjects provided the examination is a &quot;University Examination&quot; and candidate has passed 10+2 with English at a level not less than a core course;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>e.&nbsp;</strong>B.Sc examination of an Indian University, provided that he/she has passed the B.Sc examination with not less than two of the following subjects Physics, Chemistry, Biology (Botany, Zoology) and further that he/she has passed the earlier qualifying examination with the following subjects-Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>f.&nbsp;</strong>Any other examination which, in scope and standard is found to be equivalent to the intermediate science examination of an Indian University/Board, taking Physics, Chemistry and Biology including practical test in each of these subjects and English.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Marks obtained in Mathematics are not to be considered for admission to BDS Course.</li>\r\n	<li>After the 10+2 course is introduced, the integrated courses should be abolished.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>II.&nbsp;</strong>Selection of Students: The selection of students to dental college shall be based solely on merit of the candidate and for determination of the merit, the following criteria be adopted uniformly throughout the country: Provided that a candidate who has appeared in the qualifying examination the result of which has not been declared, he may be provisionally permitted to take up the competitive entrance examination and in case of selection for admission to the BDS course, he shall not be admitted to that course until he fulfils the eligibility criteria as per above regulations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>i.&nbsp;</strong>There shall be a single eligibility-cum-entrance examination namely &ldquo;National Eligibility-cum Entrance Test (NEET-UG) for admission to BDS course&rdquo; in each academic year.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ii.&nbsp;</strong>In order to be eligible for admission to BDS Course for a particular academic year, it shall be necessary for a candidate to obtain minimum of marks of 50th percentile in &lsquo;National Eligibilitycum-Entrance Test to BDS course&rsquo; held for the said academic year. However, in respect of candidates belonging to Scheduled Castes, Scheduled Tribes, Other Backward Classes, the minimum marks shall be at 40th percentile. In respect of candidates with locomotory disability of lower amendments, the minimum marks shall be at 45th percentile. The percentile shall be determined on the basis of highest marks secured in the All-India common merit list in &ldquo;National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test for admission to BDS course.&rdquo;<br />\r\nProvided when sufficient number of candidates in the respective categories fail to secure minimum marks as prescribed in National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test held for any academic year for admission to BDS Course, the Central Government in consultation with Dental Council of India may at its discretion lower the minimum marks required for admission to BDS Course for candidates belonging to respective categories and marks so lowered by the Central Government shall be applicable for the said academic year only.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>iii.&nbsp;</strong>The reservation of seats in dental colleges for respective categories shall be as per applicable laws prevailing in States/Union Territories. An All India merit list as well as State - wise merit list of the eligible candidates shall be prepared on the basis of the marks obtained in National Eligibility cum-Entrance Test and candidates shall be admitted to BDS course from the said lists only.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>iv.&nbsp;</strong>No Candidate who has failed to obtain the minimum eligibility marks as prescribed in Clause (ii.) above shall be admitted to BDS course in the said academic year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>v.&nbsp;</strong>All admissions to BDS course within the respective categories shall be based solely on marks obtained in the National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>vi.&nbsp;</strong>To be eligible for admission to BDS Course, a candidate must have passed in the subjects of Physics, Chemistry, Biology/Biotechnology and English individually and must have obtained a minimum of 50% marks taken together in Physics, Chemistry and Biology/Biotechnology at the qualifying examination as mentioned in Sub-regulation 2 of Regulation I and in addition must have come in the merit list of &ldquo;National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test&rdquo; for admission to BDS course.<br />\r\nIn respect of candidates belonging to Scheduled Castes, Scheduled Tribes or other Backward Classes the minimum marks obtained in Physics, Chemistry and Biology/Biotechnology taken together in qualifying examination shall be 40% instead of 50%. In respect of candidates with locomotory disability of lower limbs in terms of sub-regulation 4, after the commencement of these amendments, of Regulation 1 above, the minimum marks in qualifying examination in Physics, Chemistry and Biology/Biotechnology taken together in qualifying examination shall be 45% instead of 50%. Provided that a candidate who has appeared in the qualifying examination the result of which has not been declared, he/she may be provisionally permitted to take up the National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test and in case of selection for admission to the BDS course, he/she shall not be admitted to that course until he fulfills the eligibility criteria under Regulation 1.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>vii.&nbsp;</strong>The Central Board of Secondary Education shall be the organization to conduct National Eligibility cum-Entrance Test for admission to BDS course. II. A Common Counselling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1.&nbsp;</strong>There shall be a common counselling for admission to BDS course in all dental educational institutions on the basis of merit list of the National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.&nbsp;</strong>The designated authority for counselling for the 15% All India Quota seats of the contributing States and all BDS seats of Dental Education Institutions of the Central Government universities established by an Act of Parliament and the Deemed Universities shall be the Directorate General of Health Services, Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, Government of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.&nbsp;</strong>The counselling for admission to BDS course in a State/Union Territory, including Dental Education Institutions established by the State Government, University established by an Act of State/Union Territory Legislature, Trust, Society, Minority Institutions shall be conducted by the State/Union Territory Government.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4.&nbsp;</strong>In case any dispute arises on such common counselling, the respective State Government shall refer the matter to the Central Government and its decision shall be final, in this regard.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>KEY INFORMATION FOR BDS AT DJ DENTAL COLLEGE</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>*Duration:&nbsp;</strong>4 years + 1 year internship</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>*Year Started:&nbsp;</strong>1999</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>*University Affiliation:&nbsp;</strong>Dr. B.R. Ambedkar University, Agra (NAAC Accredited)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>*Approved by:&nbsp;</strong>Dental Council of India and University Grants Commission (UGC)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>*Total Seats:&nbsp;</strong>100 Recognized and Approved Seats</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>', '2022-09-05 15:58:58', '2022-09-05 15:59:51'),
(29, 83, '<p>Admission to various Programmes at Dental College Azamgarh is made based on the candidate&rsquo;s performance in NEET. If you are applying for Dental College Azamgarh, these valuable resources will be beneficial.</p>', '2022-09-05 16:29:35', '2022-09-05 16:29:35'),
(30, 84, '<p><a name=\"_Hlk112944512\"><strong>BDS Admissions</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The total number of available seats is 100.</li>\r\n	<li>The Dr. NTR University of Health Sciences in Vijayawada will choose the candidates based on the G.O.s of the Government of Andhra Pradesh.</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance exam: Candidates will be chosen based on how well they perform in the NEET exam, which will be followed by counselling.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All students must be Indian citizens.</li>\r\n	<li>Physics, Chemistry, Biology [Botany/Zoology], and English were required for the 10+2 exam.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates must have passed the NEET.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Management / NRI Quota</p>', '2022-09-06 11:26:41', '2022-09-06 11:26:41'),
(31, 85, '<p><strong>BDS Admissions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The total number of available seats is 100.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All students must be Indian citizens.</li>\r\n	<li>Physics, Chemistry, Biology [Botany/Zoology], and English were required for the 10+2 exam.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates must have passed the NEET.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Management / NRI Quota</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://mymedicalcourse.com/course/bds\" target=\"_blank\">BDS</a></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Duration:&nbsp;<strong>4+1 years ( 4 years academics + 1 years internship )</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Admission through NEET</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2022-09-06 12:32:46', '2022-09-06 12:32:46'),
(32, 86, '<p><strong>Academic staff</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This college offers a solid mix of highly educated, well-trained, and tech-equipped faculty members. Additionally, there are enough non-technical staff members available to foster an environment where students can learn on their own. They are accountable for advancing and maintaining the standards of medical education at the Meenakshi Ammal Dental College &amp; Hospital Chennai in their capacity as faculty members of the organisation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2022-09-06 12:58:32', '2022-09-06 12:58:32'),
(33, 87, '<p>Saveetha Dental College and Hospital was established in the year 1988. Located in Chennai, the college offers UG, PG, Fellowship, and Doctoral courses. It has 21 award-winning departments with 137 faculty members. Candidates are admitted to BDS and MDS courses through National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test. Those interested in taking admission shall apply online for admission. The college provides all the admission related information on its official website.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Admission to BDS and MDS courses is given through NEET-UG and&nbsp;<strong>NEET-PG</strong>&nbsp;conducted by NBE.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Admission will be done on basis of DGHS Centralised counselling.</li>\r\n	<li>Selected candidates must fill the form for final mop-up counselling.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-09-06 15:19:42', '2022-09-06 15:19:42'),
(34, 88, '<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Institution offers BDS &amp; MDS programs recognized by the Dental Council of India. Sree Balaji Dental College &amp; Hospital teaching hospital attached to the Institution provides all levels of holistic health care including major super-specialty services and provides excellent training opportunities to the students of the Academy.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>BDS DEGREE</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Duration - 4 years + 1 year Internship</li>\r\n	<li>Eligibility marks - As per DCI norms</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Academic Qualifications &amp; Eligibility :&nbsp;</strong>Candidates who have passed HSC examination (Academic Stream of 10 +2 curriculum) of any State/CBSE/ISC or any other examination recognized as equivalent thereto, with the group of subjects specified below and obtained the minimum eligible marks prescribed are eligible to apply for admission to the course concerned.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>DCI Norms:</strong>Candidates should have obtained a minimum of 50% of marks (in case of SC/ST/OBC 40%) taking together Physics, Chemistry &amp; Biology and pass in English in the qualifying examination.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Age Limit:</strong>&nbsp;Candidates should have completed 17 years of age as on 31st December of the academic year. Date of birth given in the HSC/CBSE/ISC marks sheet or in the Birth Certificate/ Passport shall be taken for computing age of the candidate.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-09-06 15:49:43', '2022-09-06 15:50:03'),
(35, 89, '<p><strong>Admission through NEET</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Internship&nbsp;in&nbsp;BDS&nbsp;(Main&nbsp;aims&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Dental&nbsp;Internship)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Improve interns&#39; knowledge about dentistry.</li>\r\n	<li>Boost your clinical aptitude.</li>\r\n	<li>Develop self-assurance in one&#39;s abilities and skills. Boost your communication abilities.</li>\r\n	<li>Develop your professionalism.</li>\r\n	<li>Develop your research skills in science.</li>\r\n	<li>Boost dental projects run by volunteers and the community.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-09-06 16:51:33', '2022-09-06 16:51:40'),
(36, 91, '<p>Admissions in the courses offered by the college and the eligibility criteria required by the candidates are as per the rules, regulations and norms laid down by The Dental Council of India (<a href=\"http://www.dciindia.org.in/\">http://www.dciindia.org.in</a>), Tamilnadu Dr. M.G.R Medical University (<a href=\"http://web.tnmgrmu.ac.in/\">http://web.tnmgrmu.ac.in</a>) and Selection Committee, Govt. of Tamil Nadu (<a href=\"http://www.tnhealth.org/\">http://www.tnhealth.org</a>) and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tnmedicalselection.org/\">www.tnmedicalselection.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>For further information contact us.</p>', '2022-09-07 14:02:16', '2022-09-07 14:02:16'),
(37, 92, '<p>Below is the Admission procedure for the compulsory courses which come under&nbsp;<strong>JKKN Dental College Komarapalayam</strong>. The candidate requested to go through with the given instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test) is a national medical entrance test. Students who wish to pursue their career in the medical field, like MBBS, BDS, Ayush, etc., from India and Abroad have to qualify for this entrance test. As per the official notice released by the NTA, the NEET UG 2022 exam date is July 17, 2022. The NTA started the registrations for NEET 2022 for over 16 lakh aspirants on&nbsp;<em>April 6 at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.edufever.com/neet-nta-nic-in/\" target=\"_blank\">neet.nta.nic.in</a></em>. Candidates can register for the undergraduate&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.edufever.com/mci-affiliated-medical-colleges-in-india/\" target=\"_blank\">medical</a>&nbsp;exam till the last date of NEET 2022 registration, May 6, 2022. The exam will be held in 545 India and 14 cities&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.edufever.com/category/study-abroad/\" target=\"_blank\">abroad</a>.</p>', '2022-09-07 15:50:28', '2022-09-07 15:50:42'),
(38, 94, '<p>The duration of the BDS program is four years plus&nbsp;one year compulsory rotatory internship. During this period, the student is required to be engaged in full-time study at this institution. Selection of students is based on the policies of the State Government.</p>', '2022-09-08 12:36:30', '2022-09-08 12:38:56'),
(39, 95, '<p>The successful completion of a BDS degree requires the student to complete 4 years of academic study, in addition to one year of Compulsory Rotatory Residential Internship (CRRI). Admissions to the BDS Course is done as per the regulations of the Dental Council of India (DCI).</p>', '2022-09-08 13:30:27', '2022-09-08 13:30:27'),
(40, 96, '<h2>ELIGIBILITY</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>BDS</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A candidate should have passed the Higher Secondary Examination HSC (10+2)/PDC academic examination or any other qualification recognized as equivalent thereto, with Physics, Chemistry, Biology / Botany, Zoology 40% of marks in aggregate for SC/ST and 50% marks in aggregate for General category.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>MDS</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates for admission to the first year of M.D.S Post Graduate Degree Dental Course shall be required to :</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>have qualified for the B.D.S Degree of this University or any other University recognised as equivalent thereto by the authority of this University and the Indian Dental Council and obtained permanent registration from any of the State Dental Councils.</li>\r\n	<li>have passes B.D.S Degree examination and completed one year of C.R.R.I.<br />\r\n	(or)<br />\r\n	One year of House Surgeon ship in a recognised Dental College, if they belong to old regulations;<br />\r\n	(or)<br />\r\n	Three years of experience in Dental practice after the B.D.S qualification and registration with the State Dental Council.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Age limit</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidate admitted to the first year BDS Course should have completed the age of 17 years at the time of admission or would complete the age on or before 31st December of the year of admission.</p>', '2022-09-09 15:48:43', '2022-09-09 15:48:43'),
(41, 100, '<h1>Admission Criteria of BDS</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. The candidate must attain the age of 17 on 31st of December, of the year of admission to the BDS course.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;The candidate must have passed the higher secondary examination or India school certificate examination which is equivalent to 10+2, higher secondary examination. The candidate must have obtained 50% marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology and must have qualifying marks in English. For SC, ST or OBC the minimum marks shall be 40%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The candidate must have obtained a minimum qualifying mark in NEET UG for the said academic year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Selection</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The college has 100 seats for BDS&nbsp;Course, Seats are filled up through NEET (National Eligibility Cum Entrance Test)&nbsp;/ As per the direction of GOI/DCI/Govt. of Rajasthan from time to time.&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>', '2022-09-13 15:34:58', '2022-09-13 15:34:58'),
(42, 103, '<ol>\r\n	<li>The B.D.S. course offered by EDCH provides deep insight into the science and practice of Dentistry. For admission please fill the application form neatly and attach the documents enlisted on the back of application form the fee is to be deposited by Demand Draft along with the application form.</li>\r\n	<li>A candidate should have secured not less than 60% marks in aggregate of PCB (Physics, Chemistry &amp; Biology) in 12th standard examination.</li>\r\n	<li>Application forms duly filled should be sent by post or submitted in person at the office of Eklavya Dental College and Hospital, Delhi-Jaipur Highway, Kotputli, Distt. Jaipur or at any of the designated centres as decided by Govt. of Rajasthan from time to time.</li>\r\n	<li>Selection of candidates will be made on the basis of merit as par the result of the written test conducted by the NEET(National Eligibility and Entrance Test)&nbsp;and as per the norms of the Dental Council of India, University of Rajasthan, State Govt. rules &amp; regulations, other governing bodies regulations and as per applicable decisions of Hon&rsquo;ble Supreme Court &amp; High Court of Rajasthan.</li>\r\n	<li>Selected candidate will be called for counseling by the concerned or designated agency. Candidates are requested to come prepared with all the documents as informed/advertised</li>\r\n	<li>Viva voce would be conducted after counseling of short listed students. Viva test is based on the subjects of P.C.B. Syllabus of 12th standard class to check candidate&rsquo;s knowledge of these subjects. Selection committee will conduct viva test. Finally selected candidates would be admitted to B.D.S course and they will be required to deposit the fees.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission of foreign and NRI students will be subject to the specified norms of the DCI &amp; Govt, of Rajasthan.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Annual intake of Students :</strong>&nbsp;The annual intake of students in the B.D.S. course is 100.&nbsp;Eligibility Criteria :</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The candidate should have completed :</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The age of &nbsp;17 years at the time of admission or shall complete this age on 31st December of the year of his/her admission, provided the candidate is being admitted to the five year BDS course.</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate should have passed the 2-year Intermediate or equivalent examination with science subjects, namely Physics, Chemistry and Biology from a recognized Indian University or Pre-University (Intermediate Board).</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate should have secured not less than 50% marks in aggregate of the above (PCB) subjects at the qualifying or competitive examination conducted on similar lines as the qualifying examination conducted by a competitive body.</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate should be medically fit and bear good moral character.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-09-13 22:55:20', '2022-09-13 22:55:20'),
(43, 105, '<p>On the basis of competitive entrance examination regulation, a candidate must have passed in the subjects of Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English individually and must have obtained a minimum of 50 % marks taken together in Physics, Chemistry and Biology at the qualifying examination and not less than 50 % marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology taken together in the competitive examination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In respect of candidates belonging to scheduled castes, scheduled tribes or any other categories notified by the government the marks obtained in Physics, Chemistry and Biology taken together in qualifying examination and competitive entrance examination(NEET National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test ) be 40 % instead of 50 % as stated above</p>', '2022-09-14 16:20:00', '2022-09-14 16:20:00'),
(44, 14, '<p>The college admission is 100 per year, and since the college is affiliated to the State owned The TN Dr MGR Medical university, 65 seats are admitted by the Government Merit list through centralized counselling and the remaining 35 seats are also admitted through Government counselling for the management quota. The fee structure of both the Government quota and Management quota is fixed by the fee fixation committee appointed by the Government of Tamilnadu, which changes yearly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students who have passed the NEET qualifying examination and have passed 12th Board examinations only are eligible to apply for the BDS course. 50% is the eligibility for all students except for SC and ST students 40 % is the eligibility criteria. Qualified NEET students, who have passed their 12th Board examinations, have to apply to the Tamil Nadu State Government -Medical Education Department for centralized counselling, both for the government quota and management quota. The State Government prepares a merit list according to the NEET qualifying marks and calls the students for counselling for both the state government quota and management quota.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>ELIGIBILITY FOR ADMISSION</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Tamil Nadu Dr M.G.R Medical University stipulates the following Eligibility criteria for admission to the BDS course: Candidates with 50% marks on aggregate in Physics, Chemistry, Biology (Botany/Zoology) and English at the qualifying examination at the end of 12 years of study for all categories except for scheduled caste and tribe who are eligible with 40% aggregate. Graduate students should have one of the following subjects as a major viz. Physics, Chemistry, Botany, Zoology or should have passed the earlier qualifying examination with the above subjects. Students who have studied abroad, the equivalency of qualification as determined by the Association of Indian Universities and should have passed in the subjects of Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English upto 12th standard with 50% marks. Candidates should have completed the age of 17 years at the time of admission or complete the age on or before 31st December of the years of admission to the first year BDS course. The students who want to join BDS should appear for the NEET examinations and should have qualified in that.</p>', '2022-09-17 13:01:15', '2022-09-17 13:01:15');
INSERT INTO `admission_process` (`id`, `college_id`, `description`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(45, 112, '<p>The candidate shall have passed 10+2 or its equivalent examination from any recognised Board with Physics, Chemistry, Biology and have obtained a minimum of sixty per cent marks taken together in Physics, Chemistry and Biology in the case of general category and fifty per cent marks in the case of the Scheduled Castes, Scheduled Tribes and Other Backward Classes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b.&nbsp;The B.A.M.S Degree programme is on 31st December&nbsp;every year9. The course duration is five years with a study period of three years and a one-year internship period and the option for a two-year extension course.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Medium of instruction</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>The medium of instruction for the programme shall be English.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The following Original Documents to be submitted at the time of admission<br />\r\n			1. NEET marks card<br />\r\n			2. 10th / SSLC marks card<br />\r\n			3. 12th /PUC marks card<br />\r\n			4. Transfer certificate<br />\r\n			5. Migration certificate ( outside Karnataka students)<br />\r\n			6. Caste certificate / income certificate ( SC, ST &amp; OBC students)<br />\r\n			7. Photocopy of Aadhar card<br />\r\n			8. 10 passport size photographs</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Admission Procedure</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Application forms are available in the college office from the admission counter and submit after filling it duly. After receiving the duly filled in applications, candidates would be informed about the remaining admission formalities.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2022-09-23 14:23:10', '2022-09-23 14:23:10'),
(46, 114, '<ul>\r\n	<li>For admission to BAMS course,the candidate must have passed the two year PUC/Equivalent Examination (Listed with RGUHS) with English as one of the language, and physiscs,Chemistry &amp; Biology as optional subjects with minimum of 50% of Marks in the aggregate of the relevant Sciences subject i.e.,Physics,Chemistry &amp; Biology of the II year PUC /Equivalent Examination, are available.</li>\r\n	<li>Age must be minimum 17 years at the time of admission</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate who have passed the B.Sc part I Degree Examination of any University or equivalent Examination conducted by statutory Universities or Boards with Science subject namely Physics, Chemistry &amp; Biology or Botany &amp; zoology and secured 50% of marks in the aggregate are eligible for admission to I BAMScourse,provided the candidate has passed the PUC Examination with Physics, Chemistry ,Biology and English as one of the languages.</li>\r\n	<li>NEET (UG) eligibility is Mandatory for UG</li>\r\n	<li>NEET (PG) eligibility is Mandatory for PG</li>\r\n	<li>All the admission made by the college to the first year of BAMS course are provisional and subject to approval by the Rajiv Gandhi University of Health Sciences, Bangalore.The institute is not responsible for any loss due to non &ndash; confirmation of admission by the University.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-09-23 16:17:57', '2022-09-23 16:17:57'),
(47, 115, '<h3>Bachelor of Ayurveda, Medicine and Surgery</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Duration: 5 1/2 years<br />\r\nEligibility: 10+2 passed with 50% in Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English.<br />\r\nAffiliation: RAJIV GANDHI UNIVERSITY OF HEALTH SCIENCES, Bangalore</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>As WHO has accepted Ayurveda as alternative medicine, one can do courses and practice Ayurveda medicine. BAMS (Bachelor of Ayurveda Medicine and Surgery) is a 5 1/2 years bachelor&#39;s degree offered by a university and approved by CCIM (Central Council of Indian Medicine) and the Department of AYUSH (Ayurveda, Yoga, Unani and Homeopathy). BAMS is designed for 5 1/2 years in this 4 1/2 years classroom training along with practical in Ayurveda hospitals and 1 year full-time internship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BRANCHES OF AYURVEDA FOR FURTHER STUDIES.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Kayachikitsa&ndash; Internal Medicine</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Shalakya Tantra &ndash; Ears, Nose, and Throat.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Vishagaravairodh Tantra Toxicology</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Kaumarabhritya Pediatrics</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Shalya Tantra Surgery</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Bhuta Vidya &ndash; Psychiatry</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Vajikarana Aphrodisiacs</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Rasayana Rejuvenation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A BAMS graduate can do masters in any of the above said branches in any CCIM approved Ayurveda medical college.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CAREER OPPORTUNITY IN AYURVEDA</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As Ayurveda is an accepted alternative medicine by WHO, there is a huge demand for Ayurveda doctors worldwide. As Ayurveda is rooted in treating the patient rather than diseases, people from all over the world look forward to Ayurveda for its healing power where allopathic medicine fails to deliver.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;BAMS doctors can practice Ayurveda medicine his/her own.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;BAMS Doctor can set up an Ayurveda clinic</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;A person who has completed BAMS can join any Ayurveda hospital. There is a dearth of qualified Ayurveda doctors in India.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;A BAMS completed graduate can do master&#39;s (MS) in any Ayurveda academic branch.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SCOPE OF AYURVEDA</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ayurveda is a complete or holistic system that integrates the mind, body and spirit. Divine plants that sustain long life and good health are now being rediscovered. Many renowned families of Vaidyas, who are specialized in certain branches of Ayurveda, are practicing ayurveda medicine in India. Today there is a revival of the ancient culture and traditions inherent to Ayurveda, which is a true gift of the ancient civilization to the modern world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>FIRST YEAR</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Padartha vigyan and ayurved itihasa</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Sanskrit</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Kriya shareera</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Rachana shareera</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Maulik siddhanta evum astanga hridya</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>SECOND YEAR</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Dravyaguna vijnan</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Agadtantra, vyavahar-ayurved evum vidhivaidyak</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Rasashastra evam bhaishajyakalpana</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Charakasamhita -purvardha</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>THIRD YEAR</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Rog-nidan</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Swasthavritta</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Prasuti tantra evum stri roga</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Kaumarbhritya parichaya</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Charak samhita (uttarardha)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>FOURTH YEAR</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Kayachikitsa</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Panchkarma</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Shalya tantra</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Shalakya tantra</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Research methodology and medical statistics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Compulsory internship</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Duration of internship: 1 year</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The student will join compulsory internship programme after passing the final professional examination. The internship programme will start after declaration of the result of final professional examination. The period of internship will be one year.</p>', '2022-09-28 15:45:14', '2022-09-28 15:45:14'),
(48, 116, '<p>The course is designed to produce holistic health practitioners and clinicians as well as lifestyle counselors and complements any health professional licensing a student may already have earned. The course offers the best level of Ayurveda education and training available in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>B.A.M.S. (Bachelor of Ayurvedic Medicine &amp; Surgery)/ AYURVEDA ACHARYA</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Intake: 100 seats.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility: Pass in 10 +2 or equivalent with 50% in PCB</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For SC/ST 45% in PCB(Applicable only within Karnataka Students).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET Eligibility</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Duration of the course:4 &frac12; year + 1-year compulsory internship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PG Courses</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course is designed to give participants a foundation in the principles and practice of Ayurveda. Ayurveda is inherently a science of self-healing and as such the course requires that students undertake it in that spirit. The teaching of the course involves both theoretical and practical learning in order to help students develop into the essence of this ancient healing tradition.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFour P.G Specialties started from the Academic year 2013-14 and 03 more specialties commenced from 2015-16.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Seven P.G. Specialties and available seats are:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>1. M.D. in Kayachikitsa(AYURVEDA VACHASPATI) with 05 seats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. M.D. in Panchakarma(AYURVEDA VACHASPATI) with 05 seats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. M.D. in Dravyaguna (AYURVEDA VACHASPATI) with 05 seats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. M.S. in Shalakya Tantra (AYURVEDA DHANWANTARI) with 05 seats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. M.S. in Shalya Tantra(AYURVEDA DHANWANTARI) with 05 seats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. M.D. in Shareera Kriya(AYURVEDA VACHASPATI) with 05 seats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. M.D. in Swasthavritta (AYURVEDA VACHASPATI) with 05 seats</p>', '2022-09-28 16:11:56', '2022-09-28 16:11:56'),
(49, 117, '<h3>Bachelor of Ayurvedic Medicine and Surgery Degree Course</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This course is of 5 and a half years duration including 4 and a half academic years and a year of compulsory Internship.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>I BAMS &ndash; 1 year</li>\r\n	<li>II BAMS &ndash; 1 Year</li>\r\n	<li>III BAMS &ndash; 1 year</li>\r\n	<li>IV BAMS &ndash; 1 year 6 months</li>\r\n	<li>Internship &ndash; 1 year</li>\r\n</ul>', '2022-09-28 17:19:53', '2022-09-28 17:20:01'),
(50, 11, '<p>For MD MS admissions in any college across Tamil Nadu, one needs to qualify the NEET PG examination which is the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses in Medicine conducted by the National Board of Examinations in Medical Sciences (NBEMS).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application window for the NEET PG 2023 exam which is to be held on 5th March, 2023 is closed now but the Final Edit Window to rectify any uploaded image such as Photograph, Signature or Thumb impression will be open from 14th to 17th February, 2023.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other important dates are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Admit Card Issue 27th February, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date of Examination 5th March, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Result Declaration 31st March, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of Contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.5al1t8wgg1o9\"><strong>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.klknfo3lh3n8\"><strong>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.srbizwij1jc9\"><strong>NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.4fk7jg6yp2tr\"><strong>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.ycqxce8ft8uc\"><strong>Counselling for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.qzwt9oimr6g0\"><strong>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.a22qg5786pt4\"><strong>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Tamil Nadu</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-02-20 16:03:22', '2023-02-20 16:03:22'),
(51, 128, '<p>Programme and Courses offered:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Under Graduate (UG) Programme in ENGINEERING &amp; TECHNOLOGY with &nbsp;Medical Sciences (NBEMS).For MD MS admissions in any college across Tamil Nadu, one needs to qualify the NEET PG examination which is the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses in Medicine conducted by the National Board of Examinations in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Post Graduate Course</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD (Doctor Of Medicine )</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MS ( Doctor Of Surgery )</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD General Medicine</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MS ENT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Psychiatry</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MS General Surgery</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Community Medicine</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MS OBG</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Pathology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MS Orthopaedics</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Pharmacology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MS Anatomy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Radio Diagnosis</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MS Opthalmology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Dermatology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Anaesthesiology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Physiology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Biochemistry</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Pediatrics</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MD Microbiology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>Course Details</h2>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h2>Course Duration</h2>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h2>3 Years</h2>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h2>Eligibility</h2>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h2>The eligibility criteria for an MS degree is a minimum of 50-60% marks in the UG level, along with a valid GATE score to get admission in the MS course.</h2>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Under Graduate Course</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>MBBS</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Course Details</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Course Duration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>5 Years</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Eligibility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pass in PUC / +2 Or Equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2023-02-21 12:09:04', '2023-02-21 12:09:04'),
