(3, 'List of Medical Degree in India', '<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>A medical degree is awarded to those who complete their degree in UG, PG or any special course. To obtain this degree, the candidate must complete the course and internship in the given period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Undergraduate medical degrees</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Students need to fulfil the eligibility criteria and qualify for the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test to get an undergraduate medical degree. Every year there are over 83,920 MBBS,29,949 BDS, 525 BVSc and 50,720 BHMS/BSMS/BAMS/BUMS/BNYS medical degrees are awarded in India. Only candidates who complete the eligibility criteria quality in the NEET exam complete the 5.5 years, of course, are awarded with the undergraduate degree.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Following are the undergraduate medical degrees in India&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; MBBS &ndash; Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; BDS &ndash; Bachelor of Dental Surgery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; BAMS &ndash; Bachelor of Ayurvedic Medicine and Surgery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; BUMS &ndash; Bachelor of Unani Medicine and Surgery.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; BHMS &ndash; Bachelor of Homeopathy Medicine and Surgery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; BYNS &ndash; Bachelor of Yoga and Naturopathy Sciences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; B.V.Sc and AH &ndash; Bachelor of Veterinary Sciences and Animal Husbandry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Postgraduate medical degrees</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to be eligible to for these national level entrance exams, the candidate must have an MBBS Degree or MBBS provisional pass certificate offered by the concerned University /college. They should have completed 12 months of internship. The candidate must possess a provisional or permanent registration certificate issued by the National Medical Commission or State Medical Council.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Following are the postgraduate medical degrees in India.&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Specialities in Doctor of Medicine (MD)</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Anaesthesiology</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Biochemistry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Community Health&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Dermatology</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Family Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Forensic Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. General Medicine</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Microbiology</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Paediatrics&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Palliative Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11. Pathology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12. Skin and Venereal diseases&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>13. Pharmacology</p>\r\n\r\n<p>14. Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15. Physiology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>16. Preventive and Social Medicine</p>\r\n\r\n<p>17. Psychiatry&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>18. Radio- diagnosis</p>\r\n\r\n<p>19. Tuberculosis and Respiratory diseases&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>20. Emergency and critical care</p>\r\n\r\n<p>21. Nuclear Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>22. Transfusion Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>23. Tropical Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Master of Surgery ( MS) Speciality in Doctor of medicine&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Ear, nose and throat.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. General surgery</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Ophthalmology</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Orthopaedics&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Obstetrics and Gynaecology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Dermatology, Venerology and Leprosy</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'list-of-medical-degree-in-india', '164275498583.png', '164275498583.png', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-01-21 14:49:45', '2022-01-21 15:47:14'),
(4, 'Medical Courses Without NEET', '<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>As there is an increase in competition every year and insufficient medical colleges, many students have to let go of their dream to become doctors. But, now, there are several courses offered to students in the medical field that one can do without appearing for the NEET Examination. There are many job opportunities in the medical field other than MBBSBDS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>These are the list of courses one can opt for without having to give the NEET examination</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>BA in Psychology&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The duration of this course is 3 years, and the average salary is 4.9 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.O.Th (</strong><strong>Bachelor of Occupational Therapy)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The duration of this course is 4 years, and the average salary is 3.5-5 lakhs per annum.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Pharm&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The duration of this course is 4 years, and the average salary is 2-5 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc in Biotechnology&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 3 years, and the average salary is 4 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc in Cardio Vascular Technology</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 3 years, and the average salary is 3-30 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc in </strong><strong> </strong><strong>Genetics&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 3 years, and the average salary is 4-5 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc in Microbiology&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 3 years, and the average salary is 3.3 &ndash; 4.5 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>8.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc in Nutrition</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 3 years, and the average salary is 50k -2.5 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>9.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Tech in Biomedical&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 4 years, and the average salary is 3.9 lakhs per annum.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>10.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc Nursing&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 4 years, and the average salary is 3-8 lakhs per annum.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>11.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc Animal Husbandry and Dairying</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 3-4 years, and the average salary is 2-3 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>12.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc cyber forensic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 3-4 years, and the average salary is 6 lakhs per annum.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>13.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc Fisheries&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 3 years, and the average salary is 5-10 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>14.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc Cardiovascular Technology</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 4 years, and the average salary is 4-20 lakhs per annum.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>15.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>B.Sc Agricultural Science&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 4 years, and the average salary is 5-9 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>16.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>BNYS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The course duration is 5.5 years, and the average salary is 2-3.5 lakhs per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'medical-courses-without-neet', '164275687720.png', '164275687720.png', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-01-21 15:21:17', '2022-01-21 15:50:44'),
(5, 'Specialities in Doctor of Medicine ( MD)', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Doctor of Medicine is a program of three years Postgraduate course degree in medicine which studies in detail about medicine in various specialisations after MBBS. The course duration is 3 years. The average salary of an MD graduate generally varies from 3-6 lakhs. Top colleges include AIIMS, PGIMER, CMC and a lot more. Medical doctors or applicants possessing M.B.B.S degrees in their under graduation are eligible to apply for this course. To excel in the field of medicine applicants opt for a Doctor of Medicine or MD degree for specialisation in post-graduation. After successfully completing this degree candidates are eligible to work as a physician.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Following are the MD Specialisations :</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Aerospace Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Marine Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Radiotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Anatomy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Medical genetics&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Respiratory Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Anaesthesiology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Microbiology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Sports Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Biochemistry&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11. Nuclear Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12. Immunohematology and blood transfusion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>13. Biophysics&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>14. Paediatrics&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15. Infectious disease&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>16. Community Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>17. Palliative Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>18. Tropical Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>19. Dermatology, Venereology and Leprosy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>20. Pathology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>21. Hospital Administration&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>22. Emergency Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>23. Pharmacology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>24. Radio Diagnosis&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>25. Family Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>26. Psychiatry&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>27. Health Administration&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>28. Forensic Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>29. Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>30. Geriatrics&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>31. General Medicine&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>32. Physiology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>33. Pulmonary medicine</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'specialities-in-doctor-of-medicine-md', '164326652361.png', '164326652374.png', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-01-21 17:36:19', '2022-01-27 12:55:23'),
(6, 'Types of NEET Scholarships and its benefits for students', '<p>NEET is a medical entrance examination that a student has to get through in order to pursue a degree like MBBS, BDS, AYUSH. NEET entrance exam is the most important exam for those who want to make a career in the medical field, and this requires a lot of dedication and perseverance over the years.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are an innumerable number of private and government colleges that offer scholarships for NEET to support the students so they can make the life of their dreams. Since NEET coaching is slightly expensive, not everyone can afford it, creating a hole in the pocket. This is why scholarships were launched to support and sponsor students so that their true potential is not lost or in vain.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>These are some of the popular NEET scholarships and their benefits</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&bull; <strong>AIPMTS ( All India Pre-Medical Scholarship Test)</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>AIPMTS is the most popular scholarship in India for medical students. Its motto is to support students who have been qualified for the NEET examination and want to pursue their education in medicine. AIPMTS provides candidates who wish to enroll in BDS/MBBS/BUMS/BHMS a platform to showcase their talent. 100% tuition fee is taken care of if the candidate is from a government college and 50 % if the candidate is from a private college.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&bull;<strong> </strong><strong>Central Sector Scheme of Scholarship for College and University Students</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This scholarship is granted by the Human Resources Development Ministry&rsquo;s Department of Higher Education for qualified NEET Examination students. This scholarship is directly granted to students coming from low-income families. This scholarship is also applicable for general category students who fall under the reserved category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&bull; <strong>Combined counselling Board scholarships for Professional courses</strong>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This scholarship is offered to students who have qualified for NEET examinations and want to pursue their desired careers. This scholarship covers the hostel fee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>&bull;</strong><strong> </strong><strong>Nationwide Education and Scholarship Test</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This scholarship is held in 65 cities across India. The sole purpose of this scholarship is to motivate the students.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'types-of-neet-scholarships-and-its-benefits-for-students', '164327411255.png', '164327411231.png', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-01-27 15:01:52', '2022-01-27 15:01:52'),
(7, 'MBBS Admissions 2023', '<p>In order to save time and get a seat before the deadline, it is advised to be well prepared for the admissions process before it starts. Knowing the qualifications and eligibility requirements for admission aids in making an informed decision and helps minimise last-minute confusion and panic. The higher demand for medical practitioners in India causes seats in the MBBS programme to fill up more quickly than those in other programmes. Thus, being prepared beforehand and being aware of the admissions process enables one to seize the chance early. The eligibility criteria, admission process as well as the relevant documents necessary for admission to MBBS colleges in India are provided below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#Eligibility Criteria\">Eligibility Criteria</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#Documents Required for MBBS Admission\">Documents Required for MBBS Admission</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#List of documents required at the time of admission:\">List of documents required at the time of admission:</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#Admission procedure for MBBS admissions\">Admission procedure for MBBS admissions</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#Counselling Schedule\">Counselling Schedule</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility Criteria</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The applicant must be at least 17 years old when they are admitted. The oldest person allowed is 25.</li>\r\n	<li>He or she must have obtained a minimum cumulative score of 50% in the CBSE or another board of equal standing&#39;s 10+2 exam. Students who fall within the reserved category are given a 5&ndash;10% relaxation.</li>\r\n	<li>The four required core subjects for the 10+ 2 exam are English, Physics, Chemistry, and Biology.</li>\r\n	<li>The applicant must pass the National Eligibility and Entrance Test, or NEET, administered by the National Testing Agency (National Testing Agency). The chances of admission are improved with a higher score. The NEET exam for MBBS 2023 will be held on 7th May, 2023 and the registrations for the same shall begin soon.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Documents Required for MBBS Admission</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is always advisable to keep all necessary documentation ready once the NEET results are announced and the admissions process is about to start, such as Class 12th marksheets, School certificates, NEET result, Character certificate, other certificates for admission under quota reservations (such as reserved category- SC/ST/OBC, sports quota), and residence documentation (as may be required by some colleges).To avoid last-minute problems, it is advised to preserve sets of attested copies of each document.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>List of documents required at the time of admission:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NEET-UG Admit Card / Hall Ticket, Selection Letter and Statement of marks</li>\r\n	<li>12th Standard Mark Sheet</li>\r\n	<li>10th Standard Mark Sheet</li>\r\n	<li>2th Standard Passing Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>10th Standard Passing Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Grade Equivalence Certificate issued by Principal (if grades are mentioned on 10th Std / 12th Std mark sheets)</li>\r\n	<li>Nationality Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Domicile Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Physical Fitness Certificate from MBBS doctor (as per NEET-UG brochure)</li>\r\n	<li>Last School/College Leaving Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Migration Certificate</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Admission procedure for MBBS admissions</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>As admission windows are typically only open for a brief period of time, be vigilant and aware of the application deadlines and dates for various government and private colleges around India.</li>\r\n	<li>Apply online, pay the required fees, and register for the specific college.</li>\r\n	<li>The NEET score and quota reservations determine which individuals are shortlisted, and those candidates are subsequently contacted for counselling.</li>\r\n	<li>After submitting the required paperwork and payment, admission is complete.</li>\r\n	<li>Make a very careful judgement about your selected college if you are invited for counselling by more than one college because the seat you once turned down cannot be given to you again.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Counselling Schedule</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>There are typically two counselling sessions: the first is for registration, fee payment, and seat allotment. Students who enrolled for round 1 but were unable to secure a spot should register for round 2. In Round 2, new registrations are accepted as well (if required).</li>\r\n	<li>Seats under the State Quota and the All-India Quota are subject to the two rounds of counselling. Counselling&#39;s Mop-Up Round and Stray Vacancy Round are primarily for places at Central or Deemed Universities.</li>\r\n	<li>The All India Quota has the following quota guidelines: 15% for SC, 7.5% for ST, 25% for OBC, 10% for EWS, and 5% for those with disabilities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to become a doctor, put all of your effort into it and the results of your labour will definitely bring success.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'mbbs-admissions-2023', '167394154235.jpeg', '167394414022.jpg', 1, '2023-01-17', 'MBBS Admissions 2023', 'It is always advisable to keep all necessary documentation ready once the NEET results are announced and the admissions process is about to start, such as Class 12th marksheets, School certificates, NEET result, Character certificate, other certificates for admission under quota reservations (such as reserved category- SC/ST/OBC, sports quota), and residence documentation (as may be required by some colleges).To avoid last-minute problems, it is advised to preserve sets of attested copies of each document.', NULL, '2023-01-17 13:45:42', '2023-01-17 14:29:00'),
(8, 'MBBS Admissions 2023 for Madhya Pradesh students', '<p>The application process for admission to the MBBS program in 2023 officially started with declaration of the NEET UG exam date as on May 7, 2023. Medical students should be aware of the many public and private medical institutions in their respective states in order to make an informed choice of institution as they get ready for this year&#39;s MBBS in India admissions. In a short while, the registration period for the NEET UG exam will start.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Private medical colleges for <strong>MBBS admissions in Madhya Pradesh:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Madhya Pradesh, there are 14 government and 11 private colleges that offer MBBS admission; however, MCI has cancelled admission for 50 M.B.B.S. seats at Sukh Sagar Medical College and Hospital in Jabalpur for the academic year 2021&ndash;2022. So it is advisable to check for the same before taking admission in Sukh Sagar Medical College and Hospital.</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:736px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:57px\">\r\n			<p>S.No.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:228px\">\r\n			<p>Name of the College</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:102px\">\r\n			<p>Place</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:123px\">\r\n			<p>Governing Body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-