(11, 'MBBS Admissions 2023 for Rajasthan students', '<p>The application process for admission to the MBBS program in 2023 officially began with the NEET UG 2023 exam date on May 7, 2023. The registration period for the same will soon begin, so medical students getting ready for this year&#39;s MBBS in India admissions should be aware of the numerous government and private medical colleges in their respective states in order to make an informed choice of institution.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Private MBBS colleges in Rajasthan</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Rajasthan, there are a total of 17 government and 9 private colleges that offer admission to MBBS programs, but only 1 of them is affiliated with a deemed university. The other 16 are all affiliated with private universities in Rajasthan that have been approved by the Medical Council of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, admission for the session 2021-22 was cancelled by the National Medical Commission for American International Institute of Medical Sciences, Bedwas, Geetanjali Medical College &amp; Hospital,Udaipur and Ananta Institute of Medical Sciences &amp; Research Centre, Rajsamand. Kindly check for the same before applying to these institutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:722px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:61px\">\r\n			<p>S.No.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:226px\">\r\n			<p>Name of the college</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:133px\">\r\n			<p>Place</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px soli