(18, 'NEET PG Exam 2023 (Application Details)', '<p>The National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses in Medicine (NEET PG) is conducted by the National Board of Examinations in Medical Sciences (NBEMS) for admission to various MD/MS or Diploma courses across India. This is a single <strong>entrance exam</strong>ination that determines the eligibility and ranking for PG- <strong>MD/MS admissions </strong>to various medical colleges of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application for the NEET PG exam which is to be held on 5th March, 2023 is out and available on the official website of NBEMS.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://cdn3.digialm.com/EForms/configuredHtml/1815/80166/Registration.html\">NEET PG 2023 (digialm.com)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The last date of submitting the application form for NEET PG exam is 27th January, 2023 (till 11:55 PM)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of Contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"General Guidelines:\" name=\"General Guidelines:\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1n-OsJsjVsprjKAkgpSRcwmwpZN2_GKdtBjgsiSspiPM/edit#heading=h.mp21p2if6dgi\"><strong>General Guidelines: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Important Dates for Application:\" name=\"Important Dates for Application:\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1n-OsJsjVsprjKAkgpSRcwmwpZN2_GKdtBjgsiSspiPM/edit#heading=h.62onyv52rnrq\"><strong>Important Dates for Application: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Application Fees for NEET PG 2023\" name=\"Application Fees for NEET PG 2023\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1n-OsJsjVsprjKAkgpSRcwmwpZN2_GKdtBjgsiSspiPM/edit#heading=h.h4w08eb6gl9k\"><strong>Application Fees for NEET PG 2023 </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Official Helpline Portals\" name=\"Official Helpline Portals\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1n-OsJsjVsprjKAkgpSRcwmwpZN2_GKdtBjgsiSspiPM/edit#heading=h.h441l6hqiq4t\"><strong>Official Helpline Portals</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>General Guidelines:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>It is a computer-based test (online) of a duration of 210 minutes i.e 3 hours and 30 minutes.</li>\r\n	<li>It is conducted once a year for the current academic session only.</li>\r\n	<li>The qualifying NEET PG Cut off percentile is 50 for GN, 45 for GN with PwD &amp; 40 for SC/ST/OBC/PwD categories&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG examination is meant for admission to PG courses in medicine for the following:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>50% of All India quota seats for all States or Union territories of India</li>\r\n		<li>All Private Medical Colleges, Universities or Deemed Universities of India.</li>\r\n		<li>Armed Forces Medical Institutions</li>\r\n		<li>State quota seats for all States/UTs of India</li>\r\n		<li>Post MBBS DNB/NBE Diploma Courses</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG is not for admission to the following institutions\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>AIIMS, New Delhi</li>\r\n		<li>Other AIIMS</li>\r\n		<li>PGIMER, Chandigarh</li>\r\n		<li>JIPMER, Puducherry</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>NIMHANS, Bengaluru</li>\r\n	<li>Sree Chitra Tirunal Institute for Medical Sciences and Technology, Trivandrum</li>\r\n	<li>No other State Government/Private Medical College or University shall conduct any separate <strong>entrance exam</strong>ination for PG admissions in medical courses.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Important Dates</strong> for Application:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Start-date of Online Registration for NEET PG exam: 7th January, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Last date for submission of Application: 27th January, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Application Edit Window (Any information/documents can be edited&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>except Name, Nationality, Email, Mobile&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>number and Test City) : 30th January, 2023 to 3rd February, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Final Edit Window 14th February, 2023 to 17th February, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(To rectify Uploaded Images such as Photograph,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Signatures or Thumb Impressions)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Admit Card Issue 27th February, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date of Examination 5th March, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Result Declaration 31st March, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cut-off for Internship eligibility for NEET PG 2023 30th June, 2023* (Revised)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*The earlier cut-off for completion of internship for being eligible for NEET PG 2023 was 31st March, 2023 which has been revised to 30th June, 2023 by The Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (MoHFW), Govt of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Application Fees for NEET PG 2023</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The application form fee for NEET PG 2023 will be paid online only via debit card, credit card or netbanking and will not be refunded or adjusted once paid.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Application fee for General, OBC or EWS: Rs. 4250*</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Application fee for SC/ST/PwD: Rs. 3250*</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*excluding payment gateway charges, if any.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Official Helpline Portals</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>For any queries related to NEET PG 2023, NBEMS has started a NBEMS Candidate Care helpline number 022-61087595. The phone support will be available from 7th January, 2023 to 15th April,2023 (Monday to Friday, 9.30 am to 6:00pm) except Gazetted holidays. The helpline will be open from 07:00 am to 07:00 pm on 5th March,&nbsp; which is the examination day for NEET PG 2023.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Online helpline portals can be accessed on the official website through candidate&rsquo;s login after registration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'neet-pg-exam-2023-application-details', '', '', 1, '2023-02-09', 'NEET PG Exam 2023 (Application Details)', 'The National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses in Medicine (NEET PG) is conducted by the National Board of Examinations in Medical Sciences (NBEMS) for admission to various MD/MS or Diploma courses across India. This is a single entrance examination that determines the eligibility and ranking for PG- MD/MS admissions to various medical colleges of India.', NULL, '2023-02-09 12:48:58', '2023-02-09 16:13:04'),
(19, 'NEET PG 2023 (Eligibility, Exam Pattern and Syllabus)', '<p>The exam date for NEET PG for <strong>MD/MS admission 2023</strong> to various medical colleges of India has been declared as 5th March, 2023 and the registration process for the same has already begun. The application form is available on the official website of NBEMS <a href=\"https://cdn3.digialm.com/EForms/configuredHtml/1815/80166/Registration.html\">NEET PG 2023 (digialm.com)</a> and the last date for submitting the application form online is 27th January, 2023 (till 11:55 PM)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of Contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:\" name=\"Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:\"><strong>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Exam Pattern\" name=\"Exam Pattern\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1mn8iAlwsQuhjuVwyHg4HQY6USniZzd0r_hwGRVPohUI/edit#heading=h.4xeykvvppha4\"><strong>Exam Pattern </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Syllabus for NEET PG 2023\" name=\"Syllabus for NEET PG 2023\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1mn8iAlwsQuhjuVwyHg4HQY6USniZzd0r_hwGRVPohUI/edit#heading=h.bdam7wmpl6ik\"><strong>Syllabus for NEET PG 2023 </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Important Dates for Application:\" name=\"Important Dates for Application:\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1mn8iAlwsQuhjuVwyHg4HQY6USniZzd0r_hwGRVPohUI/edit#heading=h.62onyv52rnrq\"><strong>Important Dates for Application: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates who have completed MBBS and have the MBBS degree or provisional MBBS pass certificate recognized by the NMC Act, 2019 and the repealed Indian Medical Council Act 1956.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates must possess a permanent or provisional registration certificate of MBBS qualification issued by the National Medical Commission (formerly known as Medical Council of India) or State Medical Council.</li>\r\n	<li>The applicant must have completed or likely to complete one year of Compulsory Rotating Resident Internship on or before 30th June, 2023. (The earlier cut-off date for completion of internship was 31st March, 2023 which has been extended to 30th June, 2023 now).</li>\r\n	<li>All Indian nationals can appear for NEET PG exam 2023</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign medical graduates (Indian citizens or OCIs) need to pass the Foreign Medical Graduate Examination (FMGE) to be eligible for the NEET PG exam and should also be registered by the NMC.</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign nationals should have completed MBBS or equivalent qualification as recognised by NMC and obtain a temporary registration issued by the NMC for the duration of the PG course.</li>\r\n	<li>There is no maximum age limit for the NEET PG exam.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Exam Pattern</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>It is an online<strong> entrance exam</strong> consisting of 200 MCQs.</li>\r\n	<li>The medium of the examination will be only English.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Marking Scheme: There will be 4 marks for every correct answer and 1 mark will be deducted for every incorrect answer. No negative mark for unattempted questions. The total marks for the exam is 800.</li>\r\n	<li>Duration of the exam will be 3 hours and 30 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>The exam will be in 3 parts: Part 1 (Pre-Clinical), Part 2 (Para Clinical) and Part 3 (Clinical).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Syllabus for NEET PG 2023</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The syllabus comprises the subjects as per Graduate Medical Education regulations issued by MCI.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>The subjects covered under the three sections of the exam i.e. Pre-Clinical, Para Clinical and Clinical are as follows:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Pre-Clinical: Anatomy, Physiology and Biochemistry</li>\r\n		<li>Para-Clinical: Pathology, Pharmacology, Microbiology, Forensic Medicine, Social and Preventive Medicine</li>\r\n		<li>Clinical: Psychiatry, ENT, Ophthalmology, Medicine, Pediatrics, Obstetrics and Gynaecology, Radiodiagnosis and Radiotherapy, Surgery, Orthopaedics, Anaesthesia, Dermatology&nbsp; and Venereology.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>As the syllabus for the entrance exam is very vast, it is advisable to plan your time well and practise enough sample question papers to understand the difficulty level and manage your time for the same.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Important Dates</strong> for Application:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Start-date of Online Registration for NEET PG exam: 7th January, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Last date for submission of Application: 27th January, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Application Edit Window (Any information/documents can be edited&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>except Name, Nationality, Email, Mobile&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>number and Test City) : 30th January, 2023 to 3rd February, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Final Edit Window 14th February, 2023 to 17th February, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(To rectify Uploaded Images such as Photograph,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Signatures or Thumb Impressions)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Admit Card Issue 27th February, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date of Examination 5th March, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Result Declaration 31st March, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cut-off for Internship eligibility for NEET PG 2023 30th June, 2023* (Revised)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*The earlier cut-off for completion of internship for being eligible for NEET PG 2023 was 31st March, 2023 which has been revised to 30th June, 2023 by The Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (MoHFW), Govt of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>', 'neet-pg-2023-eligibility-exam-pattern-and-syllabus', '', '', 1, '2023-02-09', 'NEET PG 2023 (Eligibility, Exam Pattern and Syllabus)', 'r MD/MS admission 2023 to various medical colleges of India has been declared as 5th March, 2023 and the registration process for the same has already begun.', NULL, '2023-02-09 13:30:57', '2023-02-09 16:09:35'),
(20, 'List of PG medical courses after MBBS', '<p>After completing your MBBS degree, one needs to clear the NEET PG entrance examination or PG entrance exams of other centralised colleges such as AIIMS PG, JIPMER PG etc. to apply for admission to PG courses at the medical institutes. Since there are numerous postgraduate medical courses one can choose to pursue after MBBS and each course may have specific eligibility criterias, it is important to have a thorough knowledge about your chosen PG course to be able to prepare for the same well in time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of Contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"1. MD (Doctor of Medicine)\" name=\"1. MD (Doctor of Medicine)\"><strong>1. MD (Doctor of Medicine) </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"2. MS (Master of Surgery)\" name=\"2. MS (Master of Surgery)\"><strong>2. MS (Master of Surgery) </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"3. Diploma courses:\" name=\"3. Diploma courses:\"><strong>3. Diploma courses: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"4. DNB Courses:\" name=\"4. DNB Courses:\"><strong>4. DNB Courses: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"5. Other courses after MBBS:\" name=\"5. Other courses after MBBS:\"><strong>5. Other courses after MBBS:</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What to do after MBBS?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h1>MD (Doctor of Medicine)</h1>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>If you wish to become a specialised physician or practitioner, you can pursue MD in your preferred field of medicine. The various MD (Doctor of Medicine) courses available after MBBS include but not limited to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>MD (Anesthesia)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Anatomy)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Aerospace Medicine)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (ENT)&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Respiratory Medicine)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Infectious Medicine)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Cardiology)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Biochemistry)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (General Surgery)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Dermatology)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Microbiology)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Forensic Medicine)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Geriatrics)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (General Medicine)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Orthopaedics)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Ophthalmology)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Pharmacology)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Obstetrics &amp; Gynecology)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Radio-Diagnosis)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Paediatrics)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Psychiatry)</li>\r\n	<li>MD (Pathology)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Eligibility criteria for MD courses:</em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The applicant must complete the MBBS degree including 1 year of internship</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum 50% aggregate in MBBS examinations.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Qualify the NEET PG entrance examination or the PG entrance examination of the specific medical institution.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates must possess a permanent or provisional registration certificate issued by Medical Council of India or any State Medical Council.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Duration of MD: 3 years</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h1>MS (Master of Surgery)</h1>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;To become a surgeon in a particular area of specialisation, one must pursue MS (Master of Surgery) in that specific field. One can pursue MS in the following fields:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>MS (Orthopaedics)</li>\r\n	<li>MS (ENT)</li>\r\n	<li>MS (Cardiothoracic Surgery)</li>\r\n	<li>MS (Neurosurgery)</li>\r\n	<li>MS (Biotechnology)</li>\r\n	<li>MS (Ophthalmology)</li>\r\n	<li>MS (General Surgery)</li>\r\n	<li>MS (Obstetrics and Gynecology)</li>\r\n	<li>MS (Cosmetic Surgery)</li>\r\n	<li>MS (Urology)</li>\r\n	<li>MS (Pediatric Surgery)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility criteria for MS courses: same as that of MD</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Duration of MS: 3 years</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h1>Diploma courses:&nbsp;</h1>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Apart from MD or MS, one can pursue Diploma certification courses in various fields of medicine which is for a shorter period. Although there are numerous streams in the field of medicine for one to pursue diploma certification, the following are the most sought after courses:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Clinical Pathology</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Allergy &amp; Clinical Immunology</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Radiotherapy</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Anesthesia</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Medical Radio Electrology</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Health Education</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Sports Medicine</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in ENT</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Pediatrics</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in DVL</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Microbiology</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Occupational Health</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Industrial Health</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Nutrition</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Pathology</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Obstetrics &amp; Gynecology</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Physical Medicine &amp; Rehabilitation</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Nuclear medicine</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Psychiatry</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Pulmonary medicine</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Sports Medicine</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Hospital Administration</li>\r\n	<li>Diploma in Immunohematology</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility for Diploma courses: same as that of MD</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Duration of Diploma: 2 years</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h1>DNB Courses:</h1>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Diplomate of National Board is another diploma but is equivalent to a MD course. As the name suggests, Diplomate of National Board is a diploma course program offered by the central government in various specialisations of medicine and is tougher to clear than other PG courses in medicine.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility for DNB:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The applicant should have completed an MBBS degree of 5 years with 1 year mandatory rotatory internship from a&nbsp; recognised institution by MCI.</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum 50% aggregate marks throughout MBBS.</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate must possess a permanent registration certificate as well as an internship completion certificate issued by MCI for applying for DNB admission.</li>\r\n	<li>Qualify DNB-CET or CET-NBE entrance examination for admission to DNB courses.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Duration of DNB course: 3 years</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h1>Other courses after MBBS:&nbsp;</h1>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>There are several other courses one can pursue after MBBS that are not directly related to medicine but involve the knowledge of medical science. These courses do not require NEET PG qualification.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>MBA: MBA in Hospital Administration or Healthcare Management is a great career choice for graduates interested in the management field of medicine.</li>\r\n	<li>Biomaterials and Implants: It involves creating and implementing artificial organs.</li>\r\n	<li>Regenerative Medicine: It involves replacing or regenerating damaged tissues or organs to restore its functions.</li>\r\n	<li>Stem cells: Just like regenerative medicine, stem cells aim to repair damaged cells or replace them with healthy ones.</li>\r\n	<li>Biosensors</li>\r\n	<li>Telemedicine</li>\r\n	<li>Medical Statistics</li>\r\n	<li>Molecular Imaging and Image Analysis: A type of imaging technique to visualise molecules in living patients is a growing career choice nowadays.</li>\r\n	<li>Immuno-technology: It involves advanced research study of the immune system.</li>\r\n	<li>Recombinant DNA Technology: It involves DNA cloning and restructuring.</li>\r\n	<li>Biomedical Instrumentation</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'list-of-pg-medical-courses-after-mbbs', '', '', 1, '2023-02-09', 'List of PG medical courses after MBBS', 'After completing your MBBS degree, one needs to clear the NEET PG entrance examination or PG entrance exams of other centralised colleges such as AIIMS PG, JIPMER PG etc. to apply for admission to PG courses at the medical institutes. Since there are numerous postgraduate medical courses one can choose to pursue after MBBS and each course may have specific eligibility criterias, it is important to have a thorough knowledge about your chosen PG course to be able to prepare for the same well in time.', NULL, '2023-02-09 15:27:50', '2023-02-09 15:27:50'),
(22, 'MD MS Admissions in Tamil Nadu for State Quota Seats', '<p>For MD MS admissions in any college across Tamil Nadu, one needs to qualify the NEET PG examination which is the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses in Medicine conducted by the National Board of Examinations in Medical Sciences (NBEMS).For MD MS admissions in any college across Tamil Nadu, one needs to qualify the NEET PG examination which is the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses in Medicine conducted by the National Board of Examinations in Medical Sciences (NBEMS).For MD MS admissions in any college across Tamil Nadu, one needs to qualify the NEET PG examination which is the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses in Medicine conducted by the National Board of Examinations in Medical Sciences (NBEMS).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application window for the NEET PG 2023 exam which is to be held on 5th March, 2023 is closed now but the Final Edit Window to rectify any uploaded image such as Photograph, Signature or Thumb impression will be open from 14th to 17th February, 2023.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other important dates are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Admit Card Issue&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 27th February, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date of Examination&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 5th March, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Result Declaration&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 31st March, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of Contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:\" name=\"Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.5al1t8wgg1o9\"><strong>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:\" name=\"Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.klknfo3lh3n8\"><strong>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu\" name=\"NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.srbizwij1jc9\"><strong>NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Documents required for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:\" name=\"Documents required for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.4fk7jg6yp2tr\"><strong>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Counselling for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu 2023:\" name=\"Counselling for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu 2023:\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.ycqxce8ft8uc\"><strong>Counselling for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu 2023: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu:\" name=\"Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu:\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.qzwt9oimr6g0\"><strong>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Tamil Nadu\" name=\"List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Tamil Nadu\"></a><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.a22qg5786pt4\"><strong>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Tamil Nadu </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates who have completed MBBS and have the MBBS degree or provisional MBBS pass certificate recognized by the NMC</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates must possess a permanent or provisional registration certificate of MBBS qualification issued by the National Medical</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Commission (formerly known as Medical Council of India) or State Medical Council.</li>\r\n	<li>The applicant must have completed or likely to complete one year of Compulsory Rotating Resident Internship on or before 30th June, 2023. (The earlier cut-off date for completion of internship was 31st March, 2023 which has been extended to 30th June, 2023 now).</li>\r\n	<li>All Indian nationals can appear for NEET PG exam 2023</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign medical graduates (Indian citizens or OCIs) need to pass the Foreign Medical Graduate Examination (FMGE) to be eligible for the NEET PG exam and should also be registered by the NMC.</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign nationals should have completed MBBS or equivalent qualification as recognised by NMC and obtain a temporary registration issued by the NMC for the duration of the PG course.</li>\r\n	<li>There is no maximum age limit for the NEET PG exam.</li>\r\n	<li>Additional eligibility criteria for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu:</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates must possess an MBBS degree from a college recognised by the Dr. MGR Medical University or submit an eligibility certificate.</li>\r\n	<li>Domicile Certificate: Candidates must be domiciles of Tamil Nadu state to apply for PG admissions in the state and submit relevant supporting documents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The counselling for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu is conducted by the Directorate of Medical Education, Tamil Nadu (DME). The application form for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu has not been released yet and will be available online at the official website <a href=\"https://tnmedicalselection.net/\">Selection Committee- DME (tnmedicalselection.net)</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>General: 50th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>General with physical disabilities: 45th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC/ST/OBC: 40th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC/ST/OBC with physical disabilities: 40th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Admit Card as well as Score card</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS degree and internship completion certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Medical registration (provisional or permanent) issued by MCI</li>\r\n	<li>Domicile Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Caste certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Disability certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Payment receipt for the application form</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>NRI candidates are required to submit a certificate stating the status of the candidate&rsquo;s financial supporter (local guardian) issued by the Indian Embassy of the respective country. A certificate stating the relationship of the local guardian with the applicant along with the passport and bank account details of the guardian must also be submitted.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Counselling for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>All candidates listed in the merit list declared by DME as per the NEET PG 2023 score will be eligible for PG counselling. The candidate must pay a non-refundable fee of Rs.1000 and select their preferred college as well as specialisation while filling the TN admissions application form.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some seats are reserved for armed forces as well as under various state and management quota for PG admission in the government as well as private medical colleges of Tamil Nadu. 50% seats are reserved under state quota in various medical colleges of Tamil Nadu&nbsp; and the qualifying criteria for the same differs from one college to another. Kindly check the official website of the respective college for seat reservation guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Tamil Nadu</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>CMC Vellore</li>\r\n	<li>Stanley Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Coimbatore Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Madras Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Kanyakumari Government Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>PSG Institute of Medical Sciences &amp; Research</li>\r\n	<li>K A P Viswanathan Government Medical College, Trichy</li>\r\n	<li>Kilpauk Medical College, Chennai</li>\r\n	<li>Madurai Medical College, Madurai</li>\r\n	<li>Chengalpattu Medical College, Chengalpattu</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'md-ms-admissions-in-tamil-nadu-for-state-quota-seats', '', '', 1, '2023-02-14', 'MD MS Admissions in Tamil Nadu for State Quota Seats', 'For MD MS admissions in any college across Tamil Nadu, one needs to qualify the NEET PG examination which is the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses in Medicine conducted by the National Board of Examinations in Medical Sciences (NBEMS).', NULL, '2023-02-14 13:47:58', '2023-02-14 13:47:58'),
