(31, 'How to Ace NEET PG 2023: Study Tips for Medical Students', '<p>NEET PG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses), to be held on 5th March, 2023, is an important exam for medical students in India who want to pursue their postgraduate studies in medicine. It is a highly competitive exam and therefore requires a well-planned study strategy to ace it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some study tips that can help you prepare for NEET PG 2023:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Understand the Exam Pattern: Before starting your preparation, it is important to understand the exam pattern, marking scheme and syllabus. The exam consists of 300 multiple-choice questions and the duration of the exam is 3 hours and 30 minutes. Each correct answer carries 4 marks and there is a negative marking of 1 mark for each incorrect answer. The syllabus covers all the subjects studied in MBBS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Create a Study Plan: Create a study plan that is realistic, achievable and suits your learning style. Allocate sufficient time for each subject and give extra time to your weak areas. You can divide your study time into three phases- initial preparation, revision and practice tests. Make sure you follow your study plan religiously and avoid procrastination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Study from Standard Textbooks: NEET PG is a test of your conceptual knowledge, and therefore, it is important to study from standard textbooks. Some of the recommended textbooks are Harrison&#39;s Principles of Internal Medicine, Davidson&#39;s Principles and Practice of Medicine, Robbins and Cotran Pathologic Basis of Disease and Bailey and Love&#39;s Short Practice of Surgery. Make sure you understand the concepts thoroughly and do not just memorise them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use Online Resources: There are several online resources that can be very helpful for NEET PG preparation. You can use websites like Medical Dialogues, Medical News Today and Medscape for the latest updates in the field of medicine. You can also join online forums and discussion groups where you can interact with other medical students and experts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Solve Previous Year Question Papers: Solving previous year question papers is a great way to understand the exam pattern, time management and your strengths and weaknesses. It will also help you identify the frequently asked topics and the level of difficulty of the exam. You can download previous year question papers from the official website of NBE (National Board of Examinations).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take Mock Tests: Mock tests are an important part of NEET PG preparation as they simulate the real exam environment. You can take mock tests online or offline and analyse your performance after each test. Make sure you take mock tests regularly and keep track of your progress.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stay Healthy and Motivated: It is important to stay healthy and motivated during your NEET PG preparation. Make sure you take breaks, eat healthy food, exercise regularly and get sufficient sleep. You can also join study groups where you can interact with other medical students and share your experiences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;NEET PG is a challenging exam but with a well-planned study strategy, you can ace it. Understand the exam pattern, create a study plan, study from standard textbooks, use online resources, solve previous year question papers, take mock tests and stay healthy and motivated. Remember, consistency and dedication are the keys to success. Good luck!</p>', 'neet-pg-2023-study-tips-for-medical-students', '', '', 1, '2023-03-04', 'How to Ace NEET PG 2023: Study Tips for Medical Students', 'NEET PG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses), to be held on 5th March, 2023, is an important exam for medical students in India who want to pursue their postgraduate studies in medicine. It is a highly competitive exam and therefore requires a well-planned study strategy to ace it.', NULL, '2023-03-04 11:18:24', '2023-03-04 11:18:24'),
(32, 'NEET PG 2023: Common Mistakes to Avoid During the Exam', '<p>NEET PG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test Post Graduate) is a highly competitive exam that medical students in India take to pursue their postgraduate studies in medicine. To perform well in the exam, it is important to avoid common mistakes that students tend to make during the exam. Here are some common mistakes to avoid during the NEET PG 2023 exam to be held on 5th March, 2023:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Not Reading the Instructions Properly</em>: One of the common mistakes that students make during the NEET PG exam is not reading the instructions properly. It is important to read the instructions carefully before starting the exam as it can help you to understand the exam pattern, marking scheme and other important details.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Not Managing Time Efficiently</em>: Time management is crucial during the NEET PG exam as you have to answer 300 multiple-choice questions in 3 hours and 30 minutes. It is important to allocate sufficient time for each section and not spend too much time on difficult questions. You can also mark the difficult questions and come back to them later, if you have time.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Not Maintaining Accuracy</em>: NEET PG has a negative marking system, and therefore, it is important to maintain accuracy while answering the questions. Avoid guesswork and answering questions based on assumptions. Make sure you read the questions and options carefully before answering them.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Not Practising Enough</em>: Practising enough is important to perform well in the NEET PG exam. Solve as many previous year question papers and mock tests as possible to understand the exam pattern and to improve your speed and accuracy. Make sure you analyze your performance after each test and identify your weak areas.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Not Focusing on the High-Yield Topics</em>: NEET PG covers all the subjects studied in MBBS, and therefore, it is important to focus on the high-yield topics. These are the topics that are frequently asked in the exam and carry more weightage. Make sure you cover these topics thoroughly and revise them regularly.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Not Taking Breaks</em>: Taking breaks during the NEET PG exam is important to refresh your mind and avoid mental exhaustion. Make sure you take short breaks between sections and longer breaks after every hour. You can also stretch or take a walk to refresh your mind and body.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Not Staying Calm and Composed</em>: NEET PG is a stressful exam, and therefore, it is important to stay calm and composed during the exam. Avoid getting anxious or panicking if you are stuck on a difficult question. Take a deep breath, read the question again and try to solve it calmly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG is a challenging exam but avoiding these common mistakes can help you to perform better. Read the instructions properly, manage time efficiently, maintain accuracy, practice enough, focus on high-yield topics, take breaks and stay calm and composed and you will be able to sail through the exam easily.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'neet-pg-2023-common-mistakes', '', '', 1, '2023-03-04', 'NEET PG 2023: Common Mistakes', 'NEET PG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test Post Graduate) is a highly competitive exam that medical students in India take to pursue their postgraduate studies in medicine. To perform well in the exam, it is important to avoid common mistakes that students tend to make during the exam. Here are some common mistakes to avoid during the NEET PG 2023 exam to be held on 5th March, 2023:', NULL, '2023-03-04 11:21:16', '2023-03-04 11:21:16'),
(33, 'NEET PG 2023: Strategies for Managing Exam Stress and Anxiety', '<p>NEET PG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test Postgraduate) is a highly competitive entrance exam for postgraduate medical courses in India. The exam is to be&nbsp; conducted by the National Board of Examinations (NBE) on 5th March, 2023. Aspirants who are preparing for NEET PG 2023 are likely to experience stress and anxiety given the intense competition and the importance of the exam in their career.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Managing exam stress and anxiety is essential for achieving success in NEET PG 2023. In this article, we will discuss some effective strategies for managing exam stress and anxiety.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Start early: Starting early with your preparation is one of the best ways to manage exam stress. When you start early, you have more time to prepare and revise which reduces the last-minute stress.</li>\r\n	<li>Create a study plan: A study plan helps you to stay organised and focused. Divide your syllabus into manageable chunks and allocate a specific time for each topic. Having a study plan helps you to track your progress and make necessary adjustments.</li>\r\n	<li>Take regular breaks: Taking regular breaks is essential to manage stress and improve concentration. Studying continuously for long hours can cause burnout and reduce productivity. Take a short break of 10-15 minutes every 1-2 hours to refresh your mind.</li>\r\n	<li>Exercise regularly: Exercise is an excellent stress buster. Regular exercise not only reduces stress and anxiety but also improves cognitive function. Exercise also improves blood circulation which enhances brain function.</li>\r\n	<li>Practice meditation and deep breathing: Meditation and deep breathing techniques help to calm the mind and reduce stress. Spend a few minutes every day practising deep breathing and meditation to improve focus and concentration.</li>\r\n	<li>Get enough sleep: Sleep is crucial for overall health and well-being. Lack of sleep can lead to fatigue, irritability and reduced productivity. Aim to get 7-8 hours of quality sleep every night to stay fresh and alert.</li>\r\n	<li>Eat a balanced diet: A balanced diet is essential for brain function and overall health. Eat a diet rich in fruits, vegetables, whole grains and lean protein. Avoid processed and junk food which can affect your mood and energy levels.</li>\r\n	<li>Stay positive: Positive thinking is vital for managing exam stress. Avoid negative self-talk and focus on your strengths. Visualise success and stay motivated.</li>\r\n	<li>Seek support: Talk to family, friends or a mentor for emotional support. Share your concerns and anxieties with them. They can provide valuable insights and help you to stay motivated.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Thus, managing exam stress and anxiety is essential for achieving success in NEET PG 2023. Follow these strategies to stay calm, focused and motivated throughout your preparation. Remember, a positive mindset, a well-planned strategy and consistent effort are the keys to success.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'neet-pg-2023-strategies-for-managing-exam-stress-and-anxiety', '', '', 1, '2023-03-04', 'NEET PG 2023: Strategies for Managing Exam Stress and Anxiety', 'NEET PG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test Postgraduate) is a highly competitive entrance exam for postgraduate medical courses in India. The exam is to be  conducted by the National Board of Examinations (NBE) on 5th March, 2023. Aspirants who are preparing for NEET PG 2023 are likely to experience stress and anxiety given the intense competition and the importance of the exam in their career.', NULL, '2023-03-04 11:30:06', '2023-03-04 11:30:06'),
(34, 'MD MS Admissions in Tamil Nadu for State Quota Seats', '<p>&nbsp;Medical Sciences (NBEMS).For MD MS admissions in any college across Tamil Nadu, one needs to qualify the NEET PG examination which is the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses in Medicine conducted by the National Board of Examinations in</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application window for the NEET PG 2023 exam which is to be held on 5th March, 2023 is closed now but the Final Edit Window to rectify any uploaded image such as Photograph, Signature or Thumb impression will be open from 14th to 17th February, 2023.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other important dates are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Admit Card Issue 27th February, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date of Examination 5th March, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Result Declaration 31st March, 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of Contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.5al1t8wgg1o9\"><strong>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.klknfo3lh3n8\"><strong>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.srbizwij1jc9\"><strong>NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.4fk7jg6yp2tr\"><strong>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.ycqxce8ft8uc\"><strong>Counselling for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.qzwt9oimr6g0\"><strong>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1In7ktKp9UvJpx-4YJUgwpV8It4BEyFJ6HJkpR0OOlhA/edit#heading=h.a22qg5786pt4\"><strong>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Tamil Nadu</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates who have completed MBBS and have the MBBS degree or provisional MBBS pass certificate recognized by the NMC</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates must possess a permanent or provisional registration certificate of MBBS qualification issued by the National Medical Commission (formerly known as Medical Council of India) or State Medical Council.</li>\r\n	<li>The applicant must have completed or likely to complete one year of Compulsory Rotating Resident Internship on or before 30th June, 2023. (The earlier cut-off date for completion of internship was 31st March, 2023 which has been extended to 30th June, 2023 now).</li>\r\n	<li>All Indian nationals can appear for NEET PG exam 2023</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign medical graduates (Indian citizens or OCIs) need to pass the Foreign Medical Graduate Examination (FMGE) to be eligible for the NEET PG exam and should also be registered by the NMC.</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign nationals should have completed MBBS or equivalent qualification as recognised by NMC and obtain a temporary registration issued by the NMC for the duration of the PG course.</li>\r\n	<li>There is no maximum age limit for the NEET PG exam.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Additional eligibility criteria for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates must possess an MBBS degree from a college recognised by the Dr. MGR Medical University or submit an eligibility certificate.</li>\r\n	<li>Domicile Certificate: Candidates must be domiciles of Tamil Nadu state to apply for PG admissions in the state and submit relevant supporting documents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:<br />\r\nThe counselling for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu is conducted by the Directorate of Medical Education, Tamil Nadu (DME). The application form for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu has not been released yet and will be available online at the official website <a href=\"https://tnmedicalselection.net/\">Selection Committee- DME (tnmedicalselection.net)</a>.</h1>\r\n\r\n<h1>NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>General: 50th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>General with physical disabilities: 45th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC/ST/OBC: 40th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC/ST/OBC with physical disabilities: 40th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Tamil Nadu:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Admit Card as well as Score card</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS degree and internship completion certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Medical registration (provisional or permanent) issued by MCI</li>\r\n	<li>Domicile Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Caste certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Disability certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Payment receipt for the application form</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>NRI candidates are required to submit a certificate stating the status of the candidate&rsquo;s financial supporter (local guardian) issued by the Indian Embassy of the respective country. A certificate stating the relationship of the local guardian with the applicant along with the passport and bank account details of the guardian must also be submitted.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Counselling for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>All candidates listed in the merit list declared by DME as per the NEET PG 2023 score will be eligible for PG counselling. The candidate must pay a non-refundable fee of Rs.1000 and select their preferred college as well as specialisation while filling the TN admissions application form.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Tamil Nadu:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Some seats are reserved for armed forces as well as under various state and management quota for PG admission in the government as well as private medical colleges of Tamil Nadu. 50% seats are reserved under state quota in various medical colleges of Tamil Nadu&nbsp; and the qualifying criteria for the same differs from one college to another. Kindly check the official website of the respective college for seat reservation guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Tamil Nadu</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>CMC Vellore</li>\r\n	<li>Stanley Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Coimbatore Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Madras Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Kanyakumari Government Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>PSG Institute of Medical Sciences &amp; Research</li>\r\n	<li>K A P Viswanathan Government Medical College, Trichy</li>\r\n	<li>Kilpauk Medical College, Chennai</li>\r\n	<li>Madurai Medical College, Madurai</li>\r\n	<li>Chengalpattu Medical College, Chengalpattu</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'md-ms-admissions-in-tamil-nadu-for-state-quota-seats', '167791675365.jpg', '167791675320.jpg', 1, '2023-03-04', 'MD MS Admissions in Tamil Nadu for State Quota Seats', 'MD MS admissions in any college across Tamil Nadu, one needs to qualify the NEET PG examination which is the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate courses in Medicine conducted by the National Board of Examinations in', NULL, '2023-03-04 13:59:13', '2023-03-04 13:59:13'),
(35, 'MD MS Admission in Karnataka for State Quota seats (by KEA)', '<p>Qualifying the National Eligibility Cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate medical courses (NEET PG 2023) is mandatory for MD MS admissions in the various government and private medical institutions of Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The NEET PG 2023 exam is to be held on 5th March, 2023. The application process for the same is closed now but the Final Edit Window to rectify any uploaded image such as Photograph, Signature or Thumb impression will be open from 14th to 17th February, 2023.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other important dates are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Admit Card Issue</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>27th February, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Date of Examination</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>5th March, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Result Declaration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>31st March, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of Contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gYohw0ak76CaxaWnx5QAxgdIgViQcQ0XhDMaIdGQ36o/edit#heading=h.5al1t8wgg1o9\"><strong>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gYohw0ak76CaxaWnx5QAxgdIgViQcQ0XhDMaIdGQ36o/edit#heading=h.ep4rjdiii0ud\"><strong>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Karnataka:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gYohw0ak76CaxaWnx5QAxgdIgViQcQ0XhDMaIdGQ36o/edit#heading=h.jzrd28i57cso\"><strong>NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for PG admissions in Karnataka</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gYohw0ak76CaxaWnx5QAxgdIgViQcQ0XhDMaIdGQ36o/edit#heading=h.6e0g0w1py4gc\"><strong>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Karnataka:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gYohw0ak76CaxaWnx5QAxgdIgViQcQ0XhDMaIdGQ36o/edit#heading=h.ao34q2jrkdk1\"><strong>Counselling for PG admissions in Karnataka 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gYohw0ak76CaxaWnx5QAxgdIgViQcQ0XhDMaIdGQ36o/edit#heading=h.acjpwlstpfey\"><strong>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Karnataka</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gYohw0ak76CaxaWnx5QAxgdIgViQcQ0XhDMaIdGQ36o/edit#heading=h.4nrkwiiwu0tw\"><strong>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Karnataka:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates who have completed MBBS and have the MBBS degree or provisional MBBS pass certificate recognized by the NMC.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates must possess a permanent or provisional registration certificate of MBBS qualification issued by the National Medical Commission (formerly known as Medical Council of India) or State Medical Council.</li>\r\n	<li>The applicant must have completed or likely to complete one year of Compulsory Rotating Resident Internship on or before 30th June, 2023. (The earlier cut-off date for completion of internship was 31st March, 2023 which has been extended to 30th June, 2023 now).</li>\r\n	<li>All Indian nationals can appear for NEET PG exam 2023</li>\r\n	<li>There is no maximum age limit for the NEET PG exam.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additional eligibility criteria for PG admissions in Karnataka:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Domicile: An applicant must be a domicile of Karnataka to be eligible for MD MS admissions in the colleges of Karnataka and submit relevant documents supporting the same.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Karnataka:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The counselling for MD MS admissions in Karnataka is conducted by Karnataka Examination Authority (KEA) and the process for the same has not yet started. The application form for admission to post graduate medical courses in the various colleges of Karnataka will be released soon and available on the official website <a href=\"https://cetonline.karnataka.gov.in/kea/indexnew\">KEA | Home (karnataka.gov.in)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After registration and verification of all the uploaded documents, a verification slip will be generated by KEA. Candidates must check all the details mentioned on the verification slip and report any error to KEA immediately. Also, the verification slip will have the security key of the candidate essential for further admission process.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for PG admissions in Karnataka</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>General: 50th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>General with physical disabilities: 45th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC/ST/OBC: 40th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC/ST/OBC with physical disabilities: 40th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Karnataka:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Copy of the online submitted application form</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Admit Card</li>\r\n	<li>Class 10th and Class 12th Marksheets</li>\r\n	<li>Photo ID Proof</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS Mark sheet for all the years</li>\r\n	<li>Internship Completion Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Registration certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Domicile certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Caste certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Passport sized photograph and full signature to be uploaded (same as the one used for NEET PG 2023)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Counselling for PG admissions in Karnataka 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>There will be 2 rounds of counselling for Karnataka PG medical admissions conducted by KEA followed by a mop up round. The merit list of candidates based on their NEET PG scores, reservations, eligibility criteria and choice of college or course will be released online on the official website of KEA. The counselling will be done online to fill up 50% of state quota seats.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are 4 types of seats available for PG medical admissions in the colleges of Karnataka i.e. Government, Private, NRI and Other or Management Quota. Kindly check the seat matrix for the year published by KEA before selecting your preferred medical college.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Karnataka</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>In Karnataka, admissions to postgraduate (PG) medical courses are governed by the reservation policy set by the government. The policy provides for reservation of seats for various categories of students, such as Scheduled Castes (SC), Scheduled Tribes (ST), Other Backward Classes (OBC), and economically weaker sections (EWS).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The reservation percentage for each category is as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC: 15%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ST: 7.5%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>OBC: 27%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>EWS: 10%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please note that the reservation policy is subject to change and the exact reservation percentages may vary depending on the year and the specific institution. It&#39;s always best to check with the concerned authorities for the latest information on the reservation policy for PG admissions in Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Karnataka:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bangalore Medical College and Research Institute, Bangalore</li>\r\n	<li>Kempegowda Institute of Medical Sciences, Bangalore</li>\r\n	<li>M. S. Ramaiah Medical College, Bangalore</li>\r\n	<li>St. John&#39;s Medical College, Bangalore</li>\r\n	<li>Kasturba Medical College, Mangalore</li>\r\n	<li>Basaveswara Medical College and Hospital, Chitradurga</li>\r\n	<li>K.S. Hegde Medical Academy, Mangalore</li>\r\n	<li>Shridevi Institute of Medical Sciences &amp; Research Hospital, Tumkur</li>\r\n	<li>Gulbarga Institute of Medical Sciences, Gulbarga</li>\r\n	<li>Dr BR Ambedkar Medical College, Bangalore</li>\r\n	<li>Mahadevappa Rampure Medical College, Kalaburagi, Gulbarga</li>\r\n	<li>A.J. Institute of Medical Sciences, Mangalore</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Please note that this list is not exhaustive and there may be other medical colleges in Karnataka that offer PG courses in medicine. It&#39;s always best to check with the concerned authorities for the latest information on the availability of PG medical courses in Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'md-ms-admission-in-karnataka-for-state-quota-seats-by-kea', '', '', 1, '2023-03-04', 'MD MS Admission in Karnataka for State Quota seats (by KEA)', 'Qualifying the National Eligibility Cum Entrance Test for Post Graduate medical courses (NEET PG 2023) is mandatory for MD MS admissions in the various government and private medical institutions of Karnataka.', NULL, '2023-03-04 14:24:42', '2023-03-04 14:24:42'),
(36, 'MD MS Admissions in Maharashtra for State quota seats', '<p>The NEET PG examination i.e. the All India National Eligibility Cum Entrance Examination for admission to various postgraduate medical courses (MD/MS) across all the medical colleges of India will be held on 5th March, 2023. And thus, for MD/MS admissions in Maharashtra also, qualifying NEET PG 2023 is a must.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application process for the NEET PG 2023 is closed now. However, other important dates in regards to NEET PG 2023 are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Final Edit Window for submitted applications</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>14th to 17th February, 2023.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Admit Card Issue</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>27th February, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Date of Examination</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>5th March, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Result Declaration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>31st March, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TPLYXD8GCDvHlu97mnJMYl3ZXI4UwRvEnUm-PDEpeU0/edit#heading=h.8gig64h8hpfy\"><strong>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TPLYXD8GCDvHlu97mnJMYl3ZXI4UwRvEnUm-PDEpeU0/edit#heading=h.mggv7ptpfdxq\"><strong>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Maharashtra:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TPLYXD8GCDvHlu97mnJMYl3ZXI4UwRvEnUm-PDEpeU0/edit#heading=h.4gkr9ana8bwe\"><strong>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Maharashtra:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TPLYXD8GCDvHlu97mnJMYl3ZXI4UwRvEnUm-PDEpeU0/edit#heading=h.lkjhwlwbxxmr\"><strong>Counselling for PG admissions in Maharashtra 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TPLYXD8GCDvHlu97mnJMYl3ZXI4UwRvEnUm-PDEpeU0/edit#heading=h.a5tfjeng8f7o\"><strong>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Maharashtra:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TPLYXD8GCDvHlu97mnJMYl3ZXI4UwRvEnUm-PDEpeU0/edit#heading=h.rq3q9150hqiz\"><strong>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Maharashtra:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The eligibility criteria for appearing in the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test Post Graduate (NEET-PG) 2023 are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Educational Qualification: The candidate must have a degree of MBBS or its equivalent recognized by the Medical Council of India (MCI).&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate must have completed a rotatory internship of one-year duration on or before June 30, 2023.</li>\r\n	<li>Registration with Medical Council: The candidate must be registered with the Medical Council of India or any of the State Medical Councils.</li>\r\n	<li>Indian Citizenship: The candidate must be an Indian citizen.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Maharashtra:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The counselling for postgraduate (PG) medical admissions in Maharashtra for MD/MS courses is conducted by the Directorate of Medical Education and Research (DMER), Mumbai. DMER is the state-level authority responsible for conducting the counselling process and allotting seats to eligible candidates based on their score in the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test Post Graduate (NEET-PG) examination conducted by the National Board of Examinations (NBE).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kindly check the official website <a href=\"https://cetcell.mahacet.org/\">Welcome to State Common Entrance Test Cell Maharashtra State Official Portal (mahacet.org)</a> for more updates.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Maharashtra:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Admit Card</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Score Card</li>\r\n	<li>Photo ID proof</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of online application form&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS degree</li>\r\n	<li>Compulsory internship completion certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Registration certificate from MCI/Maharashtra Medical Council or other state councils.</li>\r\n	<li>Nationality proof&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Medical Fitness Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of receipt of online fee payment</li>\r\n	<li>Caste certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Disability certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>EWS certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Counselling for PG admissions in Maharashtra 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>As with other state counsellings, there will be 2 rounds of counselling for PG medical admissions in Maharashtra followed by a mop up round. The counselling committee of DMER, Mumbai will release the merit list of all shortlisted candidates on their official website and the successful candidates will be called for counselling. The criteria for shortlisting candidates for the merit list depends on the NEET PG 2023 scores of the candidates, seat reservation criteria, choice of medical institution as selected by the candidate, availability of seats etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Maharashtra:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The reservation policy for postgraduate (PG) medical admissions in Maharashtra is determined by the concerned state-level authority, such as the Directorate of Medical Education and Research (DMER), Mumbai. The reservation policy provides for reserved categories of candidates to be allotted a certain percentage of seats in medical colleges based on their social, economic, and educational status.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The reservation policy for PG medical admissions in Maharashtra usually includes the following categories:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scheduled Castes (SC) - 15%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scheduled Tribes (ST) - 7.5%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other Backward Classes (OBC) - 27%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Economically Weaker Section (EWS) - 10%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Persons with Disabilities (PWD) - 3%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please note that the reservation policy for PG medical admissions in Maharashtra is subject to change and it&#39;s always best to check with the concerned authorities for the latest information.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Maharashtra:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The colleges for MD/MS admissions in Maharashtra include but not limited to the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Government Medical College, Latur</li>\r\n	<li>Grant Medical College, Mumbai</li>\r\n	<li>Jawaharlal Nehru Medical College, Sawangi (Meghe), Wardha</li>\r\n	<li>Topiwala National Medical College, Mumbai</li>\r\n	<li>B. J. Govt. Medical College, Pune</li>\r\n	<li>Dr. Shankarrao Chavan Govt. Medical College, Nanded</li>\r\n	<li>Lokmanya Tilak Municipal Medical College, Sion, Mumbai</li>\r\n	<li>Seth GS Medical College, and KEM Hospital, Mumbai</li>\r\n	<li>Dr Vaishampayan Memorial Medical College, Solapur</li>\r\n	<li>Indira Gandhi Medical College &amp; Hospital, Nagpur</li>\r\n	<li>Government Medical College, Aurangabad</li>\r\n	<li>Bombay Hospital Institute of Medical Sciences, Mumbai</li>\r\n	<li>SRTR Medical College, Ambajogai</li>\r\n	<li>Institute of Navel Medicine, INHS, Aswini</li>\r\n	<li>Government Medical College, Miraj</li>\r\n</ul>', 'md-ms-admissions-in-maharashtra-for-state-quota-seats', '', '', 1, '2023-03-04', 'MD MS Admissions in Maharashtra for State quota seats', 'The NEET PG examination i.e. the All India National Eligibility Cum Entrance Examination for admission to various postgraduate medical courses (MD/MS) across all the medical colleges of India will be held on 5th March, 2023. And thus, for MD/MS admissions in Maharashtra also, qualifying NEET PG 2023 is a must.', NULL, '2023-03-04 14:33:58', '2023-03-04 14:33:58'),
(37, 'MD MS Admissions in Uttar Pradesh for State Quota Seats', '<p>Admissions to the MD/MS course in various medical colleges of Uttar Pradesh is done through the National Eligibility cum Entrance test for Postgraduate medical courses i.e. NEET PG exam. The NEET PG 2023 will be held on 5th March, 2023 and the application form for the same has already been released online.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For those who have applied for NEET PG 2023, the other important dates are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Final Edit Window for submitted applications</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>14th to 17th February, 2023.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Admit Card Issue</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>27th February, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Date of Examination</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>5th March, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Result Declaration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>31st March, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1tFoqvONPIJX7bUcI6Z6yrqmCo2LYFZxwDthHk40bh7M/edit#heading=h.c6okk3qwxnnd\"><strong>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1tFoqvONPIJX7bUcI6Z6yrqmCo2LYFZxwDthHk40bh7M/edit#heading=h.ghkxsapr38vj\"><strong>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Uttar Pradesh:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1tFoqvONPIJX7bUcI6Z6yrqmCo2LYFZxwDthHk40bh7M/edit#heading=h.q7dc3s48v13j\"><strong>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Uttar Pradesh:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1tFoqvONPIJX7bUcI6Z6yrqmCo2LYFZxwDthHk40bh7M/edit#heading=h.4n7wz7ujxl2i\"><strong>Counselling for PG admissions in Uttar Pradesh 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1tFoqvONPIJX7bUcI6Z6yrqmCo2LYFZxwDthHk40bh7M/edit#heading=h.8h7a9fcghfw7\"><strong>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Uttar Pradesh:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1tFoqvONPIJX7bUcI6Z6yrqmCo2LYFZxwDthHk40bh7M/edit#heading=h.t0puswfs463y\"><strong>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Uttar Pradesh:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Eligibility criteria for NEET PG 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates must have completed an MBBS degree from a college recognised by the National Medical Commission.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates must complete the Compulsory Rotating Resident Internship on or before 30th June, 2023.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates must have a permanent or provisional registration certificate issued by NMC or the State Medical Council.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Uttar Pradesh:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>After qualifying NEET PG 2023 and meeting other criteria, the applicant must register online on the official website <a href=\"https://upneet.gov.in/\">Counselling for UPNEET</a> for admission to various postgraduate medical colleges of Uttar Pradesh under state quota. After successfully submitting the form and payment of fee, you will receive a registration number and transaction number on the registered mobile number for future reference.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Documents required for MD MS admissions in Uttar Pradesh:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Admit card&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Score Card</li>\r\n	<li>Photo ID proof</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS degree or pass Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS Mark Sheets for all the years</li>\r\n	<li>Internship Completion Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Class 10th Certificate as Date of Birth proof</li>\r\n	<li>Class 12th Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Registration Certificate issued by Medical Council</li>\r\n	<li>Caste Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Disability Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Counselling for PG admissions in Uttar Pradesh 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The counselling for PG medical admissions in Uttar Pradesh is undertaken by the Directorate General of Medical Education and Training (DGHE), Uttar Pradesh. The merit list of candidates shortlisted for counselling as per their NEET PG 2023 score, reservation policy and other eligibility parameters will be released online on the official website <a href=\"http://www.dgme.up.gov.in/\">Directorate General Medical Education and training Uttar Pradesh | DGME | Training | Medical Education (up.gov.in)</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The shortlisted candidates must fill their choice of institute and specialisation by logging into the official website and fill in the maximum number of choices available. There will be 2 rounds of counselling- if the seat is not allotted in the first round or the candidate wants to upgrade the allotted seat, then one must fill their choices again for the second round. The new allotment will automatically cancel the previous allotment of seats.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Reservation Policy for PG admissions in Uttar Pradesh:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>In Uttar Pradesh, the reservation policy for PG medical admissions is governed by the rules and regulations set by the Medical Council of India (MCI) and the state government. The reservation policy aims to provide equal opportunities to students from different social and economic backgrounds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is the general reservation policy for PG medical admissions in Uttar Pradesh:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-Scheduled Castes (SC) and Scheduled Tribes (ST): 15% of the total seats are reserved for students belonging to the SC and ST categories.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-Other Backward Classes (OBC): 27% of the total seats are reserved for students belonging to the OBC category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-Physically Handicapped (PH): 3% of the total seats are reserved for students with physical disabilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-Women: 33.33% of the total seats in each category (General, SC, ST, OBC) are reserved for women.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is important to note that the reservation policy may change from time to time and it is advisable to check the latest policy from the official website of the Medical Council of India (MCI) or the concerned university/institute for the latest updates.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>List of Medical Colleges for PG Admission 2023 in Uttar Pradesh:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the medical colleges of Uttar Pradesh that offer admission in postgraduate courses under state quota are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>King George&#39;s Medical University (KGMU), Lucknow</li>\r\n	<li>Institute of Medical Sciences, Banaras Hindu University (IMS-BHU), Varanasi</li>\r\n	<li>Sanjay Gandhi Postgraduate Institute of Medical Sciences (SGPGIMS), Lucknow</li>\r\n	<li>Lala Lajpat Rai Memorial Medical College, Meerut</li>\r\n	<li>Era&#39;s Lucknow Medical College and Hospital, Lucknow</li>\r\n	<li>M.L.B. Medical College, Jhansi</li>\r\n	<li>GSVM Medical College, Kanpur</li>\r\n	<li>U.P. Rural Institute of Medical Sciences and Research, Etawah</li>\r\n	<li>Muzaffarnagar Medical College, Muzaffarnagar</li>\r\n	<li>Rohilkhand Medical College and Hospital, Bareilly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'md-ms-admissions-in-uttar-pradesh-for-state-quota-seats', '', '', 1, '2023-03-04', 'MD MS Admissions in Uttar Pradesh for State Quota Seats', 'MD/MS course in various medical colleges of Uttar Pradesh is done through the National Eligibility cum Entrance test for Postgraduate medical courses i.e. NEET PG exam. The NEET PG 2023 will be held on 5th March, 2023 and the application form for the same has already been released online.', NULL, '2023-03-04 17:33:29', '2023-03-04 17:33:29');
