order-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:185px\">\r\n			<p>Rs 40,00,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'nri-quota-fees-for-mbbs-in-tamil-nadu', '', '', 1, '2023-03-04', 'NRI Quota fees for MBBS in Tamil Nadu', 'For MBBS admissions in the medical colleges of India, one needs to clear the NEET UG examination which will be held on 7th May, 2023. NRIs keen to pursue MBBS from India must also qualify the NEET exam in addition to fulfilling other criterias.', NULL, '2023-03-04 17:41:54', '2023-03-04 17:41:54'),
(39, 'NRI Quota fees for Medical PG courses', '<p>To get admission in PG medical courses in India, one needs to qualify NEET PG 2023 which is to be held on 5th March, 2023. NRIs who wish to join medical colleges in India for their post graduate studies must qualify the NEET exam as well as fulfil other criterias.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/17HxFHDVeHWvRmSw6-1DStF0IJrl9CbFnXhyJbb4hRBU/edit#heading=h.iki8w6kuqzcc\"><strong>About NEET PG 2023:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/17HxFHDVeHWvRmSw6-1DStF0IJrl9CbFnXhyJbb4hRBU/edit#heading=h.ibdhir2k62c6\"><strong>Eligibility to get Admission in PG courses under NRI Quota:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/17HxFHDVeHWvRmSw6-1DStF0IJrl9CbFnXhyJbb4hRBU/edit#heading=h.piqxvmjoj7ql\"><strong>Documents Required for PG medical Admission under NRI Quota in India:</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/17HxFHDVeHWvRmSw6-1DStF0IJrl9CbFnXhyJbb4hRBU/edit#heading=h.ef8xmcawve1g\"><strong>How to apply for NRI quota seats for PG medical admissions?</strong><strong> </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>About NEET PG 2023:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The application process for the NEET PG 2023 is closed now. However, other important dates in regards to NEET PG 2023 are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Final Edit Window for submitted applications</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>14th to 17th February, 2023.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Admit Card Issue</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>27th February, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Date of Examination</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>5th March, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Result Declaration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>31st March, 2023</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NEET PG examination is meant for admission to PG courses in medicine for the following:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>50% of All India quota seats for all States or Union territories of India</li>\r\n		<li>All Private Medical Colleges, Universities or Deemed Universities of India.</li>\r\n		<li>Armed Forces Medical Institutions</li>\r\n		<li>State quota seats for all States/UTs of India</li>\r\n		<li>Post MBBS DNB/NBE Diploma Courses</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG is not meant for admission to the following institutions\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>AIIMS, New Delhi</li>\r\n		<li>Other AIIMS</li>\r\n		<li>PGIMER, Chandigarh</li>\r\n		<li>JIPMER, Puducherry</li>\r\n		<li>NIMHANS, Bengaluru</li>\r\n		<li>Sree Chitra Tirunal Institute for Medical Sciences and Technology, Trivandrum</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>No other State Government/Private Medical College or University shall conduct any separate entrance examination for PG admissions in medical courses.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Eligibility to get Admission in PG courses under NRI Quota:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A Candidate can apply for medical admission under NRI quota if:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>He/She is of Indian origin but lives or studies in a foreign country.</li>\r\n		<li>The parent(s) of the candidate are Indian Government employees living abroad on deputation.</li>\r\n		<li>OCIs or PIOs and their children are considered under NRI quota.</li>\r\n		<li>Candidates who were born in a foreign country but their parents are Indians.</li>\r\n		<li>Candidates born of Indian parents but living abroad due to employment or business opportunities.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>A Candidate must have a valid passport.</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate must have qualified the NEET PG examination</li>\r\n	<li>For candidates applying under NRI sponsorship, a direct blood relation with the financial supporter is mandatory.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Documents Required for PG medical Admission under NRI Quota in India:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re applying for PG medical admission under the NRI quota in India, you&#39;ll need to provide the following documents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Proof of NRI status: You&#39;ll need to provide proof of your NRI status, such as a passport with a valid NRI visa, or a valid OCI or PIO card.</li>\r\n	<li>Educational qualifications: You&#39;ll need to provide original copies of your educational certificates, including your medical degree and transcripts.</li>\r\n	<li>Passport-size photographs: You&#39;ll need to provide several passport-sized photographs, usually around 4 to 6.</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 score card and Admit card</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of financial support: You&#39;ll need to provide proof that you have the financial means to support your studies in India, such as bank statements or sponsorships.</li>\r\n	<li>Visa: If you&#39;re an international student, you&#39;ll need to provide a valid student visa for India.</li>\r\n	<li>Medical certificate: You may be required to provide a medical certificate that certifies that you are in good health and fit to pursue medical studies.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Note that these are the general documents required for admission under the NRI quota, and the specific requirements may vary depending on the institution you&#39;re applying to. It&#39;s best to check with the institution directly for a complete and up-to-date list of requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to apply for NRI quota seats for PG medical admissions?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible for counselling, one needs to register on the official website of MCC <a href=\"https://mcc.nic.in/#/home\">Home - Medical CounsellingCommittee (MCC)</a> and fill in the required details, choice filling of the course and the institution followed by payment of fees. The seats will be allotted according to the NEET PG score, availability of seats in the chosen category, reservation policies etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There will be 3 rounds of counselling for PG medical admissions in Central as well as Deemed Universities. In addition, there may be a mop up round at the College level to fill in any vacant seats.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NRI quota fees for PG medical admissions in India:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The fees for NRI quota seats in PG medical courses in India varies from institution to institution and can be quite high compared to the fees for regular seats. The exact fees will depend on the particular medical college and the specialisation you choose. However, on an average, NRI quota fees for PG medical courses in India can range from 50 Lakhs to 1 Crore or more per annum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s important to keep in mind that these fees are subject to change and can fluctuate based on various factors such as inflation, government regulations, and the overall demand for the course. It is always a good idea to check the official website of the medical college or contact their admission office to get the most up-to-date information on NRI quota fees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'nri-quota-fees-for-medical-pg-courses', '', '', 1, '2023-03-04', 'NRI Quota fees for Medical PG courses', 'PG medical courses in India, one needs to qualify NEET PG 2023 which is to be held on 5th March, 2023. NRIs who wish to join medical colleges in India for their post graduate studies must qualify the NEET exam as well as fulfil other criterias.', NULL, '2023-03-04 17:55:31', '2023-03-04 17:55:31'),
(40, 'MD/MS Admission 2023: Top Medical Colleges in India to Consider', '<p>MD/MS (Doctor of Medicine/Master of Surgery) is a postgraduate degree program for medical students in India. The admission process for MD/MS in India is highly competitive and students need to clear the NEET PG exam to be eligible for admission to the top medical colleges in India. It requires dedication, hard work and a strong academic background to secure a seat in a top medical college. Choosing the right medical college is crucial as it determines the quality of education, exposure and job opportunities after completing the course. In this article, we will discuss some of the top medical colleges in India that students can consider for MD/MS admission in 2023.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS), Delhi: AIIMS is a premier medical institute in India that offers MD/MS programs in various specialisations. It is considered one of the best medical colleges in India with world-class infrastructure and faculty.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Christian Medical College (CMC), Vellore: CMC is a private, minority-run medical college in Vellore, Tamil Nadu. It is known for its holistic approach to medical education, excellent infrastructure and experienced faculty. CMC offers MD/MS programs in various specialisations including Surgery, Obstetrics and Gynecology and Pediatrics.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Jawaharlal Institute of Postgraduate Medical Education and Research (JIPMER), Puducherry: JIPMER Puducherry is another top medical college in India that offers MD/MS courses in various specialisations. It has world-class facilities, experienced faculty and a strong focus on research. JIPMER Puducherry is known for its excellent academic curriculum and clinical exposure.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Post Graduate Institute of Medical Education and Research (PGIMER), Chandigarh: PGIMER is a government medical college in Chandigarh known for its rigorous academic curriculum and excellent clinical exposure.It has state-of-the-art facilities, experienced faculty and a strong research focus and offers MD/MS programs in various specialisations including Anatomy, Pediatrics and Radiology.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>King George&#39;s Medical University (KGMU), Lucknow: KGMU is a government medical college in Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh and offers MD/MS programs in various specialisations including Ophthalmology, Dermatology and Psychiatry. It has a strong academic focus, excellent infrastructure and experienced faculty. KGMU Lucknow is known for its high-quality clinical exposure and job opportunities after completing the course.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Maulana Azad Medical College (MAMC), Delhi: One of the renowned medical colleges of Delhi, MAMC is a government medical college known for its quality education and research opportunities. It offers MD/MS programs in various specialisations including Surgery, Anesthesia and Obstetrics and Gynecology.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Armed Forces Medical College (AFMC), Pune: AFMC is a government medical college in Pune, Maharashtra, managed by the Indian Armed Forces. AFMC offers MD/MS programs in various specialisations including Surgery, Ophthalmology and Psychiatry.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>St. John&#39;s Medical College, Bangalore: St. John&#39;s Medical College is a private medical college in Bangalore, known for its excellent infrastructure, experienced faculty and numerous research opportunities. It offers MD/MS programs in various specialisations including Surgery, Obstetrics and Gynecology and Pediatrics.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Banaras Hindu University (BHU), Varanasi: A government medical college in Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh, known for its high quality education, research opportunities, rigorous academic curriculum and clinical exposure. BHU offers MD/MS programs in various specialisations including Anatomy, Radiology and Orthopedics.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nMadras Medical College, Chennai: A reputed college of Chennai, Madras Medical College is a government medical college that offers MD/MS programs in various specialisations including Surgery, Dermatology and Psychiatry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>MD/MS admission 2023 requires careful consideration of various factors including the quality of education, infrastructure, faculty and research facilities. The above-listed medical colleges in India are some of the best options to consider for MD/MS admission 2023. However, it is important to conduct thorough research and choose a college that aligns with your academic and career goals.</p>', 'mdms-admission-2023-top-medical-colleges-in-india-to-consider', '', '', 1, '2023-03-04', 'MD/MS Admission 2023: Top Medical Colleges in India to Consider', 'MD/MS (Doctor of Medicine/Master of Surgery) is a postgraduate degree program for medical students in India. The admission process for MD/MS in India is highly competitive and students need to clear the NEET PG exam to be eligible for admission to the top medical colleges in India.', NULL, '2023-03-04 18:09:59', '2023-03-04 18:09:59'),
(41, 'MD vs MS: Choosing the Right Specialization for Your Career Goals', '<p>MD and MS are both post-graduate degrees in the field of medicine and they represent different specialisations. MD stands for Doctor of Medicine while MS stands for Master of Surgery. In general, MD focuses on diagnosing and treating medical conditions while MS focuses on surgical procedures. Both specialisations are important in healthcare and can lead to successful careers but choosing the right one for your career goals depends on your personal interests, skills and future aspirations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>MD: Doctor of Medicine</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An MD degree is a general medical degree that focuses on diagnosing and treating medical conditions. It covers a wide range of topics including anatomy, physiology, pharmacology, pathology and clinical medicine. MDs typically work in a clinical setting such as hospitals, clinics or private practices and they are responsible for diagnosing illnesses, prescribing medications and managing patient care.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>MDs can specialise in a variety of areas including paediatrics, cardiology, neurology and more. They can also choose to work in research, teaching or administration. MDs typically have strong communication and interpersonal skills as they work closely with patients and their families.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>MS: Master of Surgery</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An MS degree is a specialised degree that focuses on surgical procedures. It covers a range of topics related to surgery including surgical anatomy, anaesthesia, wound healing and surgical techniques. MSs typically work in a surgical setting such as a hospital or outpatient surgery centre and they are responsible for performing surgical procedures on patients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>MSs can specialise in a variety of areas including orthopaedics, neurosurgery, cardiothoracic surgery and more. They can also choose to work in research, teaching or administration. MSs typically have strong technical skills and attention to detail as surgical procedures require precision and accuracy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Choosing the Right Specialization for Your Career Goals</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When choosing between MD and MS, it&#39;s important to consider your personal interests, skills and future aspirations. Here are some factors to consider:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Interest: What areas of medicine do you find most interesting? If you enjoy working with patients and diagnosing illnesses, MD may be the right choice for you. If you enjoy performing surgical procedures, MS may be a better fit.</li>\r\n	<li>Skills: What are your strengths and weaknesses? If you have strong communication and interpersonal skills, MD may be a good choice. If you have strong technical skills and attention to detail, MS may be a better fit.</li>\r\n	<li>Lifestyle: What kind of lifestyle do you want? MDs typically work regular hours in a clinical setting while MSs may work longer hours in a surgical setting. Consider the demands of each specialisation and how they fit with your personal goals and values.</li>\r\n	<li>Future aspirations: What do you want to achieve in your career? If you want to become a specialist in a particular area of medicine, MD may be the right choice. If you want to become a surgeon, MS may be a better fit.</li>\r\n	<li>Both MD and MS can lead to successful careers in medicine but choosing the right specialisation depends on your personal interests, skills and future aspirations. Consider these factors carefully before making a decision and consult with a mentor or advisor to help guide you in your career path.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'md-vs-ms-choosing-the-right-specialization-for-your-career-goals', '', '', 1, '2023-03-13', 'MD vs MS: Choosing the Right Specialization for Your Career Goals', 'MD and MS are both post-graduate degrees in the field of medicine and they represent different specialisations. MD stands for Doctor of Medicine while MS stands for Master of Surgery. In general, MD focuses on diagnosing and treating medical conditions while MS focuses on surgical procedures. Both specialisations are important in healthcare and can lead to successful careers but choosing the right one for your career goals depends on your personal interests, skills and future aspirations.', NULL, '2023-03-13 10:28:40', '2023-03-13 10:30:49'),
(42, 'MD/MS Admission 2023: Frequently Asked Questions About the Application Process', '<p>If you&#39;re planning to apply for MD/MS admission in 2023, you may have some questions about the application process. Here are some frequently asked questions and their answers to help you prepare for the application process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Q. What are the eligibility criteria for MD/MS admission?</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The eligibility criteria for MD/MS admission may vary depending on the country, institution and program. Generally, candidates must have completed their MBBS or equivalent degree from a recognized institution and obtained a valid medical registration certificate. Additionally, they may be required to meet certain academic criteria such as minimum marks in the qualifying examination or entrance test</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Q&nbsp; When do I need to start preparing for the MD/MS admission process?</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>It&#39;s never too early to start preparing for the MD/MS admission process. Ideally, you should start preparing as soon as possible especially if you plan to apply to competitive programs or institutions. You should research the institutions and programs you&#39;re interested in, gather information about the application process and requirements and start preparing for any entrance exams or interviews.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Q. What documents do I need to submit with my MD/MS application?</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The documents required for the MD/MS application may vary depending on the institution and program. Generally, you will need to submit academic transcripts, proof of medical registration, a passport-sized photograph and a valid ID proof. You may also need to submit other documents such as a statement of purpose, letters of recommendation and entrance exam scores.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Q. How important are entrance exam scores in the MD/MS admission process?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A. Entrance exam scores are usually a critical component of the MD/MS admission process. Many institutions require candidates to take an entrance exam such as NEET-PG, AIIMS-PG or JIPMER-PG to assess their knowledge and aptitude in the field of medicine. The entrance exam scores are often used to shortlist candidates for further evaluation such as interviews or counselling sessions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Q. How can I prepare for the entrance exam for MD/MS admission?</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Preparing for the entrance exam for MD/MS admission can be challenging but there are many resources available to help you. You can enrol in a coaching program or use online resources to practise and improve your knowledge and test-taking skills. You should also focus on strengthening your fundamentals in the relevant subjects such as anatomy, physiology, pharmacology and pathology.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Q. How can I choose the right institution and program for MD/MS admission?</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Choosing the right institution and program for MD/MS admission can be a daunting task. You should consider factors such as the reputation and accreditation of the institution, the availability of faculty and resources, the program curriculum and specialisation options and the location and affordability of the institution. You can also consult with current students or alumni, attend college fairs or information sessions and review online resources to gather information and make an informed decision.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The MD/MS admission process can be complex and competitive but with proper preparation and research, you can increase your chances of success. You should start early, gather all the required documents, prepare for the entrance exam and choose the right institution and program that aligns with your career goals and aspirations.</p>', 'mdms-admission-2023-frequently-asked-questions-about-the-application-process', '', '', 1, '2023-03-13', 'MD/MS Admission 2023: Frequently Asked Questions About the Application Process', 'If you\'re planning to apply for MD/MS admission in 2023, you may have some questions about the application process. Here are some frequently asked questions and their answers to help you prepare for the application process.', NULL, '2023-03-13 10:34:34', '2023-03-13 10:34:34'),
(43, 'NEET UG 2023', '<p>NEET UG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test-Undergraduate) is a medical entrance exam conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA) for admission to undergraduate medical courses like MBBS, BDS, etc. in various medical colleges in India. This year, NEET UG exam will be held on 7th May, 2023. The online registration process for the same has already started on 6th March, 2023 and will be open till 06th April, 2023 (up to 9:00 PM).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application form to register for NEET UG 2023 is available online on the official website <a href=\"https://neet.nta.nic.in/neetug-2023-registration/\">NEET(UG) 2023 Registration | NATIONAL ELIGIBILITY CUM ENTRANCE TEST | India (nta.nic.in)</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1BcWSGdiR6FJbFeOU3q1ai0EDpfLI8ltuB6w-GbpiVno/edit#heading=h.p12qhasjzydh\">General Guidelines:</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1BcWSGdiR6FJbFeOU3q1ai0EDpfLI8ltuB6w-GbpiVno/edit#heading=h.9m1rxmidret9\">Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form:</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1BcWSGdiR6FJbFeOU3q1ai0EDpfLI8ltuB6w-GbpiVno/edit#heading=h.vj5guauhvro\">Application Fees for NEET UG 2023</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1BcWSGdiR6FJbFeOU3q1ai0EDpfLI8ltuB6w-GbpiVno/edit#heading=h.9wwr7mm9dpxh\">Contact Information</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>General Guidelines:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>It will be an offline mode of examination i.e. Pen and Paper mode.</li>\r\n	<li>It will be conducted in 13 languages: English, Hindi, Assamese, Bengali, Gujarati, Kannada, Malayalam, Marathi, Odia, Punjabi, Tamil, Telugu and Urdu.</li>\r\n	<li>NEET UG 2023 will be of a duration of 200 minutes i.e. 3 hours and 20 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Date and Time of the examination: 7th May, 2023 (02:00 PM to 05: 20 PM)</li>\r\n	<li>The exam consists of 200 multiple choice questions from Physics, Chemistry and Biology (Botany and Zoology).&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>There will be 50 questions from each subject, divided into two sections (A and B).</li>\r\n	<li>Out of 200 MCQs, one needs to attempt 180 questions for a total of 720 marks.</li>\r\n	<li>4 marks are awarded for each correct answer while 1 mark is deducted for every incorrect answer.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>There is no limit in regards to the number of attempts for qualifying the NEET UG examination.</li>\r\n	<li>NEET UG exam is applicable for admission to undergraduate courses in all medical disciplines such as MBBS, BDS, BAMS, BUMS, BHMS and BSMS courses across all the medical institutions of India.</li>\r\n	<li>Qualifying NEET UG examination is also mandatory for MNS (Military Nursing Service) aspirants for admission to B.Sc Nursing course at Armed Forces Medical Service Hospitals.</li>\r\n	<li>It is conducted once every year for the current academic session.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Applicants can apply for NEET UG 2023 via the Online mode only on the official website <a href=\"https://neet.nta.nic.in/neetug-2023-registration/\">NEET(UG) 2023 Registration | NATIONAL ELIGIBILITY CUM ENTRANCE TEST | India (nta.nic.in)</a>.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Only one application is accepted for each applicant.</li>\r\n	<li>Read the instructions carefully before filling the application form. The detailed information bulletin is available at <a href=\"https://neet.nta.nic.in/\">https://neet.nta.nic.in/</a></li>\r\n	<li>Please enter the correct Mobile number or Email in the application form as the same will be used by NTA for further communication or correspondence.</li>\r\n	<li>To upload address proof (Present and permanent address) during the online Application Form of NEET (UG) &ndash; 2023, one may upload AADHAAR Card, Domicile Certificate, Passport, Voter ID card, etc. Both documents (if applicable) are to be merged and uploaded in a single pdf file. If the Present and Permanent addresses are the same, then the same document will suffice.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Application Fees for NEET UG 2023<br />\r\n&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category of Candidate</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Rs. 1700</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General -EWS/OBC-NCL</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Rs. 1600</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/PwBD/Third Gender</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Rs. 1000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Processing charges &amp; Goods and Services Tax (GST) are to be paid by the candidate, as applicable</li>\r\n	<li>For applicants appearing for NEET UG at Centres Outside India, a standard fee of rs 9500 is to be paid irrespective of the category of the candidate.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Contact Information</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>For any queries or clarification, the candidates can contact at 011-40759000 or email at neet@nta.ac.in</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'neet-ug-2023', '', '', 1, '2023-03-13', 'NEET UG 2023', 'NEET UG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test-Undergraduate) is a medical entrance exam conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA) for admission to undergraduate medical courses like MBBS, BDS, etc. in various medical colleges in India.', NULL, '2023-03-13 16:40:28', '2023-03-13 16:40:28');
