(44, 'NEET PG 2023 Result Out', '<p>NEET PG 2023 is a postgraduate medical entrance exam in India that is usually conducted once a year by the National Board of Examinations (NBE). The exam is a computer-based test and is open to all Indian citizens with an MBBS degree and consists of multiple-choice questions covering topics such as Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pharmacology, Microbiology, Pathology and Forensic Medicine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 was conducted on 5th March, 2023 and the result for the same has been declared on 14th March, 2023 on the official website of <a href=\"https://natboard.edu.in/parinam/neetpg/index\">नीट पीजी परिणाम NEET PG RESULT (natboard.edu.in)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scorecards of the candidates will be available for download on or after March 25, 2023 at <a href=\"https://nbe.edu.in/\">https://nbe.edu.in/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 Cut off:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cut-off scores as per the various categories are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Cut-off (out of 800)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General/EWS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>50th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>291</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General- PwBD</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>45th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>274</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/OBC (Including PwBD)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>40th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>257</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 Counselling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The shortlisted candidates according to the cut-off marks and other eligibility criteria will be called for counselling to take admission to NEET PG courses across the various colleges of India. The counselling schedule for the NEET PG 2023 has not been released yet and shall be notified soon by the Medical Counselling Committee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 Counselling is conducted for admission under the following quotas:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>50% All India Quota Seats</li>\r\n	<li>50% State Quota Seats</li>\r\n	<li>Deemed Universities</li>\r\n	<li>Central Universities (DU, AMU, BHU)</li>\r\n	<li>ESIC Colleges</li>\r\n	<li>Armed Forces Medical Services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>There will be 4 rounds of counselling for NEET PG 2023 i.e Round 1, Round 2, Mop up Round and Stray Vacancy Round. Depending on the choice of institute, cut-off scores, reservation policy as well as other eligibility criteria of the medical institutes, seats are alloted separately for each round.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps for NEET PG Counselling Registration:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Visit the official website of Medical Council Committee, mcc.nic.in</li>\r\n	<li>Go to PG Medical Counselling</li>\r\n	<li>Register by means of email ID and Phone number.</li>\r\n	<li>Complete the application form</li>\r\n	<li>Fill in the preferred college and course, mark details, rank in the NEET PG examination.</li>\r\n	<li>Pay the registration fee online.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Documents required for Counselling:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The candidates are required to keep the following documents (in original) handy for NEET PG Counselling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Admit Card</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Score card or Rank letter</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 seat allotment letter</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS Mark Sheets of all the years</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS Degree Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Internship Completion Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Class X Certificate for date of birth proof</li>\r\n	<li>Registration Certificate (Permanent or Provisional) issued by MCI/ SMC</li>\r\n	<li>Photo ID proof</li>\r\n	<li>Disability Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Caste Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Non-Creamy layer Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 Counselling Fees</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>College</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Non-Refundable Fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Refundable fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>For 50% AIQ/ Central Universities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>1000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>25,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/OBC</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>500</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>10,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>For Deemed Universities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>All Categories</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>5,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>2,00,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>With the NEET PG 2023 result out, the process for the counselling shall begin anytime soon and thus, the eligible candidates are advised to be well prepared with the choice filling, required documents and other relevant details.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'neet-pg-2023-result-out', '', '', 1, '2023-03-16', 'NEET PG 2023 Result Out', 'NEET PG 2023 is a postgraduate medical entrance exam in India that is usually conducted once a year by the National Board of Examinations (NBE). The exam is a computer-based test and is open to all Indian citizens with an MBBS degree and consists of multiple-choice questions covering topics such as Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pharmacology, Microbiology, Pathology and Forensic Medicine.', NULL, '2023-03-16 15:23:09', '2023-03-16 15:23:09'),
(45, 'Medical Education Common Entrance Examination for Bachelor Level 2023 - Result Out', '<p>The Medical Education Common Entrance Examination (MECEE) is an entrance exam conducted by the Medical Education Commission in Nepal for students seeking admission to Bachelor-level medical programs such as MBBS, BDS, B.Sc Nursing and BPH. The exam is one of the most important exams for students who wish to pursue a career in the medical field in Nepal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The MECEE exam tests the candidate&#39;s knowledge and aptitude in areas such as Physics, Chemistry, Biology and Mathematics. The exam is conducted in a multiple-choice question format and has a duration of three hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students who qualify the MECEE- BL exam are eligible to apply for admission to various medical colleges and universities in Nepal. The admission process is based on the merit list of the MECEE exam and the availability of seats in the respective colleges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible to appear for the MECEE exam, candidates must have passed their intermediate (10+2) examination with a minimum aggregate of 50% marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology. The eligibility criteria for different medical programs may vary and candidates must check the specific eligibility criteria for the program they wish to apply for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The MECEE exam is conducted in various centres across Nepal. Candidates can choose the centre nearest to their location while filling up the application form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The MECEE exam syllabus is based on the curriculum prescribed by the Nepal Medical Council. The syllabus covers topics such as Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pathology, Microbiology, Pharmacology and Forensic Medicine among others.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Medical Education Common Entrance Examination for Bachelor Level 2023 was conducted on 8th March, 2023 and the results for the same were declared on 15th March, 2023. The results are published online at https://entrance.mec.gov.np/ and candidates can check their results by logging in with their roll number and date of birth. The merit list is prepared based on the marks obtained in the MECEE exam. For any dissatisfaction regarding the published result, the candidate may request for re-totalling by filling up the form available on the website and mailing the same to <a href=\"mailto:retotal@mec.gov.np\">retotal@mec.gov.np</a>. The deadline for applying for retotalling is from 22nd March, 2023 at 10:00 AM to 24th March, 2023 till 05:00PM. The candidate also needs to deposit a voucher of NRs 1000/- at the account number mentioned on the official website as fees for retotalling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates who qualify the exam are eligible to apply for admission to various medical colleges and universities in Nepal. The admission process is based on the merit list of the MECEE exam and the availability of seats in the respective colleges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Medical Education Common Entrance Examination for Bachelor Level is a crucial exam for students who wish to pursue a career in the medical field in Nepal. The MECEE exam provides a fair and transparent platform for students to showcase their</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Medical Education Common Entrance Examination for Bachelor Level is a crucial exam for students who wish to pursue a career in the medical field in Nepal. The MECEE exam provides a fair and transparent platform for students to showcase their knowledge and aptitude and opens up opportunities for admission to various medical colleges and universities in Nepal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'medical-education-common-entrance-examination-for-bachelor-level-2023-result-out', '', '', 1, '2023-03-17', 'Medical Education Common Entrance Examination for Bachelor Level 2023 - Result Out', 'The Medical Education Common Entrance Examination (MECEE) is an entrance exam conducted by the Medical Education Commission in Nepal for students seeking admission to Bachelor-level medical programs such as MBBS, BDS, B.Sc Nursing and BPH. The exam is one of the most important exams for students who wish to pursue a career in the medical field', NULL, '2023-03-17 16:13:13', '2023-03-17 16:13:13'),
(46, 'NEET UG 2023 Syllabus and Exam Pattern', '<p>NEET-UG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Undergraduate) is a national-level medical entrance exam conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA) for admission to undergraduate medical courses (MBBS/BDS) in various government and private medical colleges in India. This year, the exam will be conducted on 7th May, 2023 and to prepare for the same, one needs to be aware about the exam pattern and the syllabus covered in the examination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exam Pattern of NEET UG 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exam Mode: The exam is conducted in offline mode, i.e., Pen and Paper-based Test (PBT).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Duration: The duration of the exam is 3 hours and 20 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Language: The question paper is available in 13 languages including English, Hindi, Assamese, Bengali, Gujarati, Kannada, Malayalam, Marathi, Odia, Punjabi, Tamil, Telugu and Urdu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sections: The question paper consists of 200 multiple-choice questions (MCQs) out of which one needs to attempt only 180 questions from three subjects: Physics, Chemistry, and Biology (Botany and Zoology). Each section consists of 50 questions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Marking Scheme: Each correct answer is awarded 4 marks, and 1 mark is deducted for each wrong answer. No marks are deducted for unanswered questions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Total Marks: The maximum marks that can be obtained are 720.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Syllabus of NEET UG 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Physics: Physical World and Measurement, Kinematics, Laws of Motion, Work, Energy and Power, Motion of System of Particles and Rigid Body, Gravitation, Properties of Bulk Matter, Thermodynamics, Behavior of Perfect Gas and Kinetic Theory, Oscillations and Waves, Electrostatics, Current Electricity, Magnetic Effects of Current and Magnetism, Electromagnetic Induction and Alternating Currents, Electromagnetic Waves, Optics, Dual Nature of Matter and Radiation, Atoms and Nuclei, Electronic Devices.</li>\r\n	<li>Chemistry: Some Basic Concepts of Chemistry, Structure of Atom, Classification of Elements and Periodicity in Properties, Chemical Bonding and Molecular Structure, States of Matter: Gases and Liquids, Thermodynamics, Equilibrium, Redox Reactions, Hydrogen, s-Block Elements (Alkali and Alkaline Earth Metals), Some p-Block Elements, Organic Chemistry-Some Basic Principles and Techniques, Hydrocarbons, Environmental Chemistry, Solid State, Solutions, Electrochemistry, Chemical Kinetics, Surface Chemistry, General Principles and Processes of Isolation&nbsp;of Elements, p-Block Elements, d and f Block Elements, Coordination Compounds, Haloalkanes and Haloarenes, Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers, Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids, Organic Compounds Containing Nitrogen, Biomolecules, Polymers, Chemistry in Everyday Life.</li>\r\n	<li>Biology: Diversity in Living World, Structural Organization in Animals and Plants, Cell Structure and Function, Plant Physiology, Human Physiology, Reproduction, Genetics and Evolution, Biology and Human Welfare, Biotechnology and Its Applications, Ecology and Environment.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Tips for NEET UG 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Preparing for NEET-UG 2023 can be a daunting task, but with the right approach and resources, it can be made manageable. Here are some tips for NEET-UG 2023 preparation:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Understand the syllabus: Start by understanding the NEET-UG 2023 syllabus thoroughly. This will help you to focus on the important topics and allocate your study time effectively.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Create a study plan: Develop a study plan that covers all the topics and gives you enough time to revise and practice. Divide your study sessions into small and manageable blocks to avoid burnout.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use quality study material: Use standard textbooks, reference books, and online resources for your preparation. This will ensure that you have access to accurate and updated information.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Take mock tests: Take mock tests regularly to assess your preparation and identify your weak areas. This will help you to focus on the areas that need improvement.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Solve previous year question papers: Solving previous year question papers is an excellent way to get familiar with the exam pattern and practice time management.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Seek guidance: Seek guidance from experienced teachers, tutors, and mentors who can help you with your preparation and clarify your doubts.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stay healthy: Take care of your physical and mental health by eating a balanced diet, getting enough sleep, and exercising regularly. This will help you to stay focused and alert during your preparation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember, consistent effort and practice are key to success in NEET-UG 2023. Stay motivated and stay on track with your preparation. Good luck!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'neet-ug-2023-syllabus-and-exam-pattern', '', '', 1, '2023-03-20', 'NEET UG 2023 Syllabus and Exam Pattern', 'NEET-UG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Undergraduate) is a national-level medical entrance exam conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA) for admission to undergraduate medical courses (MBBS/BDS) in various government and private medical colleges in India. This year, the exam will be conducted on 7th May, 2023 and to prepare for the same, one needs to be aware about the exam pattern and the syllabus covered in the examination.', NULL, '2023-03-20 10:56:31', '2023-03-20 10:56:31'),
