(48, 'NEET PG 2023 Participating Colleges in Karnataka', '<p>NEET-PG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Postgraduate) is a national-level medical entrance exam conducted by the National Board of Examinations (NBE) for admission to various postgraduate medical courses, such as MD/MS/Diploma in various government and private medical colleges in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to make an informed choice about MD/MS admissions in your desired choice of institution, it is necessary to be aware of all the colleges participating in the NEET PG 2023 Counselling now that the result of the exam has been released and the counselling for it will start soon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Application form for Counselling for MD MS admissions in Karnataka:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Karnataka, the Karnataka Examination Authority (KEA) administers the MD and MS admissions counselling; the procedure of which has not yet begun. The application form for NEET PG 2023 Counselling for admission to postgraduate <strong>MD/MS program</strong>mes at the various colleges in Karnataka will be available at official website <a href=\"https://cetonline.karnataka.gov.in/kea/indexnew\">KEA | Home (karnataka.gov.in)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A verification slip will be generated by KEA following registration and verification of all provided documents. Candidates must double-check all the information on the verification slip and immediately notify KEA of any errors. The candidate&#39;s security key, which is necessary for the remainder of the admissions process, will also be on the verification slip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for PG admissions in Karnataka</p>\r\n\r\n<p>General: 50th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>General with physical disabilities: 45th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC/ST/OBC: 40th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC/ST/OBC with physical disabilities: 40th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Private Medical Colleges of Karnataka for <strong>MD/MS admission</strong> through NEET PG 2023 scores</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the best priva