0; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:158px\">\r\n			<p>Trichy SRM Medical College Hospital &amp; Research Centre, Trichy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:117px\">\r\n			<p>Trichy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:97px\">\r\n			<p>Trust</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:208px\">\r\n			<p>The Tamilnadu Dr. MGR Medical University,Chennai</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a summarised list of private medical colleges of Tamil Nadu for your reference. For a detailed list, kindly check the official website of National Medical Commission:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nmc.org.in/information-desk/college-and-course-search/\">College and Course Search | NMC</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>https://www.nmc.org.in/information-desk/college-and-course-search/<a href=\"#https://www.nmc.org.in/information-desk/college-and-course-search/\">https://www.nmc.org.in/information-desk/college-and-course-search/</a><a id=\"https://www.nmc.org.in/information-desk/college-and-course-search/\" name=\"https://www.nmc.org.in/information-desk/college-and-course-search/\"></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 Counselling for State Quota seats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In India, admissions to the 50% AIQ seats at government, government-aided and private institutions are handled by the Medical Counselling Committee (MCC). Although the remaining 50% of these colleges are also filled using the NEET PG scores, the state governments in each state provide the counselling for these seats.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tamil Nadu NEET PG Counselling 2023 is conducted by the Directorate of Medical Education (DME), Chennai, the dates of which shall be announced soon on the official website <a href=\"https://tnmedicalselection.net/\">Selection Committee- DME (tnmedicalselection.net)</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For state-wise online registration, visit <a href=\"#www.nmc.org.in/information-desk/state-medical-councils/list-of-state-medical-councils/\" id=\"www.nmc.org.in/information-desk/state-medical-councils/list-of-state-medical-councils/\" name=\"www.nmc.org.in/information-desk/state-medical-councils/list-of-state-medical-councils/\">www.nmc.org.in/information-desk/state-medical-councils/list-of-state-medical-councils/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG Cut Off 2023 for <strong>MD/MS admissions in Tamil Nadu</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>General: 50th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>General with physical disabilities: 45th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC/ST/OBC: 40th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SC/ST/OBC with physical disabilities: 40th percentile</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'jee-mains-2023', '', '', 1, '2023-03-22', 'NEET PG 2023 Participating Colleges in Tamil Nadu', 'NEET-PG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test for Postgraduate) is a national-level medical entrance exam conducted by the National Board of Examinations (NBE) for admission to various postgraduate medical courses such as MD/MS/Diploma in various government and private medical colleges in India.', NULL, '2023-03-22 16:17:03', '2023-03-22 16:17:03'),
(50, 'MBBS in Nepal', '<p>MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery) is a five and a half-year undergraduate program that prepares students for a career in medicine. Nepal has several medical colleges that offer MBBS programs. These colleges are recognized by the Nepal Medical Council as well as the Medical Council of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What are the Benefits of studying MBBS in Nepal?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Studying MBBS in Nepal has become popular among international students in recent years and here are some reasons why:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Affordable Tuition Fees: The cost of studying MBBS in Nepal is relatively cheaper than many other countries offering similar courses making it an attractive option for students on a budget.</li>\r\n	<li>Quality Education: Nepal&#39;s medical colleges have a good reputation for providing quality education with highly skilled faculty members and modern medical facilities. Many colleges in Nepal are affiliated with reputed universities providing students with globally recognized degrees.</li>\r\n	<li>English Medium of Instruction: Nepal has English as its official language of instruction making it easier for international students to understand and follow the course material.</li>\r\n	<li>Similar Curriculum: Nepal follows a similar curriculum to India which makes it easier for Indian students to adjust and study in Nepal. This also helps in preparing for the Medical Council of India (MCI) screening test which is mandatory for Indian students to practise in India.</li>\r\n	<li>Cultural Similarity: Nepal shares many cultural similarities with India which helps students to adapt to the new environment easily.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>What are the various Medical Colleges in Nepal?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nepal has several medical colleges that offer MBBS programs, including&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Nepalgunj Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Kathmandu University School of Medical Sciences&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Patan Academy of Health Sciences</li>\r\n	<li>B P Koirala Institute of Health Sciences</li>\r\n	<li>Kist Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Birat Medical College</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>These colleges have well-equipped classrooms and laboratories and experienced faculty members who provide high-quality education to students.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What is the Eligibility Criteria for pursuing MBBS in Nepal?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To pursue an MBBS degree in Nepal, students must have completed their 10+2 or an equivalent examination with a minimum of 50% aggregate marks in Physics, Chemistry, and Biology. They must have also completed 17 years of age on or before 31st December of the same academic year. Also, qualifying NEET exam is mandatory for admission to MBBS courses in Nepal, but IELTS or TOEFL certification is not required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What is the Admission Process for MBBS in Nepal?</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Apply for admission online on the university portal.</li>\r\n	<li>Scan the relevant documents (Passport copy, Birth certificate, Copy of Mark Sheets, 8 Passport size photographs, Medical fitness certificate)</li>\r\n	<li>Invitation letters to shortlisted students will be received within 48 hours.</li>\r\n	<li>Pay the registration fees.</li>\r\n	<li>Apply for Visa</li>\r\n	<li>Fly to Nepal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon completion of the MBBS program in Nepal, students can pursue a career in medicine in Nepal or other countries. However, students who wish to practise medicine in India must clear the Foreign Medical Graduates Examination (FMGE) to be eligible for medical registration in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Studying MBBS in Nepal is an excellent option for students who wish to pursue a career in medicine. The program is affordable, the colleges are well-equipped and the faculty members are experienced. Upon completion of the program, students can pursue a career in medicine in Nepal or other countries.</p>', 'mbbs-in-nepal', '167964015782.jpg', '167964015766.jpg', 1, '2023-03-24', 'MBBS in Nepal', 'MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery) is a five and a half-year undergraduate program that prepares students for a career in medicine. Nepal has several medical colleges that offer MBBS programs. These colleges are recognized by the Nepal Medical Council as well as the Medical Council of India.', NULL, '2023-03-24 11:42:37', '2023-03-24 11:42:37');
