(51, 'NEET UG 2023', '<p>NEET UG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test-Undergraduate) is a medical entrance exam conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA) for admission to undergraduate medical courses like MBBS, BDS, etc. in various medical colleges in India. This year, NEET UG exam will be held on 7th May, 2023. The online registration process for the same has already started on 6th March, 2023 and will be open till 06th April, 2023 (up to 9:00 PM).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application form to register for NEET UG 2023 is available online on the official website <a href=\"https://neet.nta.nic.in/neetug-2023-registration/\">NEET(UG) 2023 Registration | NATIONAL ELIGIBILITY CUM ENTRANCE TEST | India (nta.nic.in)</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#General Guidelines:\" id=\"General Guidelines:\" name=\"General Guidelines:\">General Guidelines:</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form:\" name=\"Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form:\"><strong>Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://Application Fees for NEET UG 2023\" id=\"Application Fees for NEET UG 2023\" name=\"Application Fees for NEET UG 2023\">Application Fees for NEET UG 2023</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#Contact Information\" id=\"Contact Information\" name=\"Contact Information\">Contact Information</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>General Guidelines:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>It will be an offline mode of examination i.e. Pen and Paper mode.</li>\r\n	<li>It will be conducted in 13 languages: English, Hindi, Assamese, Bengali, Gujarati, Kannada, Malayalam, Marathi, Odia, Punjabi, Tamil, Telugu and Urdu.</li>\r\n	<li>NEET UG 2023 will be of a duration of 200 minutes i.e. 3 hours and 20 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Date and Time of the examination: 7th May, 2023 (02:00 PM to 05: 20 PM)</li>\r\n	<li>The exam consists of 200 multiple choice questions from Physics, Chemistry and Biology (Botany and Zoology).&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>There will be 50 questions from each subject, divided into two sections (A and B).</li>\r\n	<li>Out of 200 MCQs, one needs to attempt 180 questions for a total of 720 marks.</li>\r\n	<li>4 marks are awarded for each correct answer while 1 mark is deducted for every incorrect answer.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>There is no limit in regards to the number of attempts for qualifying the NEET UG examination.</li>\r\n	<li>NEET UG exam is applicable for admission to undergraduate courses in all medical disciplines such as MBBS, BDS, BAMS, BUMS, BHMS and BSMS courses across all the medical institutions of India.</li>\r\n	<li>Qualifying NEET UG examination is also mandatory for MNS (Military Nursing Service) aspirants for admission to B.Sc Nursing course at Armed Forces Medical Service Hospitals.</li>\r\n	<li>It is conducted once every year for the current academic session.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Applicants can apply for NEET UG 2023 via the Online mode only on the official website <a href=\"https://neet.nta.nic.in/neetug-2023-registration/\">NEET(UG) 2023 Registration | NATIONAL ELIGIBILITY CUM ENTRANCE TEST | India (nta.nic.in)</a>.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Only one application is accepted for each applicant.</li>\r\n	<li>Read the instructions carefully before filling the application form. The detailed information bulletin is available at <a href=\"https://neet.nta.nic.in/\">https://neet.nta.nic.in/</a></li>\r\n	<li>Please enter the correct Mobile number or Email in the application form as the same will be used by NTA for further communication or correspondence.</li>\r\n	<li>To upload address proof (Present and permanent address) during the online Application Form of NEET (UG) &ndash; 2023, one may upload AADHAAR Card, Domicile Certificate, Passport, Voter ID card, etc. Both documents (if applicable) are to be merged and uploaded in a single pdf file. If the Present and Permanent addresses are the same, then the same document will suffice.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Application Fees for NEET UG 2023</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category of Candidate</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Rs. 1700</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General -EWS/OBC-NCL</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Rs. 1600</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/PwBD/Third Gender</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Rs. 1000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Processing charges &amp; Goods and Services Tax (GST) are to be paid by the candidate, as applicable</li>\r\n	<li>For applicants appearing for NEET UG at Centres Outside India, a standard fee of rs 9500 is to be paid irrespective of the category of the candidate.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact Information</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For any queries or clarification, the candidates can contact at 011-40759000 or email at neet@nta.ac.in</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'neet-ug-2023', '1679641033100.jpg', '167964103354.jpg', 1, '2023-03-24', 'NEET UG 2023', 'NEET UG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test-Undergraduate) is a medical entrance exam conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA) for admission to undergraduate medical courses like MBBS, BDS, etc.', NULL, '2023-03-24 11:57:13', '2023-03-24 12:04:25'),
(52, 'NEET PG 2023 Result Out', '<p>NEET PG 2023 is a postgraduate medical entrance exam in India that is usually conducted once a year by the National Board of Examinations (NBE). The exam is a computer-based test and is open to all Indian citizens with an MBBS degree and consists of multiple-choice questions covering topics such as Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pharmacology, Microbiology, Pathology and Forensic Medicine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 was conducted on 5th March, 2023 and the result for the same has been declared on 14th March, 2023 on the official website of <a href=\"https://natboard.edu.in/parinam/neetpg/index\">नीट पीजी परिणाम NEET PG RESULT (natboard.edu.in)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scorecards of the candidates will be available for download on or after March 25, 2023 at <a href=\"https://nbe.edu.in/\">https://nbe.edu.in/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 Cut off:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cut-off scores as per the various categories are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Cut-off (out of 800)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General/EWS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>50th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>291</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General- PwBD</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>45th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>274</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/OBC (Including PwBD)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>40th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>257</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 Counselling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The shortlisted candidates according to the cut-off marks and other eligibility criteria will be called for counselling for<strong> MD/MS admissions</strong> across the various colleges of India. The counselling schedule for the NEET PG 2023 has not been released yet and shall be notified soon by the Medical Counselling Committee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 Counselling is conducted for admission under the following quotas:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>50% All India Quota Seats</li>\r\n	<li>50% State Quota Seats</li>\r\n	<li>Deemed Universities</li>\r\n	<li>Central Universities (DU, AMU, BHU)</li>\r\n	<li>ESIC Colleges</li>\r\n	<li>Armed Forces Medical Services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>There will be 4 rounds of counselling for NEET PG 2023 i.e Round 1, Round 2, Mop up Round and Stray Vacancy Round. Depending on the choice of institute, cut-off scores, reservation policy as well as other eligibility criteria of the medical institutes, seats are alloted separately for each round.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps for NEET PG Counselling Registration:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Visit the official website of Medical Council Committee, mcc.nic.in</li>\r\n	<li>Go to PG Medical Counselling</li>\r\n	<li>Register by means of email ID and Phone number.</li>\r\n	<li>Complete the application form</li>\r\n	<li>Fill in the preferred college and course, mark details, rank in the NEET PG examination.</li>\r\n	<li>Pay the registration fee online.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Documents required for Counselling:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The candidates are required to keep the following documents (in original) handy for NEET PG Counselling for <strong>MD/MS admissions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Admit Card</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Score card or Rank letter</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 seat allotment letter</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS Mark Sheets of all the years</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS Degree Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Internship Completion Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Class X Certificate for date of birth proof</li>\r\n	<li>Registration Certificate (Permanent or Provisional) issued by MCI/ SMC</li>\r\n	<li>Photo ID proof</li>\r\n	<li>Disability Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Caste Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Non-Creamy layer Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 Counselling Fees</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>College</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Non-Refundable Fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Refundable fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>For 50% AIQ/ Central Universities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>1000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>25,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/OBC</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>500</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>10,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>For Deemed Universities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>All Categories</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>5,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>2,00,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>With the NEET PG 2023 result out, the process for the counselling shall begin anytime soon and thus, the eligible candidates are advised to be well prepared with the choice filling, required documents and other relevant details.</p>', 'neet-pg-2023-result-out', '167964238219.jpg', '167964238237.jpg', 1, '2023-03-24', 'NEET PG 2023 Result Out', 'NEET PG 2023 is a postgraduate medical entrance exam in India that is usually conducted once a year by the National Board of Examinations (NBE). The exam is a computer-based test and is open to all Indian citizens with an MBBS degree and consists of multiple-choice questions covering topics such as Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pharmacology, Microbiology, Pathology and Forensic Medicine.', NULL, '2023-03-24 12:19:42', '2023-03-24 12:19:42');
