(59, 'NEET PG 2023 Results Declared: Check Your Score Now!', '<p>NEET PG 2023 is a postgraduate medical entrance exam in India that is usually conducted once a year by the National Board of Examinations (NBE). The exam is a computer-based test and is open to all Indian citizens with an MBBS degree and consists of multiple-choice questions covering topics such as Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pharmacology, Microbiology, Pathology and Forensic Medicine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 was conducted on 5th March, 2023 and the result for the same has been declared on 14th March, 2023 on the official website of <a href=\"https://natboard.edu.in/parinam/neetpg/index\">नीट पीजी परिणाम NEET PG RESULT (natboard.edu.in)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scorecards of the candidates will be available for download on or after March 25, 2023 at <a href=\"https://nbe.edu.in/\">https://nbe.edu.in/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>NEET PG 2023 Cut off:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The cut-off scores as per the various categories are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Cut-off (out of 800)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General/EWS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>50th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>291</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General- PwBD</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>45th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>274</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/OBC (Including PwBD)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>40th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>257</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>NEET PG 2023 Counselling</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The shortlisted candidates according to the cut-off marks and other eligibility criteria will be called for counselling for<strong> MD/MS admissions</strong> across the various colleges of India. The counselling schedule for the NEET PG 2023 has not been released yet and shall be notified soon by the Medical Counselling Committee.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>NEET PG 2023 Counselling is conducted for admission under the following quotas:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>50% All India Quota Seats</li>\r\n	<li>50% State Quota Seats</li>\r\n	<li>Deemed Universities</li>\r\n	<li>Central Universities (DU, AMU, BHU)</li>\r\n	<li>ESIC Colleges</li>\r\n	<li>Armed Forces Medical Services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>There will be 4 rounds of counselling for NEET PG 2023 i.e Round 1, Round 2, Mop up Round and Stray Vacancy Round. Depending on the choice of institute, cut-off scores, reservation policy as well as other eligibility criteria of the medical institutes, seats are alloted separately for each round.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Steps for NEET PG Counselling Registration</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Visit the official website of Medical Council Committee, mcc.nic.in</li>\r\n	<li>Go to PG Medical Counselling</li>\r\n	<li>Register by means of email ID and Phone number.</li>\r\n	<li>Complete the application form</li>\r\n	<li>Fill in the preferred college and course, mark details, rank in the NEET PG examination.</li>\r\n	<li>Pay the registration fee online.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Documents required for Counselling:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The candidates are required to keep the following documents (in original) handy for NEET PG Counselling for <strong>MD/MS admissions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Admit Card</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Score card or Rank letter</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 seat allotment letter</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS Mark Sheets of all the years</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS Degree Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Internship Completion Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Class X Certificate for date of birth proof</li>\r\n	<li>Registration Certificate (Permanent or Provisional) issued by MCI/ SMC</li>\r\n	<li>Photo ID proof</li>\r\n	<li>Disability Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Caste Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Non-Creamy layer Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>NEET PG 2023 Counselling Fees</h2>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>College</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Non-Refundable Fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Refundable fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>For 50% AIQ/ Central Universities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>1000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>25,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/OBC</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>500</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>10,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>For Deemed Universities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>All Categories</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>5,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>2,00,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>With the NEET PG 2023 result out, the process for the counselling shall begin anytime soon and thus, the eligible candidates are advised to be well prepared with the choice filling, required documents and other relevant details.</p>', 'neet-pg-result-check-your-result-now', '', '168138782088.png', 1, '2023-04-13', NULL, 'The wait is over! NEET PG 2023 result is out. Check your scorecard now and take the next step towards your dream postgraduate medical program.', NULL, '2023-04-13 17:10:20', '2023-04-13 17:10:20'),
(60, 'MBBS in Russia', '<p>Studying MBBS in Russia is the preferred choice among Indian students due to the country&#39;s affordable tuition fees, high-quality education and globally recognized medical curriculum. For many, many years, Russian universities have been among the topmost choices for Indian students seeking MBBS degrees. In regard to the quality of medical education, Russia ranks eighth in the world and it has been the home to thousands of Indian MBBS students who are now highly successful doctors all around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits of Studying MBBS in Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pursuing MBBS from Russia is comparatively cheaper than that from India.</li>\r\n	<li>Approved by NMC/MCI</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS degree from Russia is globally recognised.</li>\r\n	<li>Highly skilled faculties using the latest teaching and learning methods.</li>\r\n	<li>Well equipped and state-of-the-art infrastructure of MBBS universities of Russia</li>\r\n	<li>Easy reachability from India.</li>\r\n	<li>Indian food and accommodation provided by the Russian universities for the Indian students.</li>\r\n	<li>FMGE/NeXT coaching provided to Indian students, essential for obtaining a licence for practising medicine.</li>\r\n	<li>Simple and convenient admission process requiring no donation or entrance exam.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MBBS in Russia course details:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Duration of the course is 6 years</li>\r\n	<li>Medium of instruction is English</li>\r\n	<li>The course is approved by MCI/NMC and thus, meets the Indian standards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility criteria for pursuing MBBS in Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Most Russian medical universities require international students to have completed their secondary education (12 years of schooling) with a science background including subjects such as Physics, Chemistry and Biology with at least 50% aggregate marks.</li>\r\n	<li>Qualifying the NEET-UG examination is mandatory for admission to MBBS courses in Russia.</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants should be minimum 17 years of age.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Admission Process for MBBS in Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>University Selection: After meeting the eligibility criteria, it&#39;s important to research and choose a reputable and recognized university as there are numerous medical universities in Russia offering MBBS programs. Consider factors such as the university&#39;s accreditation, rankings, faculty expertise, facilities and location to make an informed decision about the choice of institution.</li>\r\n	<li>Application Process: Once you have selected a university, you will need to submit your application along with the required documents. This may include your high school transcripts, passport copies, medical certificates and other supporting documents as per the university&#39;s requirements. You may also need to pay an application fee.</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance Exam/Interview: Some Russian medical universities may require international students to pass an entrance exam or undergo an interview as part of the admission process. The exam or interview may assess your knowledge in subjects like Biology, Chemistry and Physics as well as your language proficiency. Preparation for the exam or interview is important to increase your chances of getting admitted.</li>\r\n	<li>Invitation Letter: If your application is accepted, the university will send you an invitation letter which is required for obtaining a student visa to study in Russia. The invitation letter will contain details such as the duration of the program, tuition fees and other important information.</li>\r\n	<li>Visa and Travel: Once you receive the invitation letter, you can apply for a student visa at the Russian embassy or consulate in your country. You will need to provide documents such as the invitation letter, passport, proof of medical insurance and other required documents. After obtaining the student visa, you can make travel arrangements to Russia to start your MBBS program.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>List of documents required for MBBS admissions in Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admission form, duly filled</li>\r\n	<li>Class 12th and 10th Passing certificate and Mark sheets</li>\r\n	<li>NEET exam Score card</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of Passport (first and last page)</li>\r\n	<li>Passport-size photographs in white background.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Top medical colleges of Russia offering MBBS admissions to Indian students</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Orel (Oryol)State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kemerovo State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Orenburg State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kazan State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Far Eastern Federal University</li>\r\n	<li>Tver State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kabardino Balkarian State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Omsk State University</li>\r\n	<li>Ingush State University Russia</li>\r\n	<li>Yaroslav-the-Wise Novgorod State University</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'mbbs-in-russia', '', '', 1, '2023-04-14', 'MBBS in Russia', 'MBBS degrees. In regard to the quality of medical education, Russia ranks eighth in the world and it has been the home to thousands of Indian MBBS students who are now highly successful doctors all around the world.', NULL, '2023-04-14 10:56:23', '2023-04-14 10:56:23'),
(61, 'NEET UG 2023', '<p>NEET UG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test-Undergraduate) is a medical entrance exam conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA) for admission to undergraduate medical courses like MBBS, BDS, etc. in various medical colleges in India. This year, NEET UG exam will be held on 7th May, 2023. The online registration process for the same has already started on 6th March, 2023 and will be open till 06th April, 2023 (up to 9:00 PM).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application form to register for NEET UG 2023 is available online on the official website <a href=\"https://neet.nta.nic.in/neetug-2023-registration/\">NEET(UG) 2023 Registration | NATIONAL ELIGIBILITY CUM ENTRANCE TEST | India (nta.nic.in)</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Table of contents:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#General Guidelines:\" id=\"General Guidelines:\" name=\"General Guidelines:\">General Guidelines: </a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form:\" id=\"Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form:\" name=\"Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form:\">Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form: </a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#Application Fees for NEET UG 2023\" id=\"Application Fees for NEET UG 2023\" name=\"Application Fees for NEET UG 2023\">Application Fees for NEET UG 2023 </a></li>\r\n	<li><a id=\"Contact Information\" name=\"Contact Information\">Contact Information</a><strong> </strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>General Guidelines:</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>It will be an offline mode of examination i.e. Pen and Paper mode.</li>\r\n	<li>It will be conducted in 13 languages: English, Hindi, Assamese, Bengali, Gujarati, Kannada, Malayalam, Marathi, Odia, Punjabi, Tamil, Telugu and Urdu.</li>\r\n	<li>NEET UG 2023 will be of a duration of 200 minutes i.e. 3 hours and 20 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Date and Time of the examination: 7th May, 2023 (02:00 PM to 05: 20 PM)</li>\r\n	<li>The exam consists of 200 multiple choice questions from Physics, Chemistry and Biology (Botany and Zoology).&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>There will be 50 questions from each subject, divided into two sections (A and B).</li>\r\n	<li>Out of 200 MCQs, one needs to attempt 180 questions for a total of 720 marks.</li>\r\n	<li>4 marks are awarded for each correct answer while 1 mark is deducted for every incorrect answer.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>There is no limit in regards to the number of attempts for qualifying the NEET UG examination.</li>\r\n	<li>NEET UG exam is applicable for admission to undergraduate courses in all medical disciplines such as MBBS, BDS, BAMS, BUMS, BHMS and BSMS courses across all the medical institutions of India.</li>\r\n	<li>Qualifying NEET UG examination is also mandatory for MNS (Military Nursing Service) aspirants for admission to B.Sc Nursing course at Armed Forces Medical Service Hospitals.</li>\r\n	<li>It is conducted once every year for the current academic session.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Important Instructions for Filling the Application Form:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Applicants can apply for NEET UG 2023 via the Online mode only on the official website <a href=\"https://neet.nta.nic.in/neetug-2023-registration/\">NEET(UG) 2023 Registration | NATIONAL ELIGIBILITY CUM ENTRANCE TEST | India (nta.nic.in)</a>.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Only one application is accepted for each applicant.</li>\r\n	<li>Read the instructions carefully before filling the application form. The detailed information bulletin is available at <a href=\"https://neet.nta.nic.in/\">https://neet.nta.nic.in/</a></li>\r\n	<li>Please enter the correct Mobile number or Email in the application form as the same will be used by NTA for further communication or correspondence.</li>\r\n	<li>To upload address proof (Present and permanent address) during the online Application Form of NEET (UG) &ndash; 2023, one may upload AADHAAR Card, Domicile Certificate, Passport, Voter ID card, etc. Both documents (if applicable) are to be merged and uploaded in a single pdf file. If the Present and Permanent addresses are the same, then the same document will suffice.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Application Fees for NEET UG 2023</h2>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category of Candidate</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Rs. 1700</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General -EWS/OBC-NCL</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Rs. 1600</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/PwBD/Third Gender</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Rs. 1000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Processing charges &amp; Goods and Services Tax (GST) are to be paid by the candidate, as applicable</li>\r\n	<li>For applicants appearing for NEET UG at Centres Outside India, a standard fee of rs 9500 is to be paid irrespective of the category of the candidate.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Contact Information</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>For any queries or clarification, the candidates can contact at 011-40759000 or email at neet@nta.ac.in</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'neet-ug-2023', '', '', 1, '2023-04-14', 'NEET UG 2023', 'NEET UG (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test-Undergraduate) is a medical entrance exam conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA) for admission to undergraduate medical courses like', NULL, '2023-04-14 11:40:19', '2023-04-14 11:40:19'),
(62, 'NEET PG 2023 Result Out', '<p>NEET PG 2023 is a postgraduate medical entrance exam in India that is usually conducted once a year by the National Board of Examinations (NBE). The exam is a computer-based test and is open to all Indian citizens with an MBBS degree and consists of multiple-choice questions covering topics such as Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pharmacology, Microbiology, Pathology and Forensic Medicine.NEET PG 2023 is a postgraduate medical entrance exam in India that is usually conducted once a year by the National Board of Examinations (NBE). The exam is a computer-based test and is open to all Indian citizens with an MBBS degree and consists of multiple-choice questions covering topics such as Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pharmacology, Microbiology, Pathology and Forensic Medicine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 was conducted on 5th March, 2023 and the result for the same has been declared on 14th March, 2023 on the official website of <a href=\"https://natboard.edu.in/parinam/neetpg/index\">नीट पीजी परिणाम NEET PG RESULT (natboard.edu.in)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scorecards of the candidates will be available for download on or after March 25, 2023 at <a href=\"https://nbe.edu.in/\">https://nbe.edu.in/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>NEET PG 2023 Cut off:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The cut-off scores as per the various categories are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Cut-off (out of 800)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General/EWS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>50th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>291</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General- PwBD</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>45th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>274</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/OBC (Including PwBD)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>40th Percentile</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>257</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>NEET PG 2023 Counselling</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The shortlisted candidates according to the cut-off marks and other eligibility criteria will be called for counselling for<strong> MD/MS admissions</strong> across the various colleges of India. The counselling schedule for the NEET PG 2023 has not been released yet and shall be notified soon by the Medical Counselling Committee.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEET PG 2023 Counselling is conducted for admission under the following quotas:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>50% All India Quota Seats</li>\r\n	<li>50% State Quota Seats</li>\r\n	<li>Deemed Universities</li>\r\n	<li>Central Universities (DU, AMU, BHU)</li>\r\n	<li>ESIC Colleges</li>\r\n	<li>Armed Forces Medical Services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>There will be 4 rounds of counselling for NEET PG 2023 i.e Round 1, Round 2, Mop up Round and Stray Vacancy Round. Depending on the choice of institute, cut-off scores, reservation policy as well as other eligibility criteria of the medical institutes, seats are alloted separately for each round.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Steps for NEET PG Counselling Registration:</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Visit the official website of Medical Council Committee, mcc.nic.in</li>\r\n	<li>Go to PG Medical Counselling</li>\r\n	<li>Register by means of email ID and Phone number.</li>\r\n	<li>Complete the application form</li>\r\n	<li>Fill in the preferred college and course, mark details, rank in the NEET PG examination.</li>\r\n	<li>Pay the registration fee online.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Documents required for Counselling:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The candidates are required to keep the following documents (in original) handy for NEET PG Counselling for <strong>MD/MS admissions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Admit Card</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 Score card or Rank letter</li>\r\n	<li>NEET PG 2023 seat allotment letter</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS Mark Sheets of all the years</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS Degree Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Internship Completion Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Class X Certificate for date of birth proof</li>\r\n	<li>Registration Certificate (Permanent or Provisional) issued by MCI/ SMC</li>\r\n	<li>Photo ID proof</li>\r\n	<li>Disability Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Caste Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Non-Creamy layer Certificate (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>NEET PG 2023 Counselling Fees</h2>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>College</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Non-Refundable Fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Refundable fees</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>For 50% AIQ/ Central Universities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>1000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>25,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>SC/ST/OBC</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>500</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>10,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>For Deemed Universities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>All Categories</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>5,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>2,00,000</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>With the NEET PG 2023 result out, the process for the counselling shall begin anytime soon and thus, the eligible candidates are advised to be well prepared with the choice filling, required documents and other relevant details.</p>', 'neet-pg-2023-result-out', '', '', 1, '2023-04-14', 'NEET PG 2023 Result Out', 'NEET PG 2023 is a postgraduate medical entrance exam in India that is usually conducted once a year by the National Board of Examinations (NBE). The exam is a computer-based test and is open to all Indian citizens with an MBBS degree and consists of multiple-choice questions covering topics such as Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pharmacology, Microbiology, Pathology and Forensic Medicine.', NULL, '2023-04-14 13:15:51', '2023-04-14 13:15:51'),
(63, 'Can Tho Medical College 2023 Admission', '<p>The Can Tho University of Medicine and Pharmacy is one of the top five medical universities in Vietnam and is the first government medical college in the country to admit Indian students for MBBS. The CTUMP has expanded from a 200+ staff and training facility for roughly 3000 students in 2003 to 446 faculty lecturers and 657 staff members in the University Hospital to teach and train about 8000 undergraduate and 1000 post graduate students. This growth has been achieved through constant hard work and improvement. Currently, it offers 45 programmes for specialists at levels I and II as well as resident doctors, 14 programmes for Masters and PhDs, 2 programmes for working individuals and 8 full-time programmes based on the credits system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of Contents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Why Study MBBS in Vietnam?\" name=\"Why Study MBBS in Vietnam?\"></a><a href=\"#Why Study MBBS in Vietnam?\"><strong>Why Study MBBS in Vietnam? </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Eligibility Criteria for MBBS admissions at CTUMP:\" name=\"Eligibility Criteria for MBBS admissions at CTUMP:\"></a><a href=\"#Eligibility Criteria for MBBS admissions at CTUMP:\"><strong>Eligibility Criteria for MBBS admissions at CTUMP: </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Admission process\" name=\"Admission process\"></a><a href=\"#Admission process\"><strong>Admission process </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a id=\"Vietnam’s Medical Education System\" name=\"Vietnam’s Medical Education System\"></a><a href=\"#Vietnam’s Medical Education System\"><strong>Vietnam&rsquo;s Medical Education System </strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Why Study MBBS in Vietnam?</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The quality of education in Vietnam has increased significantly over time, which is why more students are choosing to study there. Vietnam places a high value on education and does not compromise on the standard of education it offers its citizens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>MBBS curriculum is similar to that of India and recognised by MCI.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>6 years MBBS course program including 1 year mandatory internship.</li>\r\n	<li>English is the medium of instruction throughout the course program</li>\r\n	<li>Easy reachability from India by a mere 4 hour flight&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Course fees are comparatively cheaper as compared to Indian private medical colleges.</li>\r\n	<li>Comfortable weather and friendly citizens of Vietnam&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Convenient food and accommodation facilities, especially for Indian students.</li>\r\n	<li>Job opportunities for MBBS graduates from Vietnam are numerous.</li>\r\n	<li>Literacy rate of Vietnam is over 90% indicating their emphasis on education.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Eligibility Criteria for MBBS admissions at CTUMP:</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Applicant must be at least 17 years of age</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum 50% aggregate in Class 12th Science subjects i.e. Physics, Chemistry and Biology</li>\r\n	<li>Passed Class 12th from a recognised board with English being the medium of instruction.</li>\r\n	<li>Qualifying NEET examination</li>\r\n	<li>Medically fit to stay and study in Vietnam</li>\r\n	<li>Financially stable to survive and sustain in Vietnam.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1>Admission process</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Meet the Eligibility Criteria</li>\r\n	<li>Submit your application form for MBBS admissions</li>\r\n	<li>If you are shortlisted, you will receive an Offer letter from the institute</li>\r\n	<li>Accept the Offer Letter</li>\r\n	<li>Submit the required documents for confirmation of admission</li>\r\n	<li>Accept the invitation letter&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Apply for visa</li>\r\n	<li>Fly to Vietnam</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Vietnam&rsquo;s Medical Education System</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Vietnam has a well-established medical education system that offers various levels of programs including diplomas, bachelor&#39;s degrees, master&#39;s degrees and doctoral degrees. Medical education in Vietnam typically focuses on practical training as well as theoretical knowledge</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The medical education system in Vietnam is regulated by the Ministry of Education and Training and medical universities and colleges are accredited by the Ministry of Health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medical education in Vietnam has been expanding and improving in recent years, with a focus on enhancing the quality of education, research, and international collaborations. Vietnam is also becoming an increasingly popular destination for international students seeking to study medicine due to its quality education and affordable tuition fees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Studying MBBS in Vietnam offers a unique opportunity for international students to receive high-quality medical education, gain international exposure and experience a rich and diverse culture at an affordable cost.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'can-tho-medical-college-2023-admission', '', '', 1, '2023-04-14', 'Can Tho Medical College 2023 Admission', 'The Can Tho University of Medicine and Pharmacy is one of the top five medical universities in Vietnam and is the first government medical college in the country to admit Indian students for MBBS. The CTUMP has expanded from a 200+ staff and training facility for roughly 3000 students in 2003 to 446 faculty lecturers and 657 staff members in the University Hospital to teach and train about 8000 undergraduate and 1000 post graduate students.', NULL, '2023-04-14 14:02:41', '2023-04-14 14:02:41'),
(64, 'MBBS in Bangladesh', '<p>Bangladesh&#39;s MBBS program has historically been the most practical and affordable option for aspiring doctors from India. Each year, around 5,000 Indian students pursue medical degrees in Bangladesh. MBBS in Bangladesh is one of the top choices for Indian students looking to start their medical careers in Bangladesh because of its high-quality medical education, affordable MBBS fee structure, state-of-the-art infrastructure and technology, highly qualified instructors, affiliations with the best universities in Bangladesh, and comfortable living conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For international students, including Indian students, seat reservations range from 25% to 40% in Bangladesh&#39;s best medical colleges. The opportunity for Indian students to receive a top-notch medical education is increased by the high percentage of MBBS seats reserved for reservations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits of studying MBBS in Bangladesh:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The medical universities of Bangladesh are recognised and approved by NMC/MCI.</li>\r\n	<li>The weather, lifestyle and living conditions of Bangladesh are similar to that of India.</li>\r\n	<li>Bangladesh has the highest pass percentage of FMGE/NeXT examination.</li>\r\n	<li>The MBBS degree from Bangladesh is accepted worldwide and students can easily practise in any country around the globe.</li>\r\n	<li>Food and hostel facilities are provided by most of the medical colleges of Bangladesh.</li>\r\n	<li>The colleges of Bangladesh are affiliated to top hospitals in the country for better practical knowledge and clinical training.</li>\r\n	<li>Very close to India and thus, easy to commute.</li>\r\n	<li>Very nominal fee structure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MBBS in Bangladesh course details:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility criteria for pursuing MBBS in Bangladesh:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Most medical universities in Bangladesh require international students to have completed their Class 12th with a science background, including subjects such as Physics, Chemistry and Biology with at least 50% aggregate marks.</li>\r\n	<li>Passing the NEET-UG examination is mandatory for admission to MBBS courses in Bangladesh</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants should be of minimum 17 years.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The course is of 6 years duration including 1 year of internship.</li>\r\n	<li>Medium of instruction is English</li>\r\n	<li>The course is approved by MCI/NMC and thus, meets the Indian standards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Admission Process for MBBS in Bangladesh:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check your eligibility</li>\r\n	<li>Fill up the application form of the desirous medical college</li>\r\n	<li>Get your documents verified</li>\r\n	<li>Confirm the seat allocated to you by paying the admission fee</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain a medical fitness certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Apply for Visa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Documents required for MBBS admissions in Bangladesh:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admission and fee confirmation letter from the university</li>\r\n	<li>Class 10th Mark sheet and Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Class 12th Mark sheet and Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Passport</li>\r\n	<li>Police Clearance certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Passport size photographs</li>\r\n	<li>Visa form</li>\r\n	<li>Affidavit for sponsorship (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Bank statement of previous 6 months</li>\r\n	<li>Demand draft in favour of the Bangladesh High Commission</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Top medical colleges of Bangladesh offering MBBS admissions to Indian students</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Dhaka National Medical College</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Jahurul Islam Medical College</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. East West Medical College &amp; Hospital</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. International Medical College &amp; Hospital</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Z H Sikder Women&#39;s Medical College</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Dr. Sirajul Islam Medical College</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Popular Medical College &amp; Hospital</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Khwaja Yunus Ali Medical College and Hospital</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Anwar Khan Medical College &amp; Hospital</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Monno Medical College &amp; Hospital</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11. Delta Medical College &amp; Hospital</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12. Tairunnessa Memorial Medical College</p>\r\n\r\n<p>13. Community Based Medical College</p>\r\n\r\n<p>14. US-Bangla Medical College &amp; Hospital</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15. TMSS Medical College</p>\r\n\r\n<p>16.&nbsp; Park view Medical college and university</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'mbbs-in-bangladesh', '', '', 1, '2023-04-14', 'MBBS in Bangladesh', 'Bangladesh\'s MBBS program has historically been the most practical and affordable option for aspiring doctors from India. Each year, around 5,000 Indian students pursue medical degrees in Bangladesh.', NULL, '2023-04-14 17:04:21', '2023-04-14 17:04:21'),
(65, 'Why Study MBBS in Russia', '<p>Studying MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery) in Russia can be a viable option for international students due to several reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Quality Education: Russian medical universities are renowned for offering top-notch medical education with a strong focus on clinical, practical experience.. Many medical universities in Russia are recognized by prestigious international organisations such as the World Health Organization (WHO), UNESCO and the Medical Council of India (MCI).</li>\r\n	<li>Affordable Tuition Fees: Compared to other countries offering medical education, the tuition fees for MBBS in Russia are relatively affordable. The cost of living in Russia is also less as compared to many other countries making it a cost-effective option for studying MBBS.</li>\r\n	<li>English Medium of Instruction: Many medical universities in Russia offer MBBS programs in English which makes it accessible to international students who are not proficient in the Russian language. This eliminates the need to learn Russian language before starting the program, although learning Russian can be an added advantage for communicating with patients during clinical training.</li>\r\n	<li>Globally Recognized Degrees: The MBBS degree obtained from a recognized medical university in Russia is globally accepted and graduates are eligible to appear for licensing examinations in their home country or other countries depending on the regulations of the respective medical boards.</li>\r\n	<li>Experienced Faculty: Russian medical universities have experienced faculty members who are experts in their respective fields. They provide comprehensive training and guidance to students throughout their medical education ensuring a solid foundation for their medical career.</li>\r\n	<li>Practical Clinical Exposure: Russian medical universities provide ample opportunities for practical clinical exposure, allowing students to gain hands-on experience and develop their clinical skills. This practical training prepares students for the real-world challenges of medical practice.</li>\r\n	<li>Multicultural Environment: Studying MBBS in Russia exposes students to a multicultural environment where they can interact with students from various countries, learn about different cultures and broaden their horizons. This can help students develop their interpersonal skills and global outlook.</li>\r\n	<li>Student Support Services: Many medical universities in Russia provide extensive support services to international students including assistance with visa processing, accommodation and other administrative tasks, making the transition to studying in a foreign country smoother and more convenient.</li>\r\n	<li>Food and Accommodation Facilities: Almost all medical universities in Russia provide comfortable accommodation facilities in the form of hostels or dormitories to its students and also, have special provisions of Indian food for the medical students from India.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MBBS in Russia course details:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Duration of the course : 6 years</li>\r\n	<li>Medium of instruction : English</li>\r\n	<li>The course is approved by MCI/NMC and thus, meets the Indian standards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility criteria for pursuing MBBS in Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Passed Class 12th or equivalent with Physics, Chemistry and Biology as mandatory subjects, with at least 50% aggregate marks.</li>\r\n	<li>Qualifying the NEET-UG examination&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants should be minimum 17 years of age.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Top medical colleges of Russia offering MBBS admissions to Indian students</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Orel (Oryol)State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kemerovo State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Orenburg State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kazan State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Far Eastern Federal University</li>\r\n	<li>Tver State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kabardino Balkarian State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Omsk State University</li>\r\n	<li>Ingush State University Russia</li>\r\n	<li>Yaroslav-the-Wise Novgorod State University</li>\r\n</ul>', 'why-study-mbbs-in-russia', '', '', 1, '2023-04-14', 'Why Study MBBS in Russia', 'Studying MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery) in Russia can be a viable option for international students due to several reasons:', NULL, '2023-04-14 17:08:36', '2023-04-14 17:08:36');
