(70, 'Top Colleges for MD in Pulmonary Medicine in India', '<p>MD in Pulmonary Medicine is a postgraduate medical degree that focuses on the diagnosis, treatment and prevention of respiratory diseases. This program is designed to provide advanced training to medical graduates who have completed their MBBS degree or an equivalent qualification.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>During the MD in Pulmonary Medicine program, students will learn about the structure and function of the respiratory system, the pathophysiology of respiratory diseases and various diagnostic and treatment modalities. The program typically takes three years to complete and includes both theoretical and clinical training.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the topics covered in the MD in Pulmonary Medicine program include respiratory physiology, respiratory infections, obstructive and restrictive lung diseases, lung cancer, pulmonary hypertension and critical care medicine. Students will also learn about various diagnostic tests such as pulmonary function tests, bronchoscopy and imaging studies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After completing the MD in Pulmonary Medicine program, graduates can work as pulmonologists, critical care specialists or respiratory physicians in hospitals, clinics or private practice. They can also pursue further sub-specialization by completing a fellowship program in areas such as sleep medicine, interventional pulmonology or pulmonary hypertension.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>MD (Pulmonary Medicine) Course Details:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Duration of the course: 3 years</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility Criteria: MBBS with minimum 50 % aggregate and compulsory 1 year internship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Admission Criteria: Qualifying NEET PG examination.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Top Colleges in India for <strong>MD/MS Admissions</strong> in Pulmonary Medicine:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>For <strong>MD/MS admissions</strong> in Tuberculosis and Respiratory Diseases or Pulmonary Medicine, the following colleges are among the top colleges in India.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<tab