(72, 'Medical Education Common Entrance Examination for Bachelor Level 2023 - Result Out', '<p>The Medical Education Common Entrance Examination (MECEE) is an entrance exam conducted by the Medical Education Commission in Nepal for students seeking admission to Bachelor-level medical programs such as MBBS, BDS, B.Sc Nursing and BPH. The exam is one of the most important exams for students who wish to pursue a career in the medical field in Nepal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The MECEE exam tests the candidate&#39;s knowledge and aptitude in areas such as Physics, Chemistry, Biology and Mathematics. The exam is conducted in a multiple-choice question format and has a duration of three hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students who qualify the MECEE- BL exam are eligible to apply for admission to various medical colleges and universities in Nepal. The admission process is based on the merit list of the MECEE exam and the availability of seats in the respective colleges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible to appear for the MECEE exam, candidates must have passed their intermediate (10+2) examination with a minimum aggregate of 50% marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology. The eligibility criteria for different medical programs may vary and candidates must check the specific eligibility criteria for the program they wish to apply for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The MECEE exam is conducted in various centres across Nepal. Candidates can choose the centre nearest to their location while filling up the application form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The MECEE exam syllabus is based on the curriculum prescribed by the Nepal Medical Council. The syllabus covers topics such as Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pathology, Microbiology, Pharmacology and Forensic Medicine among others.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Medical Education Common Entrance Examination for Bachelor Level 2023 was conducted on 8th March, 2023 and the results for the same were declared on 15th March, 2023. The results are published online at https://entrance.mec.gov.np/ and candidates can check their results by logging in with their roll number and date of birth. The merit list is prepared based on the marks obtained in the MECEE exam. For any dissatisfaction regarding the published result, the candidate may request for re-totalling by filling up the form available on the website and mailing the same to <a href=\"mailto:retotal@mec.gov.np\">retotal@mec.gov.np</a>. The deadline for applying for retotalling is from 22nd March, 2023 at 10:00 AM to 24th March, 2023 till 05:00PM. The candidate also needs to deposit a voucher of NRs 1000/- at the account number mentioned on the official website as fees for retotalling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates who qualify the exam are eligible to apply for admission to various medical colleges and universities in Nepal. The admission process is based on the merit list of the MECEE exam and the availability of seats in the respective colleges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Medical Education Common Entrance Examination for Bachelor Level is a crucial exam for students who wish to pursue a career in the medical field in Nepal. The MECEE exam provides a fair and transparent platform for students to showcase their knowledge and aptitude and opens up opportunities for admission to various medical colleges and universities in Nepal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'medical-education-common-entrance-examination-for-bachelor-level-2023-result-out', '', '', 1, '2023-04-17', 'Medical Education Common Entrance Examination for Bachelor Level 2023 - Result Out', 'The Medical Education Common Entrance Examination (MECEE) is an entrance exam conducted by the Medical Education Commission in Nepal for students seeking admission to Bachelor-level medical programs such as MBBS, BDS, B.Sc Nursing and BPH. The exam is one of the most important exams for students who wish to pursue a career in the medical field in Nepal.', NULL, '2023-04-17 10:09:06', '2023-04-17 10:09:06');
