(88, 'MBBS in Russia', '<p>Russia is the largest country in the world occupying two continents, Europe and Asia. It covers an area of over 17 million square kilometres and has a population of around 144 million people.Russia is known for its rich cultural heritage and&nbsp; has a diverse landscape that includes vast plains, forests, tundra, mountains and numerous rivers and lakes including Lake Baikal, the deepest and oldest lake in the world. It is one of the world&#39;s major economies with vast natural resources including oil, natural gas and minerals. It is a leading global producer and exporter of energy resources. Other significant sectors of the economy include manufacturing, agriculture and technology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some Facts about Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:600px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:301px\">\r\n			<p>Capital</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:299px\">\r\n			<p>Moscow</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:301px\">\r\n			<p>Currency</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:299px\">\r\n			<p>Russian ruble</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:301px\">\r\n			<p>Exchange Rates to INR</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:299px\">\r\n			<p>1 Indian Rupee = 1 Russian Ruble</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:301px\">\r\n			<p>Climate</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:299px\">\r\n			<p>Continental climate.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:301px\">\r\n			<p>Time Difference between India and Russia</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:299px\">\r\n			<p>New Delhi is ahead of Moscow by</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>2 hours 30 minutes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:301px\">\r\n			<p>Travel Time from India to Russia</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:299px\">\r\n			<p>Average flight time</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>21 hrs</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:301px\">\r\n			<p>MBBS Course Duration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:299px\">\r\n			<p>6 years (including 1 year internship)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:301px\">\r\n			<p>NEET Exam</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:299px\">\r\n			<p>Mandatory</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:301px\">\r\n			<p>IELTS/TOEFL</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:299px\">\r\n			<p>Not Required</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:301px\">\r\n			<p>Medium of Teaching</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:299px\">\r\n			<p>English</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Studying MBBS in Russia is the preferred choice among Indian students due to the country&#39;s affordable tuition fees, high-quality education and globally recognized medical curriculum. For many, many years, Russian universities have been among the topmost choices for Indian students seeking MBBS degrees. In regard to the quality of medical education, Russia ranks eighth in the world and it has been the home to thousands of Indian MBBS students who are now highly successful doctors all around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits of Studying MBBS in Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pursuing MBBS from Russia is comparatively cheaper than that from India.</li>\r\n	<li>Approved by NMC/MCI</li>\r\n	<li>MBBS degree from Russia is globally recognised.</li>\r\n	<li>Highly skilled faculties using the latest teaching and learning methods.</li>\r\n	<li>Well equipped and state-of-the-art infrastructure of MBBS universities of Russia</li>\r\n	<li>Easy reachability from India.</li>\r\n	<li>Indian food and accommodation provided by the Russian universities for the Indian students.</li>\r\n	<li>FMGE/NeXT coaching provided to Indian students, essential for obtaining a licence for practising medicine.</li>\r\n	<li>Simple and convenient admission process requiring no donation or entrance exam.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MBBS in Russia course details:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Duration of the course is 6 years</li>\r\n	<li>Medium of instruction is English</li>\r\n	<li>The course is approved by MCI/NMC and thus, meets the Indian standards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility criteria for pursuing MBBS in Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Most Russian medical universities require international students to have completed their secondary education (12 years of schooling) with a science background including subjects such as Physics, Chemistry and Biology with at least 50% aggregate marks.</li>\r\n	<li>Qualifying the NEET-UG examination is mandatory for admission to MBBS courses in Russia.</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants should be minimum 17 years of age.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Admission Process for MBBS in Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>University Selection: After meeting the eligibility criteria, it&#39;s important to research and choose a reputable and recognized university as there are numerous medical universities in Russia offering MBBS programs. Consider factors such as the university&#39;s accreditation, rankings, faculty expertise, facilities and location to make an informed decision about the choice of institution.</li>\r\n	<li>Application Process: Once you have selected a university, you will need to submit your application along with the required documents. This may include your high school transcripts, passport copies, medical certificates and other supporting documents as per the university&#39;s requirements. You will also need to pay a nominal application fee.</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance Exam/Interview: Some Russian medical universities may require international students to pass an entrance exam or undergo an interview as part of the admission process. The exam or interview may assess your knowledge in subjects like Biology, Chemistry and Physics as well as your language proficiency. Preparation for the exam or interview is important to increase your chances of getting admitted.</li>\r\n	<li>Invitation Letter: If your application is accepted, the university will send you an invitation letter which is required for obtaining a student visa to study in Russia. The invitation letter will contain details such as the duration of the program, tuition fees and other important information.</li>\r\n	<li>Visa and Travel: Once you receive the invitation letter, you can apply for a student visa at the Russian embassy or consulate in your country. You will need to provide documents such as the invitation letter, passport, proof of medical insurance and other required documents. After obtaining the student visa, you can make travel arrangements to Russia to start your MBBS program.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>List of documents required for MBBS admissions in Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admission form, duly filled</li>\r\n	<li>Class 12th and 10th Passing certificate and Mark sheets</li>\r\n	<li>NEET exam Score card</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of Passport (first and last page)</li>\r\n	<li>Passport-size photographs in white background.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Top medical colleges of Russia offering MBBS admissions to Indian students</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Orel (Oryol)State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kemerovo State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Orenburg State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kazan State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Far Eastern Federal University</li>\r\n	<li>Tver State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kabardino Balkarian State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Omsk State University</li>\r\n	<li>Ingush State University Russia</li>\r\n	<li>Yaroslav-the-Wise Novgorod State University</li>\r\n</ul>', 'mbbs-in-russia', '', '', 1, '2023-05-06', 'MBBS in Russia', 'Russia is the largest country in the world occupying two continents, Europe and Asia. It covers an area of over 17 million square kilometres and has a population of around 144 million people.Russia is known for its rich cultural heritage and  has a diverse landscape that includes vast plains, forests, tundra, mountains and numerous rivers and lakes including Lake Baikal, the deepest and oldest lake in the world. It is one of the world\'s major economies with vast natural resources including oil, natural gas and minerals. It is a leading global producer and exporter of energy resources. Other significant sectors of the economy include manufacturing, agriculture and technology.', NULL, '2023-05-06 10:24:39', '2023-05-06 10:24:39'),
(89, 'Why Study MBBS in Russia', '<p>Studying MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery) in Russia can be a viable option for international students due to several reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quality Education: Russian medical universities are renowned for offering top-notch medical education with a strong focus on clinical, practical experience.. Many medical universities in Russia are recognized by prestigious international organisations such as the World Health Organization (WHO), UNESCO and the Medical Council of India (MCI).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Affordable Tuition Fees: Compared to other countries offering medical education, the tuition fees for MBBS in Russia are relatively affordable. The cost of living in Russia is also less as compared to many other countries making it a cost-effective option for studying MBBS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>English Medium of Instruction: Many medical universities in Russia offer MBBS programs in English which makes it accessible to international students who are not proficient in the Russian language. This eliminates the need to learn Russian language before starting the program, although learning Russian can be an added advantage for communicating with patients during clinical training.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Globally Recognized Degrees: The MBBS degree obtained from a recognized medical university in Russia is globally accepted and graduates are eligible to appear for licensing examinations in their home country or other countries depending on the regulations of the respective medical boards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Experienced Faculty: Russian medical universities have experienced faculty members who are experts in their respective fields. They provide comprehensive training and guidance to students throughout their medical education ensuring a solid foundation for their medical career.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Practical Clinical Exposure: Russian medical universities provide ample opportunities for practical clinical exposure, allowing students to gain hands-on experience and develop their clinical skills. This practical training prepares students for the real-world challenges of medical practice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Multicultural Environment: Studying MBBS in Russia exposes students to a multicultural environment where they can interact with students from various countries, learn about different cultures and broaden their horizons. This can help students develop their interpersonal skills and global outlook.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Student Support Services: Many medical universities in Russia provide extensive support services to international students including assistance with visa processing, accommodation and other administrative tasks, making the transition to studying in a foreign country smoother and more convenient.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Food and Accommodation Facilities: Almost all medical universities in Russia provide comfortable accommodation facilities in the form of hostels or dormitories to its students and also, have special provisions of Indian food for the medical students from India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>MBBS in Russia course details:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Duration of the course : 6 years</li>\r\n	<li>Medium of instruction : English</li>\r\n	<li>The course is approved by MCI/NMC and thus, meets the Indian standards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility criteria for pursuing MBBS in Russia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Passed Class 12th or equivalent with Physics, Chemistry and Biology as mandatory subjects, with at least 50% aggregate marks.</li>\r\n	<li>Qualifying the NEET-UG examination&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants should be minimum 17 years of age.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Top medical colleges of Russia offering MBBS admissions to Indian students</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Orel (Oryol)State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kemerovo State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Orenburg State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kazan State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Far Eastern Federal University</li>\r\n	<li>Tver State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Kabardino Balkarian State Medical University</li>\r\n	<li>Omsk State University</li>\r\n	<li>Ingush State University Russia</li>\r\n	<li>Yaroslav-the-Wise Novgorod State University</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'why-study-mbbs-in-russia', '', '', 1, '2023-05-06', 'Why Study MBBS in Russia', 'Studying MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery) in Russia can be a viable option for international students due to several reasons:', NULL, '2023-05-06 10:29:52', '2023-05-06 10:29:52'),
(90, 'MBBS in Bangladesh', '<p>Bangladesh is a relatively small country located in South Asia, bordered by India to the west, north, and east, and by the Bay of Bengal to the south. It has a diverse landscape, with the Ganges-Brahmaputra delta dominating the geography as well as numerous rivers, hills and forests.&nbsp; The culture of Bangladesh is diverse and influenced by its history, religion, and geography. The official language is Bengali, and Islam is the predominant religion with a significant Muslim population. Bengali literature, music, dance and festivals are prominent aspects of the culture. Bangladesh is classified as a developing nation, with an economy driven by agriculture, textile and garment manufacturing, and remittances from overseas workers. It has achieved remarkable economic growth in recent years, with a focus on export-oriented industries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some Facts about Bangladesh:</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Capital</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Dhaka</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Currency</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Bangladeshi taka</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Exchange Rates to INR</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>1 Indian Rupee =1.31 Bangladeshi Taka</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Climate</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Tropical monsoon-type climate</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Time Difference between India and Bangladesh</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>New Delhi is behind Dhaka by</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>30 minutes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Travel Time from India to Bangladesh</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Average direct flight time</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>2 hrs 15 mins</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>MBBS Course Duration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>6 years (including 1 year internship)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>NEET Exam</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Mandatory</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>IELTS/TOEFL</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Not Required</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Medium of Teaching</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>English</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladesh&#39;s MBBS program has historically been the most practical and affordable option for aspiring doctors from India. Each year, around 5,000 Indian students pursue medical degrees in Bangladesh. MBBS in Bangladesh is one of the top choices for Indian students looking to start their medical careers in Bangladesh because of its high-quality medical education, affordable MBBS fee structure, state-of-the-art infrastructure and technology, highly qualified instructors, affiliations with the best universities in Bangladesh, and comfortable living conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For international students, including Indian students, seat reservations range from 25% to 40% in Bangladesh&#39;s best medical colleges. The opportunity for Indian students to receive a top-notch medical education is increased by the high percentage of MBBS seats reserved for reservations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits of studying MBBS in Bangladesh:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The medical universities of Bangladesh are recognised and approved by NMC/MCI.</li>\r\n	<li>The weather, lifestyle and living conditions of Bangladesh are similar to that of India.</li>\r\n	<li>Bangladesh has the highest pass percentage of FMGE/NeXT examination.</li>\r\n	<li>The MBBS degree from Bangladesh is accepted worldwide and students can easily practise in any country around the globe.</li>\r\n	<li>Food and hostel facilities are provided by most of the medical colleges of Bangladesh.</li>\r\n	<li>The colleges of Bangladesh are affiliated to top hospitals in the country for better practical knowledge and clinical training.</li>\r\n	<li>Very close to India and thus, easy to commute.</li>\r\n	<li>Very nominal fee structure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MBBS in Bangladesh course details:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The course is of 6 years duration including 1 year of internship.</li>\r\n	<li>Medium of instruction is English</li>\r\n	<li>The course is approved by MCI/NMC and thus, meets the Indian standards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Eligibility criteria for pursuing MBBS in Bangladesh:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Most medical universities in Bangladesh require international students to have completed their Class 12th with a science background, including subjects such as Physics, Chemistry and Biology with at least 50% aggregate marks.</li>\r\n	<li>Passing the NEET-UG examination is mandatory for admission to MBBS courses in Bangladesh</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants should be of minimum 17 years.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Admission Process for MBBS in Bangladesh:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check your eligibility</li>\r\n	<li>Fill up the application form of the desirous medical college</li>\r\n	<li>Get your documents verified</li>\r\n	<li>Confirm the seat allocated to you by paying the admission fee</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain a medical fitness certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Apply for Visa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Documents required for MBBS admissions in Bangladesh:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admission and fee confirmation letter from the university</li>\r\n	<li>Class 10th Mark sheet and Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Class 12th Mark sheet and Certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Passport</li>\r\n	<li>Police Clearance certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Passport size photographs</li>\r\n	<li>Visa form</li>\r\n	<li>Affidavit for sponsorship (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Bank statement of previous 6 months</li>\r\n	<li>Demand draft in favour of the Bangladesh High Commission</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Top medical colleges of Bangladesh offering MBBS admissions to Indian students</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dhaka National Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Jahurul Islam Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>East West Medical College &amp; Hospital</li>\r\n	<li>International Medical College &amp; Hospital</li>\r\n	<li>Z H Sikder Women&#39;s Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Dr. Sirajul Islam Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Popular Medical College &amp; Hospital</li>\r\n	<li>Khwaja Yunus Ali Medical College and Hospital</li>\r\n	<li>Anwar Khan Medical College &amp; Hospital</li>\r\n	<li>Monno Medical College &amp; Hospital</li>\r\n	<li>Delta Medical College &amp; Hospital</li>\r\n	<li>Tairunnessa Memorial Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Community Based Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>US-Bangla Medical College &amp; Hospital</li>\r\n	<li>TMSS Medical College</li>\r\n	<li>Park view Medical college and university</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'mbbs-in-bangladesh', '', '', 1, '2023-05-06', 'MBBS in Bangladesh', 'Bangladesh is a relatively small country located in South Asia, bordered by India to the west, north, and east, and by the Bay of Bengal to the south. It has a diverse landscape, with the Ganges-Brahmaputra delta dominating the geography as well as numerous rivers, hills and forests.', NULL, '2023-05-06 16:02:21', '2023-05-06 16:02:21');
