(120, 'Birat Medical College', NULL, 'birat-medical-college', '', 'nepal', NULL, NULL, '166540190823.jpg', '166540190859.jpg', 'Private', 'Co-Ed', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<p>Birat Medical College (BMC) is the newest medical school in Nepal. Established in 2014 as an extended program of Kathmandu University, BMC is now gearing up for its fifth intake.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:608px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:223px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Name of the College:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:385px\">\r\n			<p>Birat Medical College Biratnagar, Nepal</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:223px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Eligibility criteria:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:385px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Aggregate of 50% in 10+2 or HSE</li>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;Must have PCB as the main subject in 10+2</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:223px\">\r\n			<p><strong>NEET examination required:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:385px\">\r\n			<p>Yes, the required score in the <a href=\"https://www.mbbsadmissionabroad.in/nta-neet-exam-pattern-syllabus-preparation-tips\"><strong>NEET examination</strong></a> is required</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:223px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Entrance examination required:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:385px\">\r\n			<p>No required&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:223px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Approved by:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:385px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Medical council of India</li>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;Medical council of Nepal</li>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;World health organization</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:223px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Medium of education:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:385px\">\r\n			<p>English and Nepali language</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:223px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Course duration:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#ffffff; border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top; width:385px\">\r\n			<p>5.5&nbsp; years</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Complete Eligibility Criteria for MBBS Admission for Indian Students&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Completed 17 years of age, and Completed 10+2 years of education or Intermediate of Science or equivalent, with English, Biology, Physics and Chemistry as main subjects</li>\r\n	<li>Passed in all the subjects mentioned above, securing not less than 50% of marks in the subjects mentioned above put together and obtaining an aggregate of 50% overall</li>\r\n	<li>Candidate should be qualified under NEET-UG</li>\r\n	<li>Must have studied in an English medium school, or have at least studied English as a subject</li>\r\n	<li>Valid Indian passport</li>\r\n	<li>Valid NMC certificate&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documentations Required to Process Admission:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All students proceeding to take admission for MBBS in Nepal must have the below list of documents at the time of admission:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Birth certificate, 10+2 certificate and mark</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct certificate signed by the Head of the Institute student last studied at</li>\r\n	<li>Nationality ID (Aadhar Card/ Passport)&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>8 Passport size Photographs</li>\r\n	<li>NEET Scorecard</li>\r\n	<li>Eligibility certificate and other certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Migration certificates. Invitation letter</li>\r\n	<li>Payment slips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>&nbsp;Fee Structure 2022:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Birat Medical College Biratnagar Fee Structure is Given below, along with&nbsp; tuition fees additional details such as hostel costs, and meal costs is given below .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>INR 25,00,000/- during the first year</li>\r\n	<li>INR 4,40,000/- for the second year</li>\r\n	<li>INR 4,40,000/- during the third year</li>\r\n	<li>INR 4,40,000/- during the fourth year</li>\r\n	<li>INR 4,40,000/- for the fifth year</li>\r\n	<li>The annual hostel fee is INR 90,000.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Three Steap Simple Admission Process for NEET Qualified Indian&nbsp; Students<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1&nbsp; Share Document&nbsp; with College<br />\r\n2. Document Verification Completed and Provisional admission letters shared by college<br />\r\n3. Minimum Amount Student have to pay in the college account for admission confirmation which is mention in the college letter&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 0, '', 1, '{\"name\":\"Birat Medical College\",\"streams\":null,\"degree\":\"MBBS\\/MD\\/MS\",\"exam\":\"NEET\"}', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, '2022-10-10 16:38:28', '2022-10-10 16:38:28');
